Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['About Us', 'Venmo was founded on the principles of breaking down the intimidating barriers around financial transactions to make them intuitive, friendly and yes, even fun. And it worked: people love sending money with Venmo and we’re growing by leaps and bounds.', 'But we’re only just getting started.', 'We want to take that magic of sending money with Venmo and cascade it across every place where people use money. That means connecting people to their money in the most intuitive and fun way possible, then connecting people with each other. Users already love Venmo, but we know there are lots of things we have yet to imagine to make the Venmo experience even more delightful and valuable.', 'All that’s going to take a lot of collaboration. Let’s figure it out together!', 'What You’ll Do', ' ', 'Partner with subject matter experts to document and translate business requirements into technical requirements', ' ', 'Develop and maintain Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Email is the universal communication tool for work. It’s where you discuss work, answer questions, and talk to all of your customers, vendors, and partners. But email wasn’t designed for business and hasn’t evolved with the way you work with a team. So you’re dropping the ball, missing important context, and relying on dozens of siloed apps just to get the job done.', 'With more than 5,000 customers Front is reinventing the inbox so people can accomplish more together. We’ve created one place where you communicate internally and externally, gain context about customers and projects, and access all your other tools so you can be more efficient, more fulfilled, and ultimately happier at work.', 'We’re looking for a collaborative and curious Data Analyst to join the data team. You’ll sit with the data team, working closely with our data engineers and other analysts. As an analytical partner to the leadership of Front, you will be tasked with designing, building and owning the answers to questions that require a deep understanding of our product and business operations. Additionally, you will contribute to the data team’s ongoing responsibility to develop, maintain and promote a system of access to metrics, detailed reports and dashboards.', 'Your work will include open-ended analytical exploration to inform decisions and raise insights, and to enable Front’s operations at scale you will build automated reporting and monitoring based on our business intelligence system and internal tools. You will be in a position of analytical leadership and collaborative partnership, with a focused goal to turn your insights into impact.', 'What will you be doing?', 'Partner with various teams to design and implement their success metrics, ongoing reports and necessary dashboards to ensure their success and comprehension of related data', 'Identify and clearly communicate insights and opportunities through exploratory analysis, including assessing trends, cohort, funnel analyses', 'Contribute to data modeling of underlying data in our warehouse to ensure reliable ground truth data in the form of consumer layers or data marts', 'Encourage other teams to self-serve when your interpretation of the data is not required, either through training or automation of tasks', 'Be a joint owner of the reporting and data access business intelligence tool for the company', 'What skills and experience do you need?', '4+ years experience in a highly analytical and quantitative role', 'Expert in SQL or equivalent data analysis framework', 'Clear written and verbal communication skills to convey the results of your analyses effectively', 'You have an  ownership mentality , focused on defining challenges and solutions', 'You are  impact-focused , eager to jump in and work in a fast-paced environment', 'You are  collaborative , forming trusting relationships with your cross-functional teammates', 'You are a strong  critical thinker , excited to solve ambiguous problems', 'You have a  low ego , focused on learning and open to feedback', ' Additional Preferences ', 'Expertise in data visualization', 'Expertise in data modeling and data warehouse-based analytical work', 'Experience in collaborative research or cross-functional working groups', 'Experience with BI tool-based dashboard creation and reporting at scale', 'B2B SaaS or general startup experience', 'An interest systems thinking', 'Front provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age or disability.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: HEALTHCARE DATA ANALYST
Description: ['Responsibilities', 'JOB SUMMARY:', 'The Healthcare Data Anaylist is skilled in healthcare administration as they are in business management. Healthcare Data Analysts is a quantitative specialists who understand the business needs of a hospital and how to use data to achieve those needs. Their duties include organizing and managing large and varied data sets, analyzing healthcare data to optimize business operations and communicating their findings through the use of data visualization and detailed reports per the direction and requests of the Quality Director.The Healthcare Data Analysts is a diligent problem solvers who uses data in creative ways to reach business goals.', 'Essential Job Functions', 'Compiling and organizing healthcare data.', 'Analyzing data to assist in delivering optimal healthcare management and decision making.', 'Using healthcare data to achieve administrative needs and goals.', 'Understanding data storage and data sharing methods.', 'Investigating data to find patterns and trends.', 'Understanding healthcare business operations.', 'Utilizing different data sources for analyses.', 'Converting data into usable information that is easy to understand.', 'Developing reports and presentations.', 'Communicating analytic insights to management, physicians and other healthcare professionals.', 'Qualifications', 'MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS:', "Associate's degree in related field (Mathematics, Statistics, or Healthcare). Bachelor's degree preferred.", '2 years experience in an analytic role.', 'Proficiency with Windows, Excel, and other database programming.', 'Proficiency with data analytics software for data manipulation.', 'Experience with data visualization tools.', 'Knowledge of data management applications.', 'Proficiency managing electronic medical records.', 'Analytical mindset with good problem-solving skills.', 'Excellent written and verbal communication skills and some knowledge of medical terminology.', 'Good interpersonal skills', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Hospital & Health Care']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['The Role', 'As a Data Analyst on the Supply Chain Automation team, you will analyze and visualize data to help with the successful launch and scale of our various programs and so that we can make better decisions as a company. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Banyan Health Systems', ' has been serving Miami-Dade and Broward Counties since 1970. We provide quality, individualized care to each of our patients. Our system of integrated health services brings together specialized psychiatric care, primary care, pediatrics, geriatrics, and an extensive program of residential and outpatient substance abuse & behavioral health services under one umbrella. At Banyan Health Systems, we believe when individuals are healthy and strong, our communities are better for it.', '\xa0', 'We are currently looking for individuals who share our mission of integrating primary and behavioral health care while providing access to all individuals.\xa0We focus on providing quality and compassionate care in order to assist our patients in living their best life.\xa0We are dedicated to the endless pursuit of excellence and treat everyone with dignity, humanity, and respect.', '\xa0', 'If you share these beliefs and want to join us to make a difference, please take some time to read the post below.', 'EHR Data Analyst -JOB SUMMARY:', 'Responsible for the design, build, testing, training, and support of the electronic medical record (EMR) system. The Analyst requires little to no supervision as they build and maintain the system. The Analyst performs complex design and analysis tasks.', 'EDUCATION AND/OR EXPERIENCE', '3 years of EHR experience or a demonstrated expertise in your application subject matter', 'Bachelor’s degree in Healthcare, Business or Computer/Information Sciences OR an equivalent level of professional experience', 'Strong computer skills including Windows, Outlook, Word, Excel, Visio, and PowerPoint', 'Understanding of the implementation and/or maintenance of EHR NAME Electronic Medical Record systems.', 'IT and operational knowledge of clinical or revenue cycle processes in one or more areas of a hospital, clinic, or business office', 'Advanced understanding of Healthcare operations and structure, general requirements of an integrated delivery system, and use of IT applications in the practicing healthcare environment.', 'Technical expertise in subject matter areas demonstrated by documented experience in analysis, process and workflow design, research, installation/implementation and support of EHR SYSTEM.', 'Must have a minimum of 5 years SQL experience', 'Experience using Data Visualization tools (Tableau, Yellowfin BI, Practice Analytics)', 'Ability to independently prioritize work assignments, meet deadlines and manage multiple projects and/or priorities.', 'LANGUAGE SKILLS:', 'Ability to read, write and speak in\xa0', 'English and Spanish', '\xa0(or other languages) helpful. Must be able to read and comprehend simple instructions, short correspondence, and memorandums. Agility to effectively communicate information both orally and written on one-to-one and small group situations to clients and other employees.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Individual & Family Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Job Posting TitleData AnalystSummaryAbout Self Aware Games', 'Self Aware Games has been creating innovative, genre-defining products since 2006. A winning mix of compelling content and engaging social experiences keeps us top-of-the-charts in the social casino category. Our flagship game, Big Fish Casino, has generated more than $1B in bookings to-date making it one of the best performing mobile games ever. Self Aware Games is based in beautiful downtown Oakland, Calif., and is a business unit of Seattle-based Big Fish Games, Inc., part of Aristocrat Leisure Limited.', 'Here Are a Few More Company Highlights', 'We are looking for passionate and highly creative game engineers, artists, designers, product managers, analysts (and more.) to help build the world’s #1 social gaming company. With a strong portfolio of live games and new products in development we are hiring in all disciplines. If you are a passionate game-maker who wants to innovate, contribute and hone your craft as part of a close-knit, collaborative and inclusive culture, Self Aware Games is for you.', 'We take care of our employees with competitive compensation, great benefits and a variety of perks including frequent team events, catered meals, commuter stipend and free professional massage.', 'We are committed to employee development and advancement with opportunities for growth across Big Fish Games and the Aristocrat family of companies.', 'Our beautiful workspace is open and light-filled and located in the vibrant Uptown neighborhood next to Lake Merritt and a short walk from the 19th Street BART station.', 'Responsibilities', "We are looking for an amazing Data Analyst to work on our social casino products at Self Aware Games Studio in Oakland. You'll be responsible for running ad-hoc analysis, visualizing data, and analyzing our day-to-day operations. Successful candidates for this role have strong SQL and statistics skills, are passionate about games, and are clear communicators.", 'Responsibilities', ' Engage with PMs, designers, CRM managers to identify analysis requirements ', ' Develop a deep understanding of available data to drive ad-hoc analysis and answer questions ', ' Effectively write, present and communicate research results with recommendations ', ' Perform statistical analysis on experimental or business data to validate and quantify trends or patterns identified by business ', 'Build data pipelines, identify new telemetry requirements, create dashboards', 'Collaborate with the live-service team to run multivariate tests', 'Qualifications', ' Bachelor’s degree or equivalent work experience in Computer Science or related discipline such as Statistics, Mathematics, Economics, etc. ', ' Experience writing and optimizing SQL queries, and working with large data sets ', ' Data visualization and dash-boarding experience using Tableau, Looker, or similar ', ' 4+ years in the analytical space ', ' Experience with manipulating and analyzing complex, high-volume, high-dimensionality data from varying sources including collecting, assembling data, cleansing, formatting, and validation of results ', 'Bonus Points', ' Experience in the gaming space ', ' Familiarity with a cloud platform. Name: Data Analytics Analyst
Description: ['Ocean Spray believes that our employees are our best asset and we offer an environment where you can work with exceptionally smart, innovative, passionate teams that are motivated to deliver Ocean Spray products around the world. ', 'Position Summary', 'Ocean Spray is looking for a Data Analytics Analyst, ', 'someone who is an outstanding ', 'data storyteller, ', 'that can be a catalyst in our ongoing effort to become a data driven organization. Someone who can help us explore beyond rear view mirror reporting and tackle predictive/preventative analytics at scale. This role will work across all our business functions, platforms, and operations to perform analytics that supports decisions, and instills a data-first culture.', 'A Day in the Life of a Data Analytics Analyst:', 'Delivering insight to key business function leads throughout the co-operative through a virtual data hub team ', 'Putting forth cohesive business architecture story across various functions through design thinking. Show the art of the possible with rapid analytical prototyping, storytelling. ', 'Building models and designing experiments that seek to uncover truth ', 'Analyzing complex data made of unstructured, semi-structured and structured datasets to drive insights ', 'Active participant in defining data strategy, its execution path, and help build our digital data fabric collaborating with our product partners ', 'Working in a data factory model and work with vendors to scale up and maintain our environment that supports our business functions ', 'What We Are Looking For', 'BA/BS in computer science or related field or equivalent relevant experience, with a focus on data analytics/ data science ', 'Minimum 5 years of related experience. ', 'Experience working in cloud environment (Azure preferred, AWS and GCP experience is acceptable) ', 'Strong understanding of SQL and NoSQL databases, ability to query data from disparate data sources. ', 'Expertise in R, Python and SQL. ', 'Demonstrate ability to lead initiatives and work effectively with others within a complex, cross-functional and fast paced organization ', 'Excellent communication. Ability to present ideas and insights to business stakeholders ', 'Extensive experience with Data Visualization, preferably in PowerBI ', 'CPG industry knowledge ', 'All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or veteran status.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Other', 'Industries', 'Food & Beverages', 'Food Production', 'Consumer Goods']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Who We Are', 'The Farmer’s Dog was created to radically improve the $90 billion global pet food industry — starting with a subscription service that sends freshly-made food directly to customers’ doors. Long term, our aim is to simplify every part of pet care, bettering the lives of the animals who make our lives better. We recently raised our Series B and are backed by early investors of Warby Parker, Dollar Shave Club, Sweetgreen, and Glossier.', "Join The Farmer’s Dog team as we continue to figure out ways of bringing peace of mind to customers, health to their companions, and much-needed change to the way people feed and care for their pets. The Farmer's Dog was", '#mustlovedogs', " Where You'll Come In ", 'At The Farmer’s Dog, we have a very strong culture of making data-driven decisions. The ', ' Data Strategy & Insights ', ' team, specifically, works on constantly bringing our whole organization to higher levels. We turn green into yellow and blue.', 'As a Data Analyst on TFD’s ', ' Data Strategy & Insights ', ' team, you will leverage your strong statistical abilities to uncover meaningful insights from our large variety of data sets and many experiments. You will use your R skills to quickly dive through our data, weed out the randomness and find the true signal. You will find meaningful effects, isolate noise, and share insights that will quickly be turned into actions and leveraged by a variety of stakeholders.', 'This is a highly visible role, working closely with stakeholders across the company, including Growth, Marketing, Operations, Customer Experience, Finance and others. You will have a strong influence on the design and analysis of our experiments and general knowledge procurement.', "How You'll Make An Impact", ' Analyze large data sets and develop custom models to uncover trends, patterns, and insights in customer and business data ', ' Deep-dive into experiment results ', ' Help design new experiments ', ' Create reports & dashboards that support a wide variety of business needs ', ' Interpret consumer research studies and help guide the business strategy based on the results ', ' Work cross-functionally to understand and elevate the analytics functions of experience development, business development, consumer marketing strategy, margin optimization, etc. ', ' Support brand and growth teams who are charged with creating campaigns, messaging, and managing channel initiatives ', ' Bring customer profiles, personalities, and needs to life within the company ', " We're Excited About You Because ", ' TECHNICAL ', ' Highly comfortable with both SQL and R to extract, manipulate, and analyze data ', ' Strong background in Statistics ', ' Ability to switch back and forth between Bayesian and Frequentist approaches ', ' Familiarity with STAN (or rstan / ratanarm) a bonus, but not required ', 'BUSINESS ', ' Proven history of delivering consumer-led business outcomes ', ' Strong focus on customer-centric approaches (what’s best for our customers)', ' Understanding of business initiatives, and how they would show up in data-form ', ' Ability to articulate consumer insights, influence decision making POVs, all the while successfully building productive working relationships with cross-functional teams ', ' Natural curiosity -- asking the next question and seeking to understand at the nuanced level to spark a new idea ', ' Must play nicely with others (humans and dogs)', ' Prefer dogs to other species. ', ' Benefits ', ' Brand new dog-friendly office in Greenwich Village (complete with free-roaming friendly dogs)', ' Comprehensive Healthcare, Dental, and Vision ', ' Flexible PTO and WFH policy ', ' Discounted fresh food for your pup ', ' Fresh breakfast, snacks and coffee for the humans ', ' Strict daily belly rub quota', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Food & Beverages', 'Internet', 'Consumer Goods']

Name: Data Analyst, Health, Google AI
Description: ['Minimum Qualifications', ' ', "Master's degree in a quantitative discipline (e.g. statistics, bioinformatics, computational biology, computer science, applied mathematics, or similar) or equivalent practical experience.", ' ', '3 years of relevant work experience (i.e. as a Statistician/Bioinformatician/Data Scientist/data Analyst/Clinical Informaticist) working on observational clinical data.', ' ', 'Experience working with data sets,', ' ', 'Experience with SQL, Python or similar.', ' ', 'Preferred Qualifications', ' ', 'Experience with clinical data warehouses and/or analysis of electronic health records.', ' ', 'Experience with statistical data analysis such as hypothesis testing, linear models, multivariate analysis, predictive modeling.', ' ', 'About The Job', "Help serve Google's worldwide user base of more than a billion people. Product Analysts provide quantitative support, market understanding and a strategic perspective to our partners throughout the organization. As a data-loving member of the team, you serve as an analytics expert for your partners, using numbers to help them make better decisions. You will weave stories with meaningful insight from data. You'll make critical recommendations for your fellow Googlers in Engineering and Product Management. As a self-starter, you relish tallying up the numbers one minute and communicating your findings to a team leader the next.", 'Google AI aims to use machine learning (ML) and other tools to improve healthcare. We work closely with partners to research and explore solutions that improve the availability and accuracy of medical services.', "As a Data Analyst you'll analyze rich structured and unstructured healthcare datasets. You'll serve as an analytics expert, ensure data quality, build ML models, and deliver meaningful insights through data. You'll make critical recommendations for your fellow Googlers in Engineering and Product Management.", 'Our team combines experts in medicine, machine learning, engineering, statistics and more to support clinical breakthroughs using a variety of techniques. Our work spans from many projects, including medical image diagnosis, medical event predictions, automatic speech recognition and more. We’ve partnered with medical researchers, bioinformaticians, and healthcare partners to explore how machine learning combined with clinical expertise could improve patient outcomes. We regularly publish in leading industry journals.', 'Responsibilities', ' ', 'Work with large, complex datasets to solve difficult, non-routine analysis problems.', ' ', 'Design automation tools for data cleaning, validation and verification.', ' ', 'Define data quality metrics and automated reports to provide insight at scale. ', ' ', 'Summarize data to draw insights or answer business questions. ', ' ', 'Apply statistical methods to measure data quality and detect data anomaly.', ' ', "At Google, we don’t just accept difference—we celebrate it, we support it, and we thrive on it for the benefit of our employees, our products and our community. Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing this form .", 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Services', 'Internet']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Current employees and contingent workers click here to apply and search by the Job Posting Title. ', 'iHeartRadio', 'Job Summary', 'The Data Analyst role offers the opportunity to have an immediate impact on various aspects of the business at iHeartRadio, which offers unlimited music all in one app from thousands of radio stations, artists, playlists, and more, as well as editorial content across the web.', 'We are looking for a Data Analyst with a strategic mindset and a passion for data, who is eager to be an expert in the latest and greatest analytics tools we oversee and utilize to inform business decisions. The ideal candidate possesses a blend of quantitative skills, data storytelling / communications abilities, and an entrepreneurial spirit, in order to be an effective member of the Analytics team. Additionally, they should be comfortable working as an active participant with cross-functional teams to solve business challenges. Last but not least, we are looking for someone who is adaptable and excited by learning, as we have a lot of data and various tools at our disposal, and are always seeking insights to drive the business forward.', 'Requirements', '1-2 years of Analytics experience, ideally at a digital and/or mobile-first company', 'Experience using Adobe Analytics and/or similar systems', 'Familiarity with SQL', 'Proficient user of Microsoft Office, including Excel and PowerPoint', 'Ability to analyze raw data and extract actionable insights', 'Strong verbal and written communication skills. Ability to present complex information into understandable, comprehendible information with actionable recommendations', 'Team Player who can work with diverse, cross-functional teams', 'Adapts easily to changing situations and can manage priorities', 'Strong desire to learn and grow career', 'Degree/Advanced Degree in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management or Statistics', 'Bonus', 'Skills in Looker, Tableau, and/or other dashboarding tools', 'Skills in Python and/or R', 'Familiarity with A/B testing and analyzing results', 'Experience working within an agile workflow', 'Location', 'Nashville, TN; 1200 Broadway, 6th Floor, 37203', 'Position Type', 'Regular', 'The Company is an equal opportunity employer and will not tolerate discrimination in employment on the basis of race, color, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, religion, disability, ethnicity, national origin, marital status, protected veteran status, genetic information, or any other legally protected classification or status.', 'Our organization participates in E-Verify. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['About Us', 'Launched in 2011, Twitch is a global community that comes together each day to create multiplayer entertainment: unique, live, unpredictable experiences created by the interactions of millions. We bring the joy of co-op to everything, from casual gaming to world-class esports to anime marathons, music, and art streams. Twitch also hosts TwitchCon, where we bring everyone together to celebrate, learn, and grow their personal interests and passions. We’re always live at Twitch. Stay up to date on all things Twitch on LinkedIn , Twitter and on our Blog .', 'About The Role', 'Data is central to Twitch’s decision-making process, and analysts are a critical component to promote data-driven decision making in all of our operations. As an analyst at Twitch, you will be in on the ground floor with your team, shaping the way product performance is measured, defining what questions should be asked, and scaling analytics methods and tools to support our growing business, leading the way for high quality , high velocity decisions for your team.', 'You Will', ' ', ' Evangelize data knowledge and insights: manage communications with your stakeholders and other teams, collaborate with both technical and non-technical colleagues to complete data projects and ensure all parties can use the insights to further improve. ', ' ', 'Maintain a customer-centric focus: aim to be a domain and product expert through data, develop trust amongst your peers and stakeholders , and ensure that your team has access to data to make decisions.', ' ', 'Work with stakeholders and mentors to distill the problem, adapt your tools to answer complicated questions, and identify the trade-offs between speed and quality of different approaches.', ' ', 'Create analytical frameworks to measure team success: partner with cross-functional teams to define success metrics, create approaches to track the data and troubleshoot errors, quantify and evaluate the data, then develop a common language for all colleagues to understand these KPIs ', ' ', 'Operationalize data processes - provide the team with ad-hoc analysis, automated dashboards, and self-service reporting tools so that everyone gets a good sense of the state of the business', ' ', ' ', 'You Have:', ' ', ' 3+ years of industry experience in a relevant field', ' ', 'A/B testing experience with an understanding of hypothesis testing and power analysis', ' ', 'Expert SQL skills--your ability to tap into our data pipeline will be key to your success', ' ', ' Proven track record of using data to create insight and achieve our goals', ' ', 'Fluency in data analysis and communication around data, including time series analysis, experimentation, data visualization, and defining KPI strategy for your business', ' ', ' ', 'Perks', ' ', 'Medical, Dental, Vision & Disability Insurance', ' ', ' 401(k) ', ' ', 'Maternity & Parental Leave ', ' ', 'Flexible PTO', ' ', 'Commuter Benefits', ' ', 'Amazon Employee Discount', ' ', 'Monthly Contribution & Discounts for Wellness Related Activities & Programs (e.g., gym memberships, off-site massages , etc. )', ' ', 'Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner Served Daily', ' ', 'Free Snacks & Beverages ', ' ', 'Pursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.', 'We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at Twitch. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Internet']

Name: Data Analyst, Data & Analytics (Advanced Analytics) (Manager)(Multiple Positions)
Description: ['Data Analyst, Data & Analytics (Advanced Analytics) (Manager)(Multiple Positions), Ernst & Young U.S. LLP, New York, NY. ', 'Provide data analytics services to help clients solve business problems, drive value, and gain strategy and insight from information.\u202f Use advanced data analysis techniques that leverage technology to process large volumes of data to perform complex computations in a scalable, reproducible and automated manner. Support information intelligence, including the collection, storage, usage and quality of information. Work as a key member of a team to implement integrated enterprise-wide reporting solutions for data transformation and delivery. Perform data analytics to help solve business challenges and achieve data automation, reconciliation, traceability, lineage and transparency. Use data analytics to provide actionable, timely and accurate data to drive business insights around technology enablement, digital transformation and enterprise intelligence.', 'Manage and motivate teams with diverse skills and backgrounds. Consistently deliver quality client services by monitoring progress. Demonstrate in-depth technical capabilities and professional knowledge. Maintain long-term client relationships and networks. Cultivate business development opportunities.', 'Full time employment, Monday – Friday, 40 hours per week,', 'Minimum Requirements', "Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Operations Research, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Engineering or a related field and 5 years of progressive, post-baccalaureate related work experience; or a Master’s degree in Computer Science, Operations Research, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Engineering or a related field and 4 years of related work experience.", 'Must have 4 years of experience providing advisory or consulting services, including helping clients achieve transformational value by improving performance through the use of advanced analytics solutions.', 'Must have 4 years of recent hands-on experience using advanced analytics, machine learning or artificial intelligence to solve business problems.', 'Must have 2 years of experience managing a team of consulting professionals, providing regular status updates, monitoring project economics and managing client relationships.', 'Must have 3 years of recent hands-on programming experience in at least 2 of the following R, Python, SAS, SPSS, or TensorFlow.', 'Must have 3 years of recent hands-on experience with SQL programming and Data Visualization skills using Tableau, Power BI, Spotfire, or D3.js.', 'Travel required up to 80%, of which 20% may be international, to meet client needs.', 'Employer will accept any suitable combination of education, training or experience.', 'TO APPLY Please apply on-line at ey.com/en_us/careers, and click on “Find jobs” (Job Number – NEW00Q9G).', 'EY provides equal employment opportunities to applicants and employees without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, protected veteran status, or disability status.', 'This particular position at Ernst & Young in the United States requires the qualified candidate to be a "United States worker" as defined by the U.S. Department of Labor regulations at 20 CFR 656.3. You can review this definition at https//www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/CFR-2011-title20-vol3/pdf/CFR-2011-title20-vol3-sec656-3.pdf at the bottom of page 750. Please feel free to apply to other positions that do not require you to be a "U.S. worker".', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Accounting', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Gloo, headquartered in beautiful Boulder, Colorado, builds software for people and organizations dedicated to improving lives. We’re leveraging the same exponential tech that’s driving success in other industries and making it available through tools such as big data, personal growth plans, custom assessments, and eventually, an entire market network focused on growth. As one of Boulder’s most successful and innovative tech companies, Gloo needs more talented professionals who are driven to make a positive impact on humanity. Are you one of them?', 'As the newest member of our revenue operations team, you will be analyzing, modeling, and interpreting data to help us make strategic business decisions.\xa0 You are a data analyst with a slant towards engineering - some might describe you as a data superhero, and that’s what we want. You have in-depth experience with data visualization and a communication style that gives you the ability to deliver your message clearly and concisely to stakeholders.\xa0 If you’ve been working in a SaaS, MarTech, or mobile app company and are ready to take on a new challenge, let’s talk!', 'How you’ll spend your days', 'Utilizing Gainsight, Salesforce, Google Analytics, Hotjar to collect essential data related to the success of the business', 'Converting raw data and complex quantitative analysis into actionable business goals', 'Helping direct insights that will improve efficiencies and identifying opportunities for product optimization\xa0', 'Reviewing and analyzing user session videos to identify patterns and correlate with analytics', 'Championing our data-driven, user centered design process, championing a metrics driven culture and outcomes', 'Collaborating with Marketing, Product, Sales, Support, Systems, Data Science, and Engineering to coordinate solutions and bring ideas to life', 'What you’ll bring to the team', 'BS in Engineering, Information Management, Computer Science, or a related discipline', 'At least 4 years of experience analyzing, modeling, and interpreting data in the market intelligence, martech or mobile/web platform space', 'Proficiency with analysis and query languages – SQL, R, Python, Athena', 'Experience with data visualization and BI tools, Tableau, Insight Squared or Lookr', 'Ability to identify opportunities for product optimization by tracking user behavior using Gainsight, Google Analytics, Hotjar, and Google Tag Manager', 'Creative, articulate, and competent communication style – you deliver your message clearly, concisely, and confidently every time', 'Intellectual curiosity – you are always looking for new ways to extract, analyze and use data to further our mission', 'Our team members enjoy', 'Competitive compensation package and a full suite of benefits', 'Bonus and ample time off for your personal pursuits', 'An incredible team of talented and passionate folks to hang out with', 'Goldstone Partners is helping this experienced team of thought leaders and engineers find an energized individual who wants to be part of something big!\xa0Principals only, please. Applications welcome for those who are US Citizens or hold a Green Card.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Computer Software']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['About Us', 'Because is re-engineering everyday consumer products and delivering them via a leading ecommerce subscription to older adults as if they were our own family. Our team consists of seasoned execs from Uber, eBay, WeWork and Gap Inc, and we are backed by Index, Khosla Ventures, Comcast Ventures and other top tier investors.', 'Because was created after our founders spent countless hours tracking down supplies for their grandparents. They had to visit multiple stores and often left empty handed when needed products were out of stock. They knew they could do better for their family and all older adults.', 'Job Summary', 'In this role, you will be part of a team responsible for delivering data-driven, actionable insights that contribute to all parts of our business. You will create standard and ad-hoc analyses to answer business questions and provide actionable insights. This is an opportunity to be an early member of a data-insights team re-engineering the ecommerce business for seniors:', ' Structure and analyze major business and customer questions through a hypothesis-driven approach ', ' Apply expertise in data analysis, data mining, and data visualization to see beyond the numbers and help provide insights behind the numbers ', ' Present insights to key internal and external stakeholders, effectively communicating the key findings and recommendations ', ' Develop and own easily consumable, visualized dashboards of key metrics for stakeholders and executives with actionable insight call-outs ', ' Position works closely with Product, Engineering, Marketing, Merchandising, Operations and the Executive Team ', 'Qualifications', ' Strong hands-on SQL experience and advanced Excel skills required; Python, R preferred ', ' Experience building dashboards and data visualizations ', ' Experience pulling unstructured data from disparate data sources ', ' Must be a doer , self-motivated, energetic, "can-do" attitude in a fast-paced environment ', '3-4 years of work experience ', 'Benefits', ' Comprehensive healthcare, including medical, dental and vision ', '401K ', ' Flex PTO ', 'We are not your typical Silicon Valley startup - no sleep pods or cold brew on tap - but we are a transparent, hard working team that enjoys helping others better their lives. We look forward to meeting you!', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Consumer Goods', 'Financial Services', 'Accounting']

Name: Data and Analytics Portfolio Advisor - Houston, TX
Description: ['Where you fit in?', 'Data and Analytics is fast emerging area in Shell and requires broad knowledge of not only the technology area but also understand its application in the business from an Business Intelligence, Management Information and application perspective.', 'The Data and Analytics Portfolio Advisor plays a key role in execution of the tasks within the end-to-end IT Service Portfolio Management process. The Data and Analytics Portfolio Advisor is part of the Enterprise Technology and Project team (ETP) that reports to the CIO IT Service Operations. As a portfolio advisor you play key role in defining the multiyear strategic roadmap, investment plan and key programs for Data and Analytics supporting Shell enterprise businesses.', "What's the role?", 'The successful candidate must balance the technology focus with the long-term strategy as it integrates with other areas of IT. You must have the ability to build and drive a natural team of many IT disciplines and business-facing teams. First and foremost the role must be able to represent a 3-5 year strategy of and end-to-end view of the Data and Analytics area and integrated across other technology portfolios.', 'Responsibilities include end to end ownerships of the Data and Analytic service from life cycle perspectives. This includes maintaining data integrity and quality in the relevant IT portfolio management systems (ServiceNow), maintaining the demand funnel, maintaining the integrated portfolio plan (including service components consumed by the service), reporting on portfolio data (total cost of ownerships, service uptakes, component service roadmaps), investment proposal, ITSO LT/ITE papers, supporting project initiation and oversight on project delivery.', 'The success of this role will depend on partnering with the business, assessing business demands and needs, determining the necessary information required and presenting it to business stakeholders in an intuitive manner to enable strategic decisions.', 'Requirements', 'What we need from you', 'Must have legal authorization to work in the US on a full-time basis for anyone other than current employer.', "Bachelor's Degree required. Degree related to Information Technology preferred.", 'Minimum of six (6) years in corporate IT with some IT leadership experience.', 'Consultant mindset – must be constantly thinking about how the status quo could be improved.', 'Proven stakeholder management – typically works within cross-functional teams. Needs strong stakeholder skills to ensure teams are all working towards the same goals.', 'Highly customer focused and fast paced environment.', 'Strong interpersonal, communication, facilitation and presentation skills. Highly experienced in communicating with business at all levels and story telling', 'The core IT competences ITIL, Portfolio/Project Management. ', 'Demonstrated skill in IT Business Analysis.', 'Knowledge of IT portfolio management processes and tools.', 'Skilled at working effectively with cross functional teams in a matrix organization. ', 'Demonstrated skill running effective meetings and getting buy-in and participation from stakeholders, Building and managing efficient relationships with Natural Team.', 'Technical knowledge on Power BI and Azure big data platforms.', 'Company Description', 'Shell is a global group of energy and petrochemical companies with about 84,000 employees across more than 70 countries. We aim to meet the world’s growing need for more and cleaner energy solutions in ways that are economically, environmentally and socially responsible. We have expertise in exploration, production, refining and marketing of oil and natural gas, and the manufacturing and marketing of chemicals. As a global energy company operating in a challenging world, we set high standards of performance and ethical behaviors. We are judged by how we act and how we live up to our core values of honesty, integrity and respect for people. Our Business Principles are based on these. They promote trust, openness, teamwork and professionalism, as well as pride in what we do and how we conduct business. Building on our core values, we aspire to sustain a diverse and inclusive culture where everyone feels respected and valued, from our employees to our customers and partners. A diverse workforce and an inclusive work environment are vital to our success, leading to greater innovation and better energy solutions.', 'An innovative place to work', 'There’s never been a more exciting time to work at Shell. Everyone here is helping solve one of the biggest challenges facing the world today bringing the benefits of energy to everyone on the planet, whilst managing the risks of climate change.', 'Join us and you’ll add your talent and imagination to a business with the power to shape the future – whether by investing in renewables, exploring new ways to store energy or developing technology that helps the world to use energy more efficiently.', 'A rewarding place to work', 'Combine our creative, collaborative environment and global operations with an impressive range of benefits and joining Shell becomes an inspired career choice.', 'We’re huge advocates for career development. We’ll encourage you to try new roles and experience new settings. By pushing people to reach their potential, we frequently help them find skills they never knew they had, or make career moves they never thought possible.', 'Disclaimer', 'Please note We occasionally amend or withdraw Shell jobs and reserve the right to do so at any time, including prior to the advertised closing date.', 'Before applying, you are advised to read our data protection policy. This policy describes the processing that may be associated with your personal data and informs you that your personal data may be transferred to Royal Dutch/Shell Group companies around the world.', 'The Shell Group and its approved recruitment consultants will never ask you for a fee to process or consider your application for a career with Shell. Anyone who demands such a fee is not an authorised Shell representative and you are strongly advised to refuse any such demand.', 'Shell participates in E-Verify.', 'All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, sex, national origin, age, religion, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, protected veteran status, citizenship, genetic information or other protected status under federal, state or local laws.', 'Shell is an Equal Opportunity Employer - Minorities/Females/Veterans/Disability.', 'Employment Type', 'Full Time', 'Skillpool', 'IT Strategy, Planning & Portfolio Mgt', 'Work Location', 'Houston - EP Center Americas', 'No. of Positions', '1', '16-Apr-2020', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'General Business', 'Analyst', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Oil & Energy']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Lori Crutchley', 'Lori Crutchley', 'DATA ANALYST.\xa0ARNOLD, MISSOURI. ', 'Arsenal Credit Union is a federally insured, state-chartered, award-winning credit union that focuses on providing excellent service experiences for its 29,000+ members through its branch network, online/mobile banking channels, call center, and back-office support departments.\xa0', 'When you work at Arsenal, it is more than a job.\xa0', 'You are part of a mission that puts helping people above all else.\xa0We have an opening for a ', 'Data Analyst ', 'in our information technology department.\xa0\xa0\xa0', 'We are seeking a candidate to provide the organization with actionable insights from analyzing a multitude of data sources.\xa0This position will configure and monitor core data processing systems and information and create business reports to support decision making and strategic planning.\xa0Must be proficient in document analysis, recommendations, conclusions and the ability to design, test and deploy data solutions.\xa0Will be responsible for designing, building and launching new data extraction, transformation, and loading processes.\xa0Will proactively work with all departments within the credit union and translate business requests into technical requirements.\xa0This position will design and develop BI/AI projects on Symitar platforms.\xa0', 'Selected applicant(s) must possess a BS in computer or computer science discipline or relevant certification.\xa0Proven working experience as a Database Developer.\xa0Basic knowledge of report creation concepts. Proficient with MS Access and Excel.\xa0Experience with SQL.\xa0Must be comfortable working in a highly collaborative environment and the ability to present in a group setting in a professional manner.\xa0', 'Preference given to applicants who have knowledge of Jack Henry - Symitar Episys – PowerOn and Easy Writer, Advanced Reporting for Credit Unions (ARCU) –SQL, Visible Equity Loan Analytics, Financial Performance Suite (ProfitStars – profitability and pricing model), PSCU DataVue (Web Intelligence), Jack Henry Synapsys Sales and Marketing Tool, PSCU, CISCO and iTalk telecommunications, NCR (Digital Insight) online banking, CO-OP shared branch and ATM use, fraud prevention tools, peer analysis.', 'Must have strong problem-solving skills and an intellectual curiosity towards existing processes and possible improvements.', 'We offer a competitive salary and incentive plan, an amazing benefits package, including 401(k) plan with generous match, medical/dental insurance, vision, voluntary & group life, STD, LTD, PTO plan and bankers holidays!', 'For consideration, resumes must include salary expectations. Name: Data Analyst

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Lou Sanchez', 'Lou Sanchez', 'Talent Acquisition Recruiter/Sales Recruiter (Latin America and the Americas) at Citrix', 'We believe work is not a place, but rather a thing you do. Our technology revolves around this core philosophy. We are relentlessly committed to helping people work and play from anywhere, on any device. Innovation, creativity and a passion for ever-improving performance drive our company and our people forward. We empower the original mobile device: YOU!', "What We're Looking For", 'You can support the sales team by developing structured sales processes, analyzing sales performance within each process framework , and implementing solutions based on the results of data analysis.', 'You have the ability to be responsible for the development of essential solutions to support sales field intelligence, including definition of key success measures for actionable performance assessment and process optimization.', 'You have the keen ability to interpret data, identify trends, and translates analysis into recommendations to improve sales effectiveness in alignment with overall business strategy.', 'Position Overview', 'Ensures that all standardized reports and dashboards are available and distributed to sales management. Assists Sales Management in periodic performance reviews and provide orientation and guidance by pointing out key findings and observations. Evaluates pricing structures to ensure fit with company objectives. Oversee the ongoing evolution of planning and sales reporting functions with a focus on process improvement and expansion of complex analytical capabilities. Facilitates the annual planning and quota allocation process with the local sales force in accordance with the policies and tools set by Corporate. Key subject areas include: Quota Setting, Pipeline, Bookings, Territory & Account Management as well as Sales Coverage and Productivity.', 'Roles Responsibilities', 'Works on multiple multifaceted software compliance projects.', 'Performs data mining and analysis on internal and external data sets and databases.', 'Develops draft reports and deliverables pertaining to software license reviews and inventory baselines.', 'Provides written updates to internal and external stakeholders in a professional manner.', 'Leverages templates to create internal and external stakeholders.', 'Provides internal updates on project status, timeline, milestones and deliverables.', 'Manages and prioritizes multiple projects and tasks, in a fluid and changing environment.', 'Clearly convey the results of complex analysis in an effective manner and demonstrate professionalism with all stakeholders.', 'Basic Qualifications', "Bachelor’s degree in Management of Information Systems, Accounting, Finance or related field required. Master's Degree in Business Administration or equivalent business experience preferred", '2+ years related audit, compliance or software asset management', 'Preferred Qualifications', 'Understanding of Citrix products and licensing models is a plus', 'Software license compliance auditing experience', 'Proficient with the following:', 'Software Asset Management (SAM) tools (e.g., SCCM, Flexera, Aspera, Snow, ServiceNow, Altiris, ILMT, Endpoint, LAN Sweeper, etc.)', 'Citrix products and offerings is a plus', 'Salesforce', 'Sharefile', 'Ability to program / code preferred.', 'Experience with IT operations and systems including: databases, security and networking.', 'Highly motivated individual that is able to work independently, as well as participate on team projects', 'Ability to work effectively with a variety of organizations, management levels, cultures, and personalities', 'Advanced level of expertise using Microsoft Office suite', 'Expert Excel user with ability to automate reports (Charts, Pivot tables, VLOOKUP, Macros, VBA, and database connectivity)', 'Fort Lauderdale, FL', 'What You’re Looking For', 'Our technology is built on the idea that everyone should be able to work from anywhere, at any time, and on any device. It’s a simple philosophy that guides everything we do — including how we work. If you’re in sales, we’ll help you make your numbers and a difference with a brand you can believe in. We want employees to do what they do best, every day.', 'Be bold. Take risks. Imagine a better way to work. If we just described you, then we really need to talk.', 'Functional Area', 'Sales Operations', 'About Us', 'Citrix is a cloud company that enables mobile workstyles. Name: Senior Data Analyst, Data Insights
Description: ['Hulu is the leading premium streaming service offering live and on-demand TV and movies, with and without commercials, both in and outside the home. Operating at the intersection of entertainment and technology, Hulu has a unique opportunity to be the number one choice for TV. We captivate and connect viewers with the stories they love, and we’re looking for people who are passionate about redefining TV through innovation, unconventional thinking, and embracing fun. Join us and see what Hulugan life is all about.', 'Summary', 'Hulu’s Data Insights team is seeking a Senior Data Analyst who will be an outstanding addition to our team. The team partners with other teams across the business to turn data into information, information into insights and insights into key business decisions that steer the strategic direction of the company. The right person for this role thrives in a fast-pace environment, loves problem-solving and is a good communicator. If you are someone who gains personal happiness from transforming data into knowledge for business insights, then this is a phenomenal role for you.', 'You will design innovative analytic approaches to test hypotheses, extract actionable insights by identifying patterns in structured and unstructured data, and develop recommendations to drive business performance. You will be instrumental in leading the use of analytics as a critical value driver across our organization.', "What You'll Do", 'Build analysis, data visualizations, and multi-functional reporting that provides critical support to the operations and decision-making of the organization', 'Facilitate the analytical needs of the business, collaborate in the design of diagnostic solutions, and deliver outstanding data products and insights', 'Act as a liaison between business units & data engineering to drive key operational metrics for enabling business success and value-addition within the data & analytics domain', 'Use internal and external analytics tools, SQL, and scripting languages to access and analyze multivariate data', 'Translate business functional requirements into technical specifications and, conversely, technical approaches into easily digestible terms', 'Develop and foster positive relationships and transparent dialogue with the business community and data colleagues', 'Provide analytics expertise to key business partners regarding data & analytics questions', 'Support business units, data teams and product/program management with process improvements for optimized delivery of diverse data requests', 'Take personal accountability for delivery of projects and committed timelines', 'Support business partners in adopting reporting solutions and business intelligence tools for self-service', 'What To Bring', 'A bachelor’s or master’s degree in Computer Science, MIS, Statistics, Economics, Mathematics, etc.', '4+ years of experience as an analyst in a data and analytics domain', 'Excellent SQL skills for complex querying, analysis, performance optimization, and persisting data', 'Excellent data visualization skills with tools like Tableau, QlikView, MicroStrategy, etc.', 'Experience working in a “big-data” environment (Hadoop, Hive, Presto, BigQuery, Snowflake, Redshift, etc.)', 'Experience demonstrating analytical concepts to craft an actionable story for technical and non-technical audiences', 'Familiarity with data science programming languages like R, SAS, and Python', 'Familiarity working with web analytics tools (particularly: Google Analytics, Google Search Council, etc.)', 'Understanding of data warehousing concepts, design, modeling and data engineering', 'Experience taking vague requirements and transforming them into crisp insights', 'Intense curiosity, high intellectual and analytical horsepower, passionate pursuit of analytics driven insights', 'Demonstrable ability to build strong working Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['A great deal of effort is spent on using masses of data to understand user behavior to inform and improve upon Microsoft’s products and marketing efforts.', 'We are the Modern Life and Search Data Analytics team focused on using data analysis and data science to influence and impact Microsoft’s consumer product and marketing efforts. We enable data driven decisions by converting data into insights drive enhanced customer experiences and improve business performance.', 'We partner closely with Engineering, Marketing, and Finance teams to answer key questions related to product adoption, engagement, satisfaction and monetization. Our work requires regular collaboration with our partner teams as well as technical expertise to mine big datasets and discover key insights.', 'To support this mission, we are looking for experienced Data Analyst who has a passion for analyzing big data to uncover customer usage insights and driving those insights into actions with our partner teams.', 'The ideal candidate should be self-directed, passionate about data, and focused on delivering the right results. The candidate should be able to apply programming acumen and a breadth of tools, data sources and analytical techniques to answer a wide range of high-impact business questions and present the insights in a concise and effective manner. Technical aptitude and programming skills are necessary in this role. The candidate should also be an effective communicator capable of independently driving issues to resolution and communicating insights to both technical and non-technical audiences.', 'Responsibilities', 'Core Responsibilities:', 'Build a holistic understanding of our product features, its customer, data infrastructure, product and business goals', 'Analyze complex, high-volume, high-dimensionality data from varying sources using a variety of tools and data analysis techniques', 'Develop analytical data sets in Azure or internal Big Data Environments which can be used to for analytics and data science', 'Understand business performance (trends, funnels) as well as answer product and business questions to drive product and marketing actions', 'Build and maintain learning plans for the product(s) with key analytical questions', 'Leverage industry best practices in establishing repeatable BI practices, principles & processes', 'Qualifications', 'Key Skills, Competencies, Qualifications:', 'Ability to understand, translate and map business and product questions into analysis projects', 'Expertise in database technology technologies with an understanding and hands-on skills with SQL Server, SSIS, solid understanding of SSAS / n-dimensional cubes is required', 'Experience building large scale data sets in Azure, AWS, Hadoop or similar big data environments is required', 'Proficiency in advanced Excel functions (e.g., creating formulas, pivot tables) and PowerBI is required', 'Ability to influence diverse audiences and build strong partnerships with stakeholders', 'Strong ability to articulate vision, requirements & benefits, providing a solid rationale to business and technical partners', 'Self-motivated, agile and driven to think out-of-the-box', '3+ years relevant experience (e.g., data analytics, technical, development, project and/or program management) is required', '#MLS&D', 'Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or the recruiting process, please send a request via the Accommodation request form.', 'Benefits/perks listed below may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Microsoft and the country where you work.', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Computer Hardware', 'Computer Software', 'Information Technology and Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Podium is an Interaction Management platform that makes it simple for local businesses to conveniently connect with leads, customers, and their teams. Our work streamlining this process for local businesses has awarded us recognition on top industry lists, such as Forbes’ Next Billion Dollar Startups, Forbes’ Cloud 100, the Inc. 5000 (#13), and Fast Company’s World’s Most Innovative Companies — in the last year alone. For more about our product, watch this video. Podium has a positive, diverse, and supportive culture and was recently named one of Inc. Magazine’s Best Workplaces for 2019. We look for people who are curious, creative and work to be a little better every day. In our work together we embody our values: Be a founder, Murder drama, and Enjoy the ride.', 'As a data analyst at Podium you will analyze and recommend strategic, data-driven decisions to clients and to the internal leadership team. You will be a critical part of illustrating ROI to clients, and keeping those clients loyal to Podium. This role has client-facing responsibilities. You will be on email threads and phone calls with clients, talking through their reporting needs and proposing solutions. You will also help train these clients on the custom reports that you build. If you are someone who is passionate about building a business, turns their curiosity into valuable deliverables, can creatively solve problems using quantitative metrics, and thrives in a fast-paced, open environment, then this is the right role for you!', 'What You Will Be Doing', ' ', 'Build reporting dashboards for Podium’s clients, providing insights into their public online reviews, private internal feedback, and messaging habits. Present these dashboards to the clients, and train them on all aspects of the reporting', ' ', 'Create new ways to visualize data for our clients, and build those new reports in a scalable manner', ' ', 'Become an expert on all data infrastructure and Podium’s products, and know how to quickly answer any question that crosses your plate', ' ', 'Partner with all other teams at Podium (sales, engineering, product, marketing, etc.) to design and build internal dashboards', ' ', 'Foster relationships with our Strategic account managers, and make recommendations on how to best handle their accounts (identify at-risk clients, provide ad-hoc charts for slide deck presentations, etc.)', ' ', 'What You Should Have', ' ', '2+ years professional experience with SQL and relational databases', ' ', 'The ability to clearly and effectively communicate the results of complex analyses', ' ', 'Scripting language experience (R preferred)', ' ', 'An understanding of common statistical applications and methods (correlation, summary statistics, regression)', ' ', 'Experience managing multiple, simultaneous projects, and do so with minimal guidance', ' ', 'A passion for identifying and understanding stories in data, and an innate curiosity to find more stories', ' ', 'Experience with Domo/Tableau/PowerBI preferred', ' ', 'Benefits', ' ', 'Transparent culture', ' ', 'Work in this building in Lehi, UT', ' ', 'Great opportunities for career growth', ' ', 'A stellar onsite gym with local professional coaches, morning and night classes offered ', ' ', 'Weekly free lunch, breakfast and smoothies', ' ', 'Swag', ' ', 'Podium is an equal opportunity employer. Podium provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, genetic information, marital status or veteran status.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Fraud Data Analyst
Description: ['Company Description', 'OUR COMPANY', 'Abercrombie & Fitch Co. is a portfolio of lifestyle brands including Abercrombie & Fitch, abercrombie kids, Hollister, and Gilly Hicks. Whether you lead yourself, a team, or the company, we believe everyone is a leader at A&F. We believe the people make the place. We are accountable and aim to the highest caliber. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Lindsey White', 'Lindsey White', 'Technical Recruiter- Data Governance - accepting new clients', 'We have immediate needs for Data Analysts who are interested in working in a fast-paced environment.\xa0', 'Who you are:', 'As a Data Governance Analyst, you will have blended responsibilities of Data and Business Analysis. In this role, there will be a moderate to heavy usage of SQL queries since you will be analyzing substantial data sets. You will work in a Data Warehouse Environment and could potentially be involved in working with MetaData, Data Marts, ETL, Source Systems, Cloud Environment and various Reporting elements. Additionally, you would be involved in writing complex queries, conducting data cleansing, ensuring data quality, and data enrichment. You would leverage programming and business intelligence skills (including Python, SQL, Tableau) on analytical platforms to prepare and manage data; create dashboards; develop KPIs and provide business insights. You would collaborate with Business Users and Stakeholders to understand and prepare Business Requirements and Technical Specifications. Extended skillsets are welcome and encouraged.', 'Who we are:', "Team Incept helps our Clients implement their Data Governance program to bring all the enterprise-wide data sources onto an integrated platform. We are partners with Informatica and other Organizations who are leaders in the Data Governance space. Incept has been instrumental in training and development of the next generation's Data Governance specialists. As part of our strategic plan to continue transforming our Clients into data-driven Organizations, our teams excel in design and implementation of Data Governance. Our Clients are leading providers in Banking, Entertainment, Financial, Healthcare, Insurance and Retail domains", 'Preferred Qualifications:', 'Bachelor’s or a Master’s in Computer Science, Business or Information Systems, OR atleast 3+ years of related work experience would help you hit the ground running. If you have robust Database and SQL knowledge, that would be fantastic. Exposure to Cloud technologies, Big Data Analytics, Hadoop Eco-System, Data Lakes and Data Warehouse concepts like Fact tables, Dimension tables, Dimensional Modeling, Star Schema, Snowflake Schema, Slowly Changing Dimensions is desirable. If there are any gaps, we have people who can help you fill them, keep your learning hat on!', 'Benefits', ':', 'We’ve got a culture focused on smarts, kindness, and continual learning. Your experience at Incept would not be of the mundane cubical job; you would be joining a friendly and passionate team. Data Governance is a relatively new and upcoming field with limitless potential. Your annual compensation would depend on how much you can learn and is generally between $70k-$90k per annum. We believe in and provide exhaustive skill enhancement training and certification programs and have excellent Healthcare and other employee benefits. Most of these positions donot require clearance and we are accepting OPT candidates however US Citizens are encouraged to apply.', 'Our location: ', 'We are based out of Virginia. Our address is: 22365 Broderick Dr #230, Sterling, VA 20166', 'How to apply: ', 'You can email your resume to bh@inceptds.com', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Analyst', 'Consulting', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Management Consulting', 'Information Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Job Purpose', "Under general supervision, perform data research and financial analysis to answer complex business questions. Name: Analyst I - Data Analytics
Description: ['Position Description', 'This position will be responsible to participate in interface issue resolution within the DP&S Insurance Operational Systems. (NYSE: ALLY) is a leading digital financial services company and a top 25 U.S. financial holding company offering financial products for consumers, businesses, automotive dealers and corporate clients. Ally's legacy dates back to 1919, and the company was redesigned in 2009 with a distinctive brand, innovative approach and relentless focus on its customers. Ally has an award-winning online bank (member FDIC), one of the largest full service auto finance operations in the country, a complementary auto-focused insurance business, a growing digital wealth management and online brokerage platform, and a trusted corporate finance business offering capital for equity sponsors and middle-market companies.", 'Business Unit/Enterprise Function Description', 'Ally Insurance', ' is a leading provider of automobile-related insurance, vehicle maintenance and reinsurance products, and services for automobile dealers and their customers. Plus, we have a flexible paid-time-off program including time off for volunteer opportunities. Description: ['DATA ANALYST', 'General Description', 'Firaxis Games, creator of some of the most successful and award winning strategy games of all time (including the Sid Meier’s Civilization and the XCOM series) and home of legendary game designer, Sid Meier, is looking to hire an experienced and passionate Data Scientist to work with our designers, engineers and producers to transform player behavior data into actionable insights that improve the overall player gameplay experience. Experience with big data technologies such as Spark or NoSQL DBs, columnar databases like Vertica a plus', ' ', 'Experience with data visualization tools, Tableau preferred', ' ', 'Excellent communication skills, with a proven track record of working across various disciplines of an organization - having the information is one thing, you must be able to disseminate and educate', ' ', 'Drive to solve problems, meet deadlines, and build whatever is necessary along the way', ' ', 'Experience understanding the strengths and weaknesses of different modeling approaches and can effectively reason about when to apply different combinations and iterate', ' ', 'Demonstrated expert communication, facilitation, and collaboration skills to effectively present, explain, influence, and advise within cross-functional teams', ' ', 'Video games industry experience and/or gaming familiarity very helpful', ' ', 'Basic programming experience with C++ in large code bases a plus', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Computer Games', 'Computer Software', 'Entertainment']

Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Name: Associate Data Analyst
Description: ['LIMRA/LOMA, and our parent organization, LL Global, INC., are the world’s largest association of life insurance and financial services companies, which together represent more than 1,300 members across 64 countries, including most of the world’s largest life insurance companies. We are currently recruiting for the position of ', 'Associate Data Analyst ', 'in our Windsor Location', ' The Data Analysis team provides ', ' advanced analytics, data visualization, survey design and development, programming and statistical support to research studies. ', ' In this role', ',', ' you will work closely with LIMRA’s Research Project Directors on project design, as well as data collection, analysis, reporting, and visualization.', 'Job Duties', 'This position will be responsible for understanding the needs of each project, selecting the appropriate analytical tools, and applying the established best practices to your work.
