Performs other job related duties as assigned', '\u200b', 'Qualifications : ', 'Knowledge, Skills and Abilities (KSAs):', '• Business Communication: Writes, speaks, and presents clearly and succinctly across a variety of communication settings and adjusts communication style to the audience by translating and articulating technical concepts to non-technical groups.', '• Creative Thinking: Demonstrates originality and imagination in thinking while developing a solution to a problem.', '• Financial Acumen: Utilizes fundamental concepts of finance to manage budgets, forecast costs, and provide information to account for the financial impact of decision-making.', '• Adaptability: Adapts to and embraces change with composure, resilience, and perseverance in the face of constraints, high pressure, and adverse situations.', '• Delivers Results: Demonstrates a clear bias for action and a sense of urgency on priorities.', '• Drives Excellence: Approaches problems systematically; develops solutions with sustainable and scalable results.', '• Excels in Customer Service: Thinks and acts with a customer perspective.', '\xa0', 'Background Experiences', '• Bachelor degree preferred or equivalent combination of education & work experience', '• ', '2+ years of analytical or planner experience', '• ', 'Working knowledge of JDE', '• Experience with Six Sigma or other Process Improvement Methodology a plus', '• Proficient in: Microsoft Office Suite including Access, l, PowerPoint, Project, Word and Visio.', '• Advanced Skills in: Excel, Access, SQL, Visual Basic Skills for Data Acquisition and Analysis', '• Experience in an FDA regulated industry, medical device or pharmaceutical preferred', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Production', 'Analyst', 'Strategy/Planning', 'Industries', 'Medical Devices']

Name: Manual Integration Data Analyst
Description: ['POSITION SUMMARY: ', 'Manual Integration Data Analyst responsibilities include conducting investigating the source and root cause of client concerns, maintenance/improving/automating current manual technical support asks, checking and validating assumptions, proposing solutions, and implementing these solutions, typically through use of SQL scripts. The Manual Integration Data Analyst will own the solution over the course of these investigations and data corrections, proactively communicating with all necessary parties. \xa0', 'POSITION DESCRIPTION: ', 'Handle client-related issues and with internal business partners and external customers to demonstrate findings and resolve issues.', 'Evaluate client records and access issues in a timely manner, resolving issues that might arise.', 'Audit data accuracy. Ensure that the data we received is correct.', 'Audit data processing. Follow the process steps to ensure that data was transformed as expected.', 'Identify sources of data errors and take measures to resolve them. This typically requires the analyst to either help the client change their process or write queries to correct data retroactively.', 'Locate and define new process improvement opportunities.', 'Execute manual technical support tasks', 'Maintenance/improving/automating current manual technical support asks.', 'QUALIFICATIONS/REQUIREMENTS:', "Bachelor's degree in Information Management, Healthcare Information, Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, or equivalent combination of related experience.", 'Working experience as a data analyst, business data analyst, programmer, or a demonstrated aptitude for the role.', 'Strong knowledge of and experience with relational databases, including structure and querying. Exceptional candidates without relational database experience may be considered if they have a programming background.', 'Experience using spreadsheets to create a shared understanding of data issues. Candidate must be able to explain findings visually. ', 'Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy.', 'Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings', 'Ability to communicate thoroughly and without being asked. This includes the ability to communicate directly with clients. The ideal candidate must be an excellent communicator. ', 'NICE TO HAVE:', 'Ability to design comprehensive data reports and other business tools to assist business managers and clients in making good business decisions', 'Experience with statistical analysis.', 'Prior customer service experience.', 'Prior object oriented development experience.', '\xa0', 'TRAVEL', 'Travel is not required for this position.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Marketing', 'Sales', 'Industries', 'Computer Software']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['About Amobee', 'Amobee is the world’s leading independent advertising platform that unifies all channels—including TV, programmatic and social—across all formats and devices. We provide marketers with advanced cross-channel media planning powered by advanced analytics and proprietary data. Our platform and technology provide sophisticated video-advertising solutions for the convergence of linear TV, over the top, connected TV, and premium digital.', 'Amobee has been named to Fortune’s Top 10 Best Workplaces in Advertising and Marketing. Amobee’s platforms have been widely recognized amongst our industry winning numerous awards in technology innovation. We are a wholly owned subsidiary of Singtel, one of the largest telco companies in the world, reaching over 700 million mobile subscribers in 21 countries. Amobee operates across North America, Europe, Middle East, Asia and Australia. For more information, visit amobee.com or follow @amobee.', 'Position Overview', 'As a Data Analyst, you will be working with the team to support the deployment, reporting and analysis of algorithms used to buy, sell, , allocate, forecast and deliver advertising on the internet and TV. You will contribute to bleeding-edge solutions through the application of mathematics, optimization, and machine learning capabilities. The position provides great opportunities to communicate with the business directly, bridging the gap between technology and business. Qualified individuals will have a solid background in the fundamentals of data engineering, data science, computer science or statistics, along with experience and comfort accessing and manipulating data.', 'Responsibilities', ' ', 'Apply mathematics to optimize the acquisition and allocation of advertising inventory using information about the inventory, advertiser and the targeted consumer', ' ', 'Work cross functionally to gather feedback and requirements from end users', ' ', 'Design innovative solutions and build prototypes for proof of concept', ' ', 'Develop, launch, and evolve new products', ' ', 'Be a thought leader in identifying and vetting new data sources', ' ', 'Execute research that results in ground-breaking papers and case studies that support the needs of the sales and marketing functions', ' ', 'Perform ad-hoc analysis on campaign, publisher, or product performance', ' ', 'Requirements', ' ', 'A bachelor’s degree in a quantitative discipline, such as Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Industrial Engineering, Mechanical Engineering.', ' ', '1-4 years of experience in Data Science/Engineering.', ' ', 'Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail', ' ', 'Ability to work as part of a team in a fast-paced environment', ' ', 'Good communications skills', ' ', 'Experience with statistical software (e.g., Python, R)', ' ', 'Experience with data engineering tools used to access, merge, transform and evaluate data sources (SQL)', ' ', 'Additional Skill Of Interesting', ' ', 'Experience with data frameworks (e.g., Spark, Pig)', ' ', 'Experience with Gurobi ', ' ', 'Experience with modeling concepts, such as training/test paradigm, validation of models, and knowledge of modeling techniques (linear and logistic regression, decision trees, etc.)', ' ', 'Location: Baltimore, MD', 'In addition to our great environment, we offer a competitive base salary, employee development programs and other comprehensive benefits. Please send a cover letter along with your resume when applying to the position of interest located at Amobee.com. We are an Equal Opportunity Employer. No phone calls and no recruiting agencies, please.', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Science', 'Information Technology', 'Engineering', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Leads efforts to collect, organize, and maintain datasets; under direction, conducts quantitative analysis and research to evaluate and report transit system performance; enables, supports, and encourages use of data and analysis in support of decision-making utilizing data visualization techniques; ensures work efforts and products are in alignment with industry best practices.', 'Data: Lead efforts to collect, organize, and maintain datasets using best practices, including but not limited to designing data tables, applying data validation, and implementing procedures to support data needs. Assess data for accuracy, anomalies and completeness. As issues arise, determine and execute a solution, with supervisor input as needed.', 'Analysis: Under direction, conduct quantitative analysis and research to evaluate and report performance in support of decision-making. Collaboratively develop and assess analysis methods and systems. Implement, document and maintain analysis, methods, processes and systems. Ensure that analysis methods and products are in alignment with industry best practices and comply with federal and state policies and requirements.', 'Engagement and advocacy: Enable, support, and encourage use of data in decision-making. Seek opportunities to increase the use of data through improved access. Engage internal and external partners in the development, use and integration of data. Serve as a subject matter expert to internal and external partners. Regularly provide presentations and guidance to internal and external groups.', 'Organization: Monitor work processes and report progress toward goals. Manage competing priorities and interests. Support organizational change.', 'Performs other duties of a similar nature or level.', 'Minimum Qualifications', 'A bachelor’s degree in statistics, computer science, mathematics, planning, engineering.', 'Three years progressively responsible experience managing and querying data in a relational database environment, such as Oracle (PL/SQL), SQL Server (T-SQL), etc.)', 'At least two years’ experience in applying quantitative methods of analysis and research in support of decision-making.', 'At least one year experience utilizing analytical tools such as Tableau.', 'One year experience applying statistical analysis.', 'OR an equivalent combination of education and experience sufficient to successfully perform the essential duties of the job.', 'Preferred Qualifications', 'Experience in quantitative analysis in the transportation industry.', 'Experience in leading teams or projects and applying project management methods and techniques.', 'ENTRY REQUIREMENTS FOR: Knowledge and Skills', 'Qualification to enter this position requires knowledge of the following:', 'Data and Analysis', 'Software applications including word processing, spreadsheets and databases.', 'Principles and methods for analysis, research and evaluation; including statistical analysis techniques.', 'Best practices related to data collection, processing, modeling, management, analysis, stewardship and reporting; including relational database theory.', 'Project management methods and techniques.', 'Qualification To Enter This Position Requires Skill In', 'Data and Analysis', 'Developing, managing and using data and data systems.', 'Conducting studies by applying the principles and methods of data analysis, research and evaluation. Making recommendations based on findings.', 'Consistently analyzing a variety of techniques and selecting the most appropriate, taking into account the goals, potential payback, resource requirements and possible drawbacks. Effectively communicating the justification for choosing specific techniques and how the technique will accomplish the desired goals.', 'Compiling, processing, analyzing, and reporting various types of data to support decision making.', 'Ensuring that data, analysis, and research are organized, documented, and communicated in a way that they can be understood, interpreted, and acted upon effectively.', 'Communicating complex technical information effectively using verbal, written and visual communication skills including public speaking. Adapting communication style to various audiences.', 'The use of computers and a variety of software including Excel, Word, Outlook and SQL.', 'Organizational influence and leadership', 'Gaining the support of others through persuasiveness, credibility and expertise. Inspiring others to collaborate voluntarily.', 'Communicating effectively within interdisciplinary teams; including sharing accurate and pertinent information in a timely manner.', 'Consistently building and maintaining positive working relationships internally and externally, even in times of stress and conflict.', 'Participating in, facilitating, and supporting conflict resolution; exchanging feedback in an open, constructive, and professional manner.', 'Leading efforts to collaboratively make decisions, establish and meet timelines and deliver results that meet customer needs.', 'Improving work processes and efficiency.', 'Managing projects, setting clear, reasonable expectations and facilitating delivery and achievement.', 'Problem-solving and strategic judgment', 'Organizing and prioritizing work despite tight deadlines, multiple customers, and competing priorities; monitoring and reporting progress towards goals.', 'Leading teams to generate and implement workable and useful solutions to difficult problems.', 'Exhibiting situational awareness and strategic judgment. Recognizing when sources of information and/or partners should be consulted and when to apply past experiences.', 'Using intelligence, logical thinking, common sense, hard work and tenacity to solve difficult and complex challenges.', 'Identifying opportunities for creative problem solving while staying within the parameters of good practice.', 'Proficient Performance Requirements For Knowledge And Skills', 'Qualification to fulfill the full range of this position’s duties requires the following knowledge, which may be gained or further developed after entering the job:', 'Software applications including business intelligence tools and geographic information systems.', 'Public transit planning and operation principles and specific terms and programs including the National Transit Database (NTD).', 'Transit technology as a data source for transit planning analysis and research.', 'Community Transit planning, marketing, and operations.', 'Skills', 'Qualification to fulfill the full range of this position’s duties requires the following skills, which may be gained or further developed after entering the job', 'The use of software applications including ArcGIS.', 'Physical Requirements', 'Sedentary Work: Exerting up to 10 pounds of force occasionally and/or a negligible amount of force frequently or constantly to lift, carry, push, pull or otherwise move objects, including the human body. Sedentary work involves sitting most of the time. Jobs are sedentary if walking and standing are required only occasionally and all other sedentary criteria are met.', 'APPLICATION AND SELECTION PROCESS', 'On-line applications only at www.communitytransit.org. Please attach a resume and cover letter for consideration. The evaluation process may include interviews, background checks, reference checks and various performance tests. First Consideration by March 10, 2020', 'If you have a family member, or share the same living quarters of a current Community Transit employee, please let your Human Resources Recruiter know as your eligibility for this position may be affected.', 'Community Transit provides a tobacco-free and drug-free work environment. As a recipient of federal funds, Community Transit is an Equal Opportunity employer and does not unlawfully discriminate on any basis prohibited by Federal, State or Local law. We value and encourage diversity in our workforce. EOE AA/M/F/Vet/Disability. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to their race, color, religion, national origin, sex, protected veteran status or disability.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Nonprofit Organization Management', 'Government Administration']

Name: Data Analyst I, 2020
Description: ['Please note that this position will be starting in the summer of 2020. We are looking for applicants who are current college seniors, graduating in the spring of 2020.', 'Definitive Healthcare is a rapidly growing data and analytics provider of the most up-to-date, comprehensive, and integrated information on hospitals, physicians, and other healthcare providers.', 'Recently honored as one of the fastest growing private companies in Massachusetts and named a ', 'Best Place to Work', ' by both the Boston Business Journal and the Boston Globe, Definitive has more than doubled in size over the past 2 years and has over 400 employees. Our expansion has created the need for a talented, team oriented, and data driven Data Analyst I to join our Professional Services Team. If you would like to work on a product that is in high demand and evolving rapidly, keep reading!', 'Your Challenge', 'Our new Data Analyst I will help provide custom reports and recurring data extracts to our diverse client base. Your work will include synthesizing data in SQL and collaborating with colleagues and clients to deliver polished reports in a timely manner; all while balancing multiple ongoing projects and dealing with competing priorities and deadlines. Sound like fun?!', 'Specific Duties Will Include The Following', ' ', 'Generate quantitative reports of large-scale healthcare data for use in solving client business issues', ' ', 'Deliver custom projects using SQL, Excel, or other software', ' ', 'Work with the Product and Customer Success teams to deliver informed analyses to customers', ' ', 'Engage with customers over web conference to understand data use-cases and uncover reporting opportunities', ' ', 'Collaborate with fellow team members to implement optimized solutions', ' ', 'What You’ll Need', ' ', 'Bachelor’s Degree from a 4-year institution (e.g. Mathematics, Economics, Public Health, Business Analytics, etc. a plus)', ' ', '0-1 year of work experience in a professional office setting', ' ', 'Exposure to general technical applications or programming languages (e.g. SQL, Excel, STATA, SPSS, Access)', ' ', 'Exceptional attention to detail', ' ', 'Strong written and oral communication skills', ' ', 'High level of organization skills and the ability to juggle multiple tasks with minimal supervision', ' ', 'Why we love Definitive, and why you will too!', ' ', 'Industry leading products', ' ', 'Work hard, and have fun doing it', ' ', 'Incredibly fast growth means limitless opportunity', ' ', 'Flexible and dynamic culture', ' ', 'Work alongside some of the most talented and dedicated teammates', ' ', 'Definitive Cares, our community service group, gives all of us a chance to give back', ' ', 'Competitive benefits package including great healthcare benefits and a 401(k) match', ' ', 'What Our Employees Are Saying About Us On Glassdoor', '“Great Work atmosphere, great work life balance, excellent company to work for, amazing top notch product, incredible customer service, lots of tools to help you succeed.”', ' ', 'Business Development Manager', '“Great team. Amazing growth. Employees are treated very well.”', 'Research Analyst', '“I have waited 36 years to work at a dream job for a dream company and I am so happy to have finally got there.”', 'Profile Analyst', 'Definitive Hiring Philosophy', 'Definitive Healthcare is an equal opportunity employer that celebrates diversity and is committed to creating an inclusive workplace with equal opportunity for all applicants and teammates. Our goal is to recruit the most talented people from a diverse candidate pool regardless of race, color, religion, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation or any other status. If you’re interested in working in a fast growing, exciting working environment – we encourage you to apply!', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software']

Name: Data Analyst
Location: Washington, District of Columbia, United States
Description: ['The Position ', 'The Data Analyst helps analyze the Credit Risk Transfer deals placed in the market and manage the portfolio of prior transactions. He/She will utilize a variety of models developed within the analytics team to provide estimation of the performance of the deals under a variety of economic scenarios as well as identifying the drivers of changes in performance across deals (identifying impacts from changes such as collateral mix or economic changes). He/She will provide a wide variety of surveillance reporting on CRT deals that will be used within the team as well as by external teams.', ' Job Responsibilities', ' Evaluates deal performance for new and existing deals using internal models under a variety of scenarios ', ' Fully understands the underlying portfolio metrics as well as the technical nature (strengths/weakness) of the risk models that produce them. ', ' Fully understands how risk variables affect results ', ' Understands different capital regimes – rating agency, regulatory and economic. ', ' Assists in creating Transaction Analytics Reports for senior management and other internal groups that may then be shared with third party clients. ', ' Develop analytical tools to support portfolio surveillance. ', ' Keep abreast of the latest changes in U.S. housing and mortgage industry. ', ' Knowledge & Skills', ' Required Skills/Experience ', ' General knowledge of analytic tools/languages (e.g. SQL, SAS, R, Python) and basic programming concepts and principles. ', ' Proficient in Data Visualization tools (e.g. Power BI, Tableau, Qlik) ', ' Proficient in MS Excel; able to convert raw data into meaningful formats for analysis. ', ' Detail-oriented with strong analytical skills. ', ' Good organizational skills to manage independent work. ', ' Good interpersonal and communication skills to work effectively with internal and external contacts. ', ' Education ', 'Required knowledge and skills would typically be acquired through a Bachelor’s degree and 1-2 years of experience, or a Master’s degree. Course of study in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Economics, Finance, Data Science or related degrees required.', ' Working Conditions/Environment & Physical Demands ', ' ', ' Normal office environment ', 'Disclaimer', 'Incumbent may be asked to perform other duties as required.', ' The Company', 'About Our Company', 'Arch Capital Group Ltd. is a Bermuda-based company which provides insurance, reinsurance and mortgage insurance on a worldwide basis. Arch Capital Services Inc. provides support and expertise to entities across ACGL to help them operate effectively and efficiently. Arch is committed to helping its associates create what’s next by providing access to a variety of programs supporting your professional development and a culture that encourages innovation, collaboration and professional growth. We seek talent that thinks innovatively, values collaboration and will go the extra mile to serve our customers and develop our company.', 'Arch Capital Services Inc', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Insurance', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['About the Data Analyst Position', ' ', ' ', '  ', 'As a technology leader, we have high-traffic websites and store  massive amounts of data that we need to slice and dice every day. We are  looking for a Data Analyst that will be part of a growing, world-class  team supporting our account management and site optimization groups. The  ideal candidate for the Data Analyst role will be a key resource for  analytic best practices within Study.com and for analyzing and querying  data in a fast-paced Internet business environment. ', ' ', '  ', 'The Data Analyst must be passionate about digging into data and  understanding the stories the data are telling. You will be equally  passionate about helping others solve problems, gain insights, and make  decisions using data. ', ' ', '  ', 'Responsibilities: ', ' ', '  ', 'As part of the Business Intelligence team, own and maintain the entire data warehouse, including tens of millions of events coming through a Kafka queue each day, a 15 TB relational data warehouse, and integration with Google BigQuery. ', "Work in a cross-functional team and be the team's point person for any data related tasks (ETLing, analysis, visualizations, etc.). ", 'Monitor and analyze the team’s A/B tests and proactively communicate key insights within your team and to external stakeholders. ', "Be the voice of data by supporting the team's product owner in making data driven decisions and defining KPIs. ", 'Actively establish processes and build tools to make data more accessible to everyone. ', 'Use your knowledge of statistics to support the Business Intelligence team in building and maintaining machine learning models (logistic regressions, recurrent neural nets, etc.) that drive a significant portion of our revenue. ', 'Help and teach others throughout the company to better use and understand our data. ', '  ', '  ', ' ', 'Requirements: ', ' ', '  ', ' ', 'A passion for learning and a willingness to pick up whatever you need to to get the job done ', ' ', "4+ years' experience in a data analyst role, experience with web analytics is a plus ", ' ', 'Solid MySQL/SQL experience or other related databases ', ' ', 'Solid experience in Excel for data analysis and visualization ', ' ', 'Strong analytical skills and ability to draw conclusions based on data ', ' ', 'Comfortable working in a fast-paced, dynamic environment while juggling multiple projects ', ' ', 'BS in Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, Operations Research, or similar fields ', ' ', 'Good interpersonal communication and presentation skills ', ' ', 'Self-motivated, detail-oriented and passionate ', ' ', '  ', ' ', 'Preferred Qualifications: ', ' ', '  ', ' ', 'Reporting and Business Intelligence experience (Tableau, QlikView, Microstrategy, etc) ', ' ', 'Proficient in using statistical software (R, MATLAB, SAS, etc.) ', ' ', 'Hands-on experience with advanced statistical concepts, such as  cluster analysis, singular value decomposition, stochastic gradient  descent, and Bayesian methods ', ' ', 'Experience using an ETL tool (Pentaho, Talend, SSIS, etc.) on large datasets (terabytes in size) ', ' ', 'Knowledge of web analytics software and best practices ', ' ', 'Knowledge of programming knowledge in a scripting language such as  Groovy, Python, Perl, or in a compiled language such as Java or C++ ', ' ', 'Higher degrees such as Masters or PhD', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Analyst', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'E-Learning', 'Higher Education', 'Education Management']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ["What You'll Do", 'Do you love working with data? Are you passionate about turning complex data into information, information into insight, and insight into business decisions? Then the Cisco Customer & Partner Data Operations team may be an exceptional opportunity for you.', 'In this role, you will', 'Build, update, and maintain Tableau and Power BI dashboards', 'Perform ad-hoc data analysis to answer specific business questions and audit data quality', 'Build and maintain Python data pipelines in support of analytics projects and reports', 'Build, maintain and support data-driven applications and related infrastructure', 'Identify, analyze, and interpret patterns in complex data sets', 'See opportunities for innovation and automation of internal processes', 'Share knowledge and insights through documentation, presentations, and demonstrations for business and technical users', 'Have a solid focus on internal customers, professional demeanor, and high intellectual curiosity with the ability to learn new concepts/frameworks and technology rapidly as changes arise.', "Who You'll Work With", 'On this team, we interface between technical and business teams to solve problems. We work with management to prioritize their business and information needs. We partner with technical and support teams to implement data pipelines, automate business processes, and analyze program and performance metrics. We work to break down information silos and support each other to accomplish our goals and grow our skills.', 'Minimum Requirements', 'BS in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or related field', '3+ years of experience as a business data analyst or a data analyst', 'Proficient using SQL to obtain and manipulate data', 'Data visualization experience using Tableau or other BI tools', 'Knowledge of Python or similar language, especially data processing libraries and techniques', 'Strong documentation and communication skills', 'We Are Cisco', '#WeAreCisco, where each person is unique, but we bring our talents to work as a team and make a difference. Here’s how we do it.', 'We embrace digital and help our customers implement change in their digital businesses. Some may think we’re “old” (30 years strong!) and only about hardware, but we’re also a software company. And a security company. An AI/Machine Learning company. We even invented an intuitive network that adapts, predicts, learns and protects. No other company can do what we do – you can’t put us in a box!', 'But “Digital Transformation” is an empty buzz phrase without a culture that allows for innovation, creativity, and yes, even failure (if you learn from it.)', 'Day to day, we focus on the give and take. We give our best, we give our egos a break and we give of ourselves (because giving back is built into our DNA.) We take accountability, we take bold steps, and we take the difference to heart. Because without diversity of thought and a commitment to equality for all, there is no moving forward.', 'So, you have colorful hair? Don’t care. Tattoos? Show off your ink. Like polka dots? That’s cool.', 'GEM20', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Computer Hardware', 'Computer Software', 'Computer Networking']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['DOMA Technologies delivers comprehensive and managed cloud services in support of federal, healthcare, state, local, education, and commercial customers. The DOMA DX7.7 Content Services Platform is a powerful cloud based Intelligent Content Services Platform that is delivered as a Software as a Service (SaaS) solution. DOMA has built an unparalleled development team focused on cloud application development delivering all aspects of the requirement gathering, design, development, testing, and deployment. We assist federal, health, and private organizations to embrace intelligent automation and stay one step ahead.', 'We are looking for a Data Analyst to join our team at our main office located in Virginia Beach, VA. We offer the potential for career development, the opportunity to create positive change in the world, and the chance to be a part of a great team. And we are committed to being an equal opportunity employer.', 'Summary of Position', 'The Data Analyst will provide analytical insights to support business solution development based on metrics and other key drivers. The position is responsible for identifying and analyzing data patterns and developing recommendations to improve varied business metrics.', 'Essential Duties And Responsibilities', ' Analyzes data and summarizes performance using summary statistical procedures.', ' Develops and analyzes incoming volume and business performance reports (e.g. for claims, data, provider data, utilization data) and provides notations of performance deviations and anomalies.', ' Performs qualitative and quantitative techniques and processes to enhance productivity and business gain.', ' Creates and publishes periodic reports, as well as any necessary ad hoc reports.', ' Provides leadership team recommendations based upon data analysis.', ' Develops and refines analysis templates for problem diagnosis and opportunities assessment; ability to manipulate large sets of data is required', ' Develops predictive models and other tools that help predict data trends.', ' Conducts in-depth research to address challenging issues in measuring outcomes.', ' May collaborate with businesses and technical areas to implement new or enhanced products.', ' Analyzes complex end user needs to determine optimal means of meeting those needs.', ' Identifies and recommends business process improvements to reduce effort, increase work quality, and mitigate bottlenecks, and prepare process documentation, workflows, and functional requirements for the future state.', ' Other duties as assigned.', 'Qualifications', " Bachelor's degree from an accredited university in Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or related field.", ' 5+ years of relevant experience in data analytics and/or statistical analysis.', ' 3+ years of experience with business intelligence software tools.', 'Knowledge, Skills and Abilities', ' Strong analytical, organizational and problem-solving skills. This job is focused on complex and varied metrics, making recommendations and aiding staff.', ' Demonstrated ability to present complex concepts to groups of varying levels of technical and management responsibility and experience, both verbally and in writing.', ' Must be able to work independently.', ' Strong communication, presentation, and writing skills, including the ability to work closely with customers and conduct high level meetings with clients.', ' Ability to solve practical problems and deal with a variety of concrete variables in situations where only limited standardization exists.', 'DOMA Technologies is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate against candidates or employees based on race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, pregnancy, disability, military status, veteran status, genetic history or any other protected status. DOMA encourages all qualified individuals to apply.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Hospital & Health Care']

Name: Junior Customer Data Analyst
Description: ['The Startup', 'Located in breathtaking downtown Santa Barbara, centered in the vibrant, up-and-coming Haley Corridor, Briq is altering the landscape for construction decision making. We are harnessing the power of data to build the industry’s first construction data cloud. Leaders in automation, machine learning, and artificial intelligence, Briq is delivering deep insights empowering construction professionals to drive better outcomes.', 'The Skinny', 'Briq is creating amazing products and even better teams. We are growing fast and are looking for great people to join us. We are seeking an energetic and self-starting Customer Data Analyst to play a critical role in our accelerated growth.', 'Our team of strategists, leaders, data scientists, and change-makers are revolutionizing the world by providing optimized tools that improve decision-making in one of the most changing industries today. Our clients are among the largest builders in the world; responsible for creating the infrastructure you thrive on and building the places where you live, work and play. They are hungry for better, smarter data and we are hungry for your talents to help make it happen.', 'The Skill', 'The Briq Customer Data Science team is looking for a Customer Data Analyst to accelerate growth. In this role, you are responsible for delivering dependable and valuable insights to Briq clients.', 'You will indulge your passion for developing business metrics and insights from complex datasets. You will work closely with construction company executives, project managers, ETL engineers, software development engineers, and product managers to produce reports and analyses that provide our clients with deep insights.', 'You are able to turn ambiguous business questions into clearly defined problem sets, research and develop quantifiable metrics, implement Extract-Transform-Load (ETL) processes, and deliver high quality results on time.', 'You enjoy designing insightful reports and compelling data visualizations with high attention to quality, and want to automate everything you have built.', 'To Be Successful, You', 'Deliver project charters with timelines, milestones, and regular updates to clients through project management principles & techniques.', 'Maintain above-industry levels of client retention', 'Deliver high quality, trusted, results with zero data-defects', 'On a normal day at Briq HQ, a Customer Data Analyst can be found:', 'Analyzing new data from multiple public and private sources, and instruct the necessary teams with how to ingest, transform, analyze and present the results to answer complex questions about our clients’ business', 'Developing records management processes and policies', 'Conceptualizing dashboard wire-frames with the goal of enabling data-driven decision making', 'Presenting complex topics to key client stakeholders and senior executives', 'Delivering recommendations to our clients on how to improve construction KPIs', 'Ensuring models and results are implemented correctly in the Briq platform', 'Work with ETL engineers and clients to improve client’s data hygiene', 'Share the reports for internal and external audiences using the Briq platform', 'Write SQL queries to extract data from the data warehouse', 'Define and work with ETL, automation, and product teams to establish and maintain automated data processes', 'Exercise extreme level of due diligence in regards to client data quality', 'The Standard', 'To succeed in this role and at Briq, you are driven, dedicated, and committed to advancing your career. You hustle, collaborate, innovate, have an unmatched attention to detail, and are constantly challenging yourself to learn and grow. You LOVE to learn new things and adapt easily when trajectories pivot. You have an insatiable curiosity we will struggle to please and mad communications skills. You’re empathetic, enthusiastic, and eager to work harder than you ever have before.', 'You have a great attention to detail and pride yourself in delivering projects with the highest levels of quality.. Furthermore, you’re the type of person who is energized by and embraces the challenge of managing multiple complex projects simultaneously. And you enjoy tackling challenges head on and innovative problem solving.', 'You have 1-2 years experience in a related field. You hold at least a Bachelor’s Degree in mathematics, statistics, or business with an analytics focus. You are experienced in statistical methodologies, complex modeling, data cleansing, and data enriching techniques.', 'You succeed because you have strong project management skills and a combination of analytical skills, intellectual curiosity, creative problem solving, reporting acumen and strong technical skills. You have some knowledge of SQL, R, or Python.', 'You love to tell compelling stories built on a foundation of data and supported by exceptional visualizations. And you are comfortable presenting these stories and engaging in business and data discussions with company executives.', 'Briq is an equal opportunity employer and values diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. If you think you have what it takes to thrive here, we want you!', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

We ease anxiety and fear around digital transformation and replace it with opportunity.', 'Qualified applicants, please respond to inquire@launchcg.com with your full name, resume, and a brief description of how your skills match the requirements above. ', 'Please refer to job #3646', 'Launch Consulting is an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Description', 'Model N is looking for a highly motivated Data Analyst reporting to the Senior Director, Professional Services to join our exciting High-Tech Data Analyst team. This Data Analyst role will review, analyze, and ensures the quality of customer data. You will work with business data formats to identify, compare, and ensure Directory (address information) quality.', 'Essential Functions', 'Ability to search and identify key information for addresses and product attributes while updating and adding to existing product catalog data', 'Possess good comprehension of geography or foreign countries-preferably key global (international) market locations.', 'Follows data quality standards, metrics and audit procedures as defined and set forth by Manager-Directory Governance.', 'Correct data quality errors and produce required revisions according to audit procedures, either with system tools or user interfaces.', 'Adhere to standard company protocol/policy and respect Directory privacy & security.', 'Run reports using various tools such as Looker, Jasper Reporting, Tableau, or others', 'Maintain high-quality output and exceptional customer service', 'Qualifications', 'Bachelor’s degree in computer science, statistics, data analysis, operations or equivalent is preferred', '1 year of Data Analyst/Data Entry experience or equivalent is preferred', 'Excellent analytical thinking with the ability to connect the dots', 'Technical skills necessary to work with computer systems is a must. With deep industry expertise, Model N supports the complex business needs of the world’s leading brands in pharmaceutical, medical technology, semiconductor, and high-tech manufacturing across more than 100 countries, including Johnson & Johnson, AstraZeneca, Novartis, Microchip Technology and ON Semiconductor. For more information, visit www.modeln.com. Model N® is the registered trademark of Model N, Inc. Name: Private Equity Data Analyst
Description: ["Company Overview LP Analyst is a leading independent private asset cloud-based analytics and consulting solutions firm that works closely with many of the industry's most prominent institutional investors (LPs) and fund managers (GPs) to get better, more actionable decision making intelligence into the hands of today's demanding investors. Our firm truly sits at the intersection of private asset analytics and consulting which means we take both a highly quantitative and qualitative approach to tackling big challenges and developing cutting-edge solutions for our clients. For our data analyst team, this means not only getting into the details when working with large amounts of private asset data across a wide range of strategies but also an opportunity to synthesize this information, through the firm's proprietary reporting and analytics platform, for key decision makers at our clients' programs, including private asset class heads and chief investment officers. So if you are a high achiever who is passionate about disrupting the private asset analytics and consulting landscape while also being part of a strong, motivated and innovative team of young professionals, LP Analyst might be the right place for you. Job Summary This is a contractor position that supports the Private Asset team. The contractor role can lead to full-time employment. Responsibilities and Duties Assisting on projects focused on Private Equity, Venture Capital, Real Estate, Real Asset, Infrastructure and Credit strategies Working with private asset financial statements Organizing and entering private asset financial metrics and company data Performing research on a range of private asset related topics Contributing to diligence, monitoring, valuation and other consulting deliverables Supporting the marketing of the firm's analytics and consulting solutions Qualifications and Skills Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics or related field (GPA of 3.3+) 0-2 years of business-related experience (including coursework or other internships) Strong Excel skills; Proficiency in PowerPoint a plus Exceptionally high attention to detail and proficiency with numbers High self-motivation with ability to learn quickly and meet deadlines Strong written / verbal communication and interpersonal skills Excellent written / verbal communication and interpersonal skills Positive attitude, energy and overall enthusiasm for private assets, financial data and analytics Benefits and Perks Great company culture with free snacks, access to office gym, free parking and casual dress code", 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Finance', 'Sales', 'Industries', 'Venture Capital & Private Equity', 'Financial Services', 'Investment Management']

Description: ['About The Team…', 'The Compliance Team is responsible for proactively protecting the DoorDash platform from risk. The main tasks revolve around background adjudication for all potential candidates. Accurate and efficient adjudication not only protects our platform but also our customers and merchants. Furthermore, the team is responsible for fraudulent financial activity, claims reporting and garnishments. adjudicating background and motor vehicle checks on potential Dashers.', 'The Trust and Safety Team presents a united front to protect DoorDash’s Merchants, Customers and Dashers. Through the team’s proactive approach, we are aggressively maintaining, building and protecting DoorDash’s brand. By staying on top of stakeholder escalations, monitoring our day-to-day data for outliers, and improving our detection tools, we empower DoorDash’s teams to focus on creating an amazing experience for our Merchants, Customer, and Dashers. This position is a tremendous opportunity to join a fast growing team with an extreme focus on building DoorDash’s Trust and Safety brand, while protecting our community.', ' ', 'Please note: due to current circumstances, our recruiting process is currently being run entirely via phone and Zoom video conference', ' ', 'About The Role…', 'The CTnS Junior Data Analyst is responsible for analyzing large data sets in SQL, verifying the accuracy of queries, and presenting their data through dashboards and other tools.', 'The CTnS Junior Data Analyst is expected to collaborate within the team, as well as, cross functionally with business partners. You will be responsible for building out reports through SQL, Salesforce, and Google Sheets. Through collaboration, you will help identify problems, and make recommendations to improve the process.', 'The CTnS Junior Data Analyst is a problem solver and a subject matter expert who is always looking for ways to help the team become more efficient by streamlining processes and eliminating waste. They are excellent communicators who know how to communicate complex topics effectively.', 'You Are Excited About This Opportunity Because You Will...', ' ', 'Analyze large data sets in SQL, Python or similar tools.', ' ', 'Produce ad hoc queries from scratch.', ' ', 'Produce ad hoc reports and data as needed.', ' ', 'Review query results for accuracy and anomalies.', ' ', 'Actively identify areas of improvement and conceptualize methods on how to be more efficient.', ' ', 'Prioritize tasks in a rapidly changing environment based on business needs.', ' ', 'Coach the CTnS teams through technical problems.', ' ', 'Communicate up to senior leaders and make recommendations.', ' ', 'Complete projects with GoogleApps scripting.', ' ', 'Perform additional duties as assigned.', ' ', 'We Are Excited About You Because...', ' ', 'You are comfortable working with highly sensitive and provocative content.', ' ', 'You have a mind and talent for process improvement.', ' ', 'You have strong verbal and written communication skills. You are able to translate technical concepts to a non-technical audience and are comfortable communicating with business partners.', ' ', 'You are an analytical thinker who can create data-driven recommendations.', ' ', 'You thrive in a dynamic and fast-paced environment with frequently changing goals.', ' ', 'You have a track record of maintaining a high-level of professional maturity.', ' ', 'You are innovative and you are not afraid to challenge the status quo.', ' ', 'You operate autonomously while collaborating closely with business partners.', ' ', 'You are a hustler with an entrepreneurial mindset and a bias to action.', ' ', 'Experience and basic understanding of at least one dashboarding tool.', ' ', 'You have 2-4 years of relevant technical experience.', ' ', 'Bachelor’s degree preferred.', ' ', 'It would be great if…', ' ', 'You have knowledge of Salesforce, Jira, Chartio, Mode, Tableau, AWS, back-end development, and IT.', ' ', 'Why You’ll Love Working at DoorDash', ' ', 'We are leaders', ' - Leadership is not limited to our management team. It’s something everyone at DoorDash embraces and embodies.', ' ', 'We are doers', ' - We believe the only way to predict the future is to build it. Creating solutions that will lead our company and our industry is what we do -- on every project, every day. ', ' ', 'We are learning', ' - We’re not afraid to dig in and uncover the truth, even if it’s scary or inconvenient. Everyone here is continually learning on the job, no matter if we’ve been in a role for one year or one minute.', ' ', 'We are customer obsessed', ' - Our mission is to grow and empower local economies. We are committed to our customers, merchants, and dashers and believe in connecting people with possibility.', ' ', 'We are all DoorDash', ' - The magic of DoorDash is our people, together making our inspiring goals attainable and driving us to greater heights. ', ' ', 'We offer great compensation packages and comprehensive health benefits.', ' ', 'About DoorDash', 'DoorDash is a technology company that connects customers with their favorite local and national businesses in over 4,000 cities and all 50 states across the United States and Canada. Founded in 2013, DoorDash empowers merchants to grow their businesses by offering on-demand delivery, data-driven insights, and better in-store efficiency, providing delightful experiences from door to door. By building the last-mile delivery infrastructure for local cities, DoorDash is bringing communities closer, one doorstep at a time. Read more on the DoorDash blog or at www.doordash.com.', 'Our Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion', 'We’re committed to growing and empowering a more inclusive community within our company, industry, and cities. That’s why we hire and cultivate diverse teams of the best and brightest from all backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. We believe that true innovation happens when everyone has room at the table and the tools, resources, and opportunity to excel.', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Data Analyst, Analytics
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['Overview', 'The Orchard is a leading music distribution company operating in over 40 markets worldwide - distributing music from independent artists including Ozuna, Skepta, Jorja Smith, John Prine, and Kelsea Ballerini. With cutting edge operations and an unparalleled global team, The Orchard partners with labels of all sizes to make their music and video available across hundreds of digital and physical retailers around the world. At The Orchard, the focus is to provide a comfortable, social and engaging environment to encourage productivity and creativity.', 'The Orchard is hiring a Technical Data Analyst, Analytics to join our New York team.', 'Responsibilities', 'Reporting to the Director, Analytics based in New York, NY, The Orchard has an immediate opening for a full-time Technical Data Analyst, working on data modeling, analytics architecture, and the development of our set of internal BI tools. This person will be responsible for understanding business requirements as communicated by internal stakeholders, translating them into technical solutions, and executing on the work required to accomplish those solutions. Success in this position requires a strong ability to communicate and collaborate within the team and with internal stakeholders across The Orchard.', 'Qualifications', ' 2-4 years experience working as an analyst with a focus on technical solutions', ' SQL Expert', ' Extensive experience with data modeling', ' Familiarity with Python or other scripting language', ' Familiarity with BI tools such as Looker, Tableau, etc', ' Experience using dbt, Jenkins (or other chron scheduling tool), or LookML a plus', 'Responsibilities', ' Liaise with engineering teams to ensure current systems are being leveraged', ' Build upon a set of existing data models to meet internal user needs', ' Understand business needs and facilitate technical solutions that provide efficient and streamlined access for business users', ' Prioritize business requests and accurately scope out the level of effort from a development perspective', ' Organize and maintain existing code base in existing git repository', ' Create systems that allow for analysts to collaborate on code base', ' Provide subject matter expertise in collaboration with the product and engineering teams to provide best in class analytic solutions for our clients.', 'The Ideal Candidate Has', ' A passion for data, especially for creating efficient and scalable models', ' An ability to extract the essence of a business request across various disciplines and translate those needs into a data solution', ' The ability to work independently and effectively communicate successes and roadblocks across various teams', ' Curiosity about unfamiliar data sets, and once they become familiar, new ways to model that data to create self-service analytics solutions', ' Working knowledge of the music industry, and an understanding of the current music consumption landscape', 'About The Orchard', 'The Orchard is a leading music distribution company operating in over 40 markets worldwide. With a comprehensive artist & label services offering including full-service marketing, sync licensing, comprehensive video services, transparent data analysis, advertising, rights management, digital and physical distribution and more, The Orchard empowers creators and businesses to grow and adapt in the dynamic global industry. For further information, visit www.theorchard.com.', 'The Orchard is committed to providing equal employment opportunity for all persons regardless of age, disability, national origin, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity or expression, pregnancy, veteran or military status, marital and civil partnership/union status, alienage or citizenship status, creed, genetic information or any other status protected by applicable federal, state, or local law.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Restaurants']

Name: SQL Data Analyst I
Description: ['Company Description', 'Zayo Group Holdings, Inc. provides communications infrastructure solutions, including fiber and bandwidth connectivity, colocation and cloud infrastructure to the world’s leading businesses. Customers include wireless and wireline carriers, media and content companies, cloud providers, finance and professional services and other large enterprises. Zayo provides customers with flexible solutions and self-service through Tranzact, an innovative online platform for managing and purchasing bandwidth.', 'Position Description', 'This position is primarily responsible for maintaining the Big Data case queue and ensuring Sales and Business Development requests are handled within the prescribed SLA. Name: Data Reduction Analyst
Description: ['Aerojet Rocketdyne is seeking a Data Reduction Analyst to join our facility in Redmond, Washington', '. In this role, you will play a vital function in the successful hot fire testing of our rockets, which includes testing of monopropellant, bipropellant, and electric thrusters for various in-space applications. The Data Reduction Analyst will contribute to our success by preparing data reduction software to process raw data from rocket engine test firings.', 'This position may be filled at this level or one level higher.', '70% - Using AR developed software programs, process recorded data files in order to exhibit performance parameters for various models of AR products that are undergoing acceptance or development testing.', '20% - Process instrumentation sensor calibrations and coordinate results with test and calibration personnel. Store calibrations results in online databases and prepare sensor calibration information to deliver to test personnel.', '5% - Verify Test Control Software listings that they comply with requirements of test procedures.', '5% - Support software related day of testing activities in control bay to verify real time performance of rockets.', "Qualifications: A bachelor's degree in an engineering discipline or mathematics is preferred, but not required. Description: ['Tracking Code 1068271_RR00040535 Job Description', 'NYU Grossman School of Medicine', " is one of the nation's top-ranked medical schools. For 175 years, NYU Grossman School of Medicine has trained thousands of physicians and scientists who have helped to shape the course of medical history and enrich the lives of countless people. An integral part of NYU Langone Health, the Grossman School of Medicine at its core is committed to improving the human condition through medical education, scientific research, and direct patient care. For more information, go to med.nyu.edu, and interact with us on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram.", 'Position Summary', 'We have an exciting opportunity to join our team as a Data Analyst.', 'This position will manage large data and execute ongoing analysis of research questions related to the food environment, eating and food purchasing behaviors. The data analyst will process data from conceptualization through presentation and will be responsible for management of datasets, mainly sales and nutrition data from a national restaurant chain. The analyst will work in the Department of Population Healths Section on Health Choice, Policy and Evaluation (HCPE), a dynamic and active research group dedicated to determining the influence of public policy on health and health choices and advancing ways to make policies more effective. Using multidisciplinary approaches, particularly behavioral economics, the group focuses on low-income, racial and ethnic minority populations and pressing public health problems, with a significant focus on obesity. A strong area of interest for the group is growing our capacity to use machine learning techniques to solve health problems. The analyst will support a dynamic group to make informed policy recommendations that impact health policy, health choice/behavior, health economics, and population health.', 'Job Responsibilities', ' ', 'Assist in writing and editing manuscripts for publication', ' ', 'Conduct relevant literature reviews to inform cohort selection, variable definitions, and analytic methods', ' ', 'Participate in data-driven decision making with investigators', ' ', 'Accurately and appropriately communicate the processes used and results achieved, suggest new and alternative approaches', ' ', 'Prepare reports, charts and tables of data for faculty and staff', ' ', 'Develop, manage, and improve databases to track provenance and versioning', ' ', 'Detect and address issues in data and analytic results', ' ', 'Perform statistical analyses according to the study design', ' ', 'Import and clean raw datasets, monitor, evaluate and improve data quality, and create analytic datasets', ' ', 'Communicate projects needs and requirements with external teams, such as the IT departments and our partner organizations', ' ', 'Minimum Qualifications', ' ', "To qualify you must have a Bachelor's Degree with 1-2 years relevant work experience in Public Health, Economics, Statistics, Biostatistics, or related quantitative research field", ' ', 'Must be proficient in SQL, preferably MySQL', ' ', 'Strong statistical computing skills', ' ', 'Proficiency with statistical software such as R, Python or others ', ' ', 'Keen attention to detail and good documentation habits.', ' ', 'Excellent written and oral communication skills. ', ' ', 'Strong ability to identify, analyze and solve problems.', ' ', 'Self-directed and able to manage priorities on multiple projects simultaneously, strong time-management skills. ', ' ', 'Must work and communicate effectively with partners.', ' ', 'Preferred Qualifications', ' ', 'Experience working with large datasets ', ' ', 'Experience working with high performing clusters', ' ', 'Interest in learning new programming languages. ', ' ', 'Experience contributing to research or articles for peer review.', ' ', 'Qualified candidates must be able to effectively communicate with all levels of the organization.', "NYU Grossman School of Medicine provides its staff with far more than just a place to work. Description: ['Artsy’s mission is to expand the art market to support more artists and art in the world. Artsy has created the world’s largest two-sided art marketplace, with more than 1,000,000 works by 100,000 artists from 4,000 of the world’s leading galleries, auction houses, art fairs, and institutions across 190 countries.', 'We are seeking a Data Analyst who is technical enough to dive deep but strategic enough to think big, question existing assumptions, and help uncover new product and business opportunities. Analysts are comfortable operating in unstructured environments where they can proactively identify problems and opportunities, communicate them clearly to stakeholders and leadership, and offer data-informed suggestions and solutions.', 'Key Responsibilities', ' ', 'Being a strategic partner to PM and business leaders to drive the right business outcomes', ' ', 'Building statistical and machine learning models (like Time-Series Forecasting Models, Regressions, Kmeans Clustering, Random Forest, SVM etc.) to answer business and product challenges', ' ', 'Designing and reporting on A/B tests using rigorous hypothesis testing methods', ' ', 'Modeling data in our data pipeline and Looker in response to reporting requirements', ' ', 'Maintaining and contributing to the ETL (extract-transform-load) pipeline', ' ', 'Working with stakeholders to ascertain modeling needs for analytics and reporting purposes', ' ', 'Informing, setting and tracking Key Results for our product and business teams ', ' ', 'Communicating results to leadership, peers, and the wider team', ' ', 'Candidate Qualifications', '2+ years of relevant analytical experience at a technology company or 1+ year of experience and a degree in a quantitative field', ' ', 'Proficient with SQL and statistical programming in either R or Python', ' ', 'Knowledge of probability, statistical bias and inference, and how to calculate statistical power of an experiment', ' ', 'Knowledge of common statistical and machine learning models and how to apply them to real-world problems', ' ', 'Able to design compelling data visualizations and to explain difficult concepts simply', ' ', 'Ability to prioritize in terms of impact and velocity and unafraid to make hard calls about how to spend time', ' ', 'Able to work both independently and collaboratively within a dynamic data analytics org to initiate and promote best-practices across the team', ' ', 'Energetic, curious, thoughtful and passionate about defining problems and reaching conclusions.', ' ', 'Ability to dig deep and discover the backstory to any data point', ' ', 'Understanding that data doesn’t fall from the sky in .csv form', ' ', 'About Artsy Data', 'Artsy has a dynamic, data-driven culture in which analytical insights guide continuous improvement in our products, operations and strategy. By building strong partnerships with key stakeholders in business, product, and engineering, the Data Science and Analytics team develops and enables insights across all our products and business operations. We work on challenges like defining the right metrics to track, implementing ways to track and measure those metrics, and recommending and leading initiatives to improve them.', 'Artsy Values', 'Artsy has five core values that will inform your experience at Artsy.', 'Art x Science:', ' We believe in uniting empathy with logic, emotion with data, and intuition with research in everything we do. Whether in business strategy or design, culture or code, we seek the magic that happens when the often separate worlds of art and science come together.', 'People are Paramount:', ' We spend extraordinary energy finding the best person for a job—and once found, we give them the trust and autonomy to be CEO of their role. We avoid pointless bureaucracy and prefer to empower people with information rather than limit them with process.', 'Quality Worthy of Art:', ' We aim to create an experience worthy of all the world’s art and so hold ourselves to the highest standards in all our work. We believe that the best long term quality comes from rapid shipping, iterating, and learning as we go.', 'Positive Energy:', ' We know positivity and optimism benefit our work, and we harness positive energy as a vehicle towards greater awareness, growth, and collaboration. We believe in cultivating a positive relationship to art as opposed to one based on exclusivity or scarcity.', 'Openness:', ' We believe in being open with each other and the world—whether in open-sourcing our code, sharing feedback, or building a diverse and inclusive work culture. We believe in bringing our full selves to work and manifesting an open world where everyone has access to art.', 'Artsy is an equal opportunity employer. We value a diverse workforce and an inclusive culture. We encourage applications from all qualified individuals without regard to race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, national origin, marital status, disability, and veteran status.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Data Strategist Analyst
Description: ['Overview', 'At WellStar, we all share common goals. That’s what makes us so successful – and such an integral part of our communities. We want the same things, for our organization, for our patients, and for our colleagues. As the most integrated healthcare provider in Georgia, this means we pride ourselves on investing in the communities that we serve. We continue to provide innovative care models, focused on improving quality and access to healthcare.', 'Responsibilities', 'The WellStar Marketing team is hiring a new Data Analyst reporting to the Executive Director of Knowledge and Insight. Our marketing team is fast-paced, thoughtful and purpose driven organization. We are looking for an individual that brings an entrepreneurial, self-starter mindset in a rapidly growing organization. The K&I team provides thought leadership and actionable insights to support the WellStar Marketing Community.', 'A successful candidate must be highly skilled in all aspects of data analytics, including mining, generation, and visualization. He/she will be expected to leverage best practices and willing to think out-side the box to uncover holistic', 'insights to inform strategies and drivers of in-market performance.', ' Data Querying and Data Management', ' Generating Data Driven Reports and Applications', ' Organizing and Reporting Results to Stakeholders', ' Able to build reports and connect various data sources within Tableau', ' Able to manage API data transfer and access', ' Able to liaison with Business Intelligence and IT', ' This position does not oversee any direct reports.', 'Key Traits', ' Brings an entrepreneurial, self-starter mindset in a rapidly growing marketing organization.', ' Able to operate with limited structure short-term and show thought leadership to establish processes and structure to achieve long-term harmony.', ' Open to changes in role’s scope and responsibilities to drive value for the organization and personal growth.', 'Qualifications', 'Required Minimum Education:', ' Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Finance, Computer Science, Information Science, Healthcare Analytics, or equivalent experience', 'Required Minimum Experience', ' 3+ years experience mining data as a data analyst', ' Proven analytic skills, including mining, evaluation, analysis, and visualization', ' Prior experience with database and model design and segmentation techniques', ' Proven success in a collaborative, team-oriented environment', 'Required Minimum Skills', ' Strong Tableau, SQL and Excel skills with the ability to learn other analytic tools', ' Knowledge and use of Epic, Healthgrades, NRC, IRI, Nielsen, Millward Brown, Kantar, Datarama, CRM or equivalent sources of data', ' Knowledge of data warehousing and APIs', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Business Development', 'Sales', 'Industries', 'Health, Wellness and Fitness', 'Hospital & Health Care', 'Medical Practice']

Name: Product Data Analyst
Description: ['Are you curious, motivated, and forward-thinking? At FIS you’ll have the opportunity to work on some of the most challenging and relevant issues in financial services and technology. Our talented people empower us, and we believe in being part of a team that is open, collaborative, entrepreneurial, passionate and above all fun. ', 'FIS, a global leader in financial technology solutions, is looking for an organized and enthusiastic data analyst to join the fast-growing Data Products team.  This is an individual work with directly with the product team to develop data, insights, and analytical output for clients. He/she will develop a keen understanding of the data, write software programs, algorithms, and automated processes to transform large datasets into meaningful information for gathering insight. ', ' ', 'Responsibilities:', ' ', 'Interacts with product and service teams to understand client use cases and translate business problems to programs so data can be delivered to the client ', 'Designs and maintains data systems and databases; this includes fixing coding errors and other data-related problems ', 'Designs, develops and programs methods, processes, and systems to consolidate and analyze, diverse "big data" sources to generate actionable insights and solutions for client services and product enhancement ', 'Develops strong understanding of the FIS/Worldpay data sets and identifies ways to enhance its value by combining it with other data sets ', 'Collaborates with programmers, engineers, and organizational leaders to identify opportunities for process improvements, recommend system modifications, and develop policies for data governance ', 'Creating appropriate documentation that allows stakeholders to understand the steps of the data analysis process and duplicate or replicate the analysis if necessary. ', 'Works in cross-functional teams and work independently ', 'Builds strong working relationships with shared services teams ', ' ', 'Business/Communication skills:', ' ', ' ', 'Required: ', 'Ability to work in a fast paced corporate/business environment ', 'Strong communication skills (written and verbal) ', 'Able to manage multiple projects at the same time ', 'A creative and curious approach to solving challenging business problems with data solutions ', 'Experience communicating complex concepts in simple terms to business partners and clients ', 'Data skills:', ' ', ' ', 'Required: ', 'Data modeling ', 'Proficiency with analytics tools and programming languages (SQL, R, Python) and visualization platforms (Tableau, PowerBI, or Webfocus) ', 'Effectively combines multiple large datasets ', 'Identifies and interprets trends and patterns in datasets ', 'Descriptive and inferential statistics ', 'Ability to document their work in a very detailed and organized manner ', 'Strong Microsoft Excel and Power Point skills ', 'Desired: ', 'Interest in product management ', 'Experience in client facing technical role ', 'Familiarity with marketing technology ', ' ', 'Education Qualifications:', ' ', 'Bachelor’s degree in quantitative degree required (e.g., mathematics, statistics, economics, analytics, computer science, etc.) ', "Typically requires a minimum of 2 years of related experience with a Bachelor's degree; or Master's degree", 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Engineering', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services']

Name: Data Analyst Intern
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Dan Connell', 'Dan Connell', 'Talent Acquisition (Software Engineering, Machine Learning & AI) at Adobe', 'Our Company', 'Changing the world through digital experiences is what Adobe’s all about. We give everyone—from emerging artists to global brands—everything they need to design and deliver exceptional digital experiences. We’re passionate about empowering people to craft alluring and powerful images, videos, and apps, and transform how companies interact with customers across every screen.', 'We’re on a mission to hire the very best and are committed to building exceptional employee experiences where everyone is respected and has access to equal opportunity. We realize that new ideas can come from everywhere in the organization, and we know the next big idea could be yours!', 'This Opportunity', "Adobe Experience Platform - Content Services (AEP-CS) builds a shared foundation for Adobe customers' content platform used in Creative Cloud, Document Cloud, and Experience Cloud - enabling consistent experiences, cross-cloud collaboration workflows, and innovative data insights with a goal to accelerated time-to-value. Our content services are delivered as a multi-tenant SaaS storage platform with micro services for identity, access, cache/sync, collaboration, search, and AI to work with the variety of content that our customers deal with (e.g. images, videos, documents, text, web pages, campaigns, blogs, tweets etc.).As member of the AEP-CS PM team you will work with platform product managers and services development engineers to help design, build, evolve and maintain the analytic dashboards needed to enable data-driven product decisions. You will have opportunities to define, measure and track key metrics that guide execution across multiple service teams while building dashboards and reports for teams, business leaders and stakeholders to promote transparency and enable intelligent decisions.", 'What You Will Need To Do', 'Build dashboards and tools that provide insight around key metrics', 'Help drive the strategy and roadmap for data/analytics tools and systems', 'Become the subject matter authority on our data platform, including driving the requirements for our internal event logging systems, data processing engines, experimentation frameworks, and data visualization/dashboard tools.', 'Perform ad hoc analysis and data modeling to understand and predict behavior trends, in order to optimize performance and engagement', 'Partner closely with multi-functional team members including product managers and software engineers to find opportunities and advocate for product improvements and service optimizations', 'Work with Adobe’s data ingestion, data platform and product teams to understand and validate instrumentation and data flow', 'Support regular ad-hoc analysis of large data and metadata sources; interpret and optimally communicate insights and leanings to product, service, and business managers', 'What You’ll Need To Succeed', 'Pursuing degree in Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics or a related field with a graduation date of Spring or Summer 2021', 'Proven technical knowledge in data modeling, system and database design development, and data mining techniques', 'Strong proficiency in querying, manipulating and analyzing large data sets using SQL and/or SQL-like languages.', 'Proficiency in Java or Python', 'Working knowledge of a data visualization tool such as Tableau or Power BI.', 'Strong analytical and problem resolution skills, incl. the ability to research and simplify complex situations', 'Ambitious, strong work ethics and able to work independently with minimal supervision', 'Excellent communicator, both verbal and written', 'At Adobe, you will be immersed in an exceptional work environment that is recognized throughout the world on ', 'Best Companies lists', '. You will also be surrounded by colleagues who are committed to helping each other grow through our unique ', 'Check-In', ' approach where ongoing feedback flows freely.', "If you’re looking to make an impact, Adobe's the place for you. Discover what our employees are saying about their career experiences on the Adobe Life blog and explore the meaningful benefits we offer.", 'Adobe is an equal opportunity employer. We welcome and encourage diversity in the workplace regardless of race, gender, religion, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or veteran status.', 'Seniority level', 'Internship', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software']
