Description: ['Posted by:', 'Lisa Cushing', 'Lisa Cushing', 'Senior Recruiter, Talent Acquisition at Brighthouse Financial', 'Req Id: ', '2665', 'Job location: ', 'Charlotte, NC, US, 28277', "Brighthouse Financial is on a mission to help people achieve financial security. As one of the largest providers of annuities and life insurance in the U.S., we specialize in products designed to help people protect what they've earned and ensure it lasts. We are built on a foundation of experience and knowledge, which allows us to keep our promises and provide the value they deserve. ", "At Brighthouse Financial, we're fostering a culture where diverse backgrounds and experiences are celebrated, and different ideas are heard and respected. We believe that by creating an inclusive workplace, we're better able to attract and retain our talent, provide valuable solutions that meet the needs of our advisors and their clients, and deliver on our mission of helping more people achieve financial security. We're se eking passionate, high-performing team member to join us. Sound like you? Read on. ", ' How This Role Contributes to Brighthouse Financial: ', ' ', ' This role is a critical member of the Underwriting Data & Analytics Team and will be expected to synthesize, cleanse, and analyze large data sets. This role will also collaborate with the Sales, Marketing, Product, and Data teams in order to gather business intelligence, make connections, and glean key insights about data. The person in this position should be able to use his or her judgment to appropriately divide data into significant segments in order to properly communicate out key insights on the life applications submitted, pending and new business written. ', ' Key Responsibilities: ', ' ', ' Support effort to stand up meaningful KPIs for the Life New Business & Underwriting department that follow SMART criteria, with focus on communication as well as repeatable and standardized data collection with well-understood definitions ', ' Support development of repeatable, analytical structure for Data & Analytics Team production reports, focusing on actionable insights that tie in KPI trends ', ' Support model building and maintenance related to underwriting functions ', ' Build and maintain data visualization dashboards for the Life New Business & Underwriting team ', ' Collaborate with underwriting and business partners in support of company initiatives and, under general supervision, perform sensitivity analyses where appropriate to evaluate impact of options/paths ', ' Summarize main actionable insights of data to leaders with clear, concise communication ', ' Essential Business Experience and Technical Skills: ', ' ', ' Degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Actuarial Science, Economics, Finance, Data Science, or other related quantitative field ', " 2+ years' experience in a quantitative/data analytics role, preferably at a life insurance company ", ' Strong Excel required; prior experience with VBA and SQL preferred ', ' Prior experience using Tableau, PowerBI, Adobe Analytics, TrackVia, or other business intelligence tools required ', ' Prior modeling experience (mortality and/or risk-sensitivity) a plus ', ' Strong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills ', ' Knowledge of fluidless and/or accelerated underwriting processes a plus ', ' Positive attitude with an eagerness to learn ', ' Ability to work in a team environment, juggle participation on multiple projects, and resolve conflicting priorities ', 'PI119354229', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Insurance', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Description', 'Job ID: 45192', 'Data Analyst', 'This contractor position is essential to assist with the delivery of a telecommunication services across our client’s enterprise. Description: ['Job Description', 'POSITION TITLE: Operations Research Analyst, Data Analytics, Journeyman', 'LOCATION: Elizabeth City NC', 'Position Description', "The Aviation Logistics Center's (ALC) Business Operations Division's (BOD) (also known as ALC BOD) provides effective costing, logistics and data analysis with stakeholders across acquisition, development, sustainment, and operational environments critical to managing successful acquisition projects within the U.S. Coast Guard. Duties include:', 'Plan and provide analytical support for facilitation, training, methodology development and evaluation, business management techniques, and organizational development.', 'Support USCG and ALC business process improvement and modernization projects.', 'Develop modern business methods, identifying best practices, and creating and assessing performance measurements.', 'Complete data collection, analysis, and experiment report development and preparation.', 'Manage, analyze, and ', 'visualize data using statistical software', ', spreadsheet and graphic presentation software, and develop customized tools.', 'Aid customer with executing decision analysis processes to prioritize events and develop reports.', 'Required Experience', 'Education, Knowledge and Skills Requirements ', 'Three (3) years experience in operations research, or a related field, and a Bachelors Degree in one of the following:', 'Operations Research', 'Industrial Engineering', 'Supply Chain Management', 'Computer Programming', 'Or related fields', 'Working knowledge in at least three (3) of the following disciplines:', 'Supply Chain Management', 'Statistics', 'Operations Research', 'Computer Programming', 'Constraint/Queuing Theory', 'Mathematical Simulation Models', 'Spares Optimization', 'Highly Desired Experience', ' Two (2) years of ', 'V-Metric, PTC Parts/Servigistics', ' software or SAS software experience (or similar applications)', 'Keyword: statistical analysis Pivot', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Other', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Defense & Space', 'Computer Software']

Name: Data Production Analyst
Description: ['As part of the Professional Services team, the Data Production Analyst is responsible for working closely with the customer and internal teams to ensure data integrity within a SaaS environment.', 'This position utilizes skills in data mining, data analysis, and data manipulation against large-scale datasets. You must be able to understand business scenarios, analyze, interpret and communicate findings to all levels of the organization. Additional tasks would include performing data analysis and source-to-target mapping; performing ad-hoc analysis; and validating, structuring and deriving insights from large amounts of data. A drive to learn and master new technologies and techniques. Have a strong track record of applying problem-solving skills, particularly in relation to large data volumes and technical systems. Must have a curious and innovative mind-set, with a determination to understand challenging concepts and find new solutions. Intellectually curious and enjoys problem-solving, requirement gathering, and adaptive to lead with example. Ability to sense check and identify trends or patterns in data. Comfortable taking ownership of tasks and working with limited supervision or instruction in a remote work environment. Thoughtful and comfortable communicator (in person or on paper) with both technical and business stakeholders, with the ability to facilitate discussions. Ability to thrive in a flexible and collaborative environment. A willingness to adapt and learn.', 'Responsibilities', ' Work closely with customer and internal teams to ensure timely completion of project milestones related to data requirements while handling multiple project priorities. ', ' Manipulate data sets ', ' Understanding of business scenarios related to the data ', ' Work diligently to help ensure overall data quality for customer accounts ', ' Assist in resolution of data issues ', ' Ensure accuracy and integrity of data through analysis, coding, writing clear documentation and problem resolution. ', ' Participate in off-hour and weekend support rotation ', ' Experience and understanding of data life cycle: data acquisition, data quality and data management ', ' Strong Analytics knowledge and insight generation ', ' Able to rationally and systematically analyze the raw data, check for anomalies, cleanse and transform into information useful for decision making ', ' Hands-on experience with data aggregation techniques, data ingest/transformation, data analytics, machine learning ', ' Ability to apply, modify, and formulate algorithms and processes to solve challenging problems ', ' Ability to present results in an intuitive, actionable manner that can be understood by sponsor audiences, regardless of technical expertise ', ' Identify data quality issues, root causes, and apply remediation ', ' Strong problem-solving skills. ', ' Communicate with stakeholders to understand current needs, near-term plans, and opportunities for improved data-driven decision support. ', ' Write custom SQL queries to extract data from internal databases. ', ' Write python or perl scripts to structure data into the desired format or to clean/parse data. ', ' Strong knowledge and experience in querying, manipulating and summarizing large amount of data through SQL, in addition to experience in scripting languages such as R or Python ', ' Understanding and related experience in the integration of data from multiple data sources and automation of data processes ', 'Qualifications', ' DESIRED EXPERIENCE ', ' 8+ years experience and proficiency in SQL(Oracle, DB2, SQL Server) ', ' 8+ years experience with scripting/programming languages (Perl, Python, Java, PHP, etc.) ', ' Data mapping experience with ETL tools, EDI, DataStage or MapReduce ', ' Data cleansing experience ', ' Retail systems experience (supply chain, POS, trade funds, etc.) ', ' 1-2 years experience with data warehouse environments or BigData ', ' 5+ years experience and proficiency in SQL(Oracle, DB2, SQL Server) ', ' 5+ years experience with scripting/programming languages (Perl, Python, PHP, Java etc.) ', ' 1-2 years with ETL tools, EDI, DataStage or MapReduce ', ' Analyzing, organizing, cleansing and manipulating large amounts of data ', ' Troubleshooting, problem-solving and decision-making skills ', ' Demonstrated partnering and communication skills ', ' 1 year Linux/Unix with shell scripting ', ' Experience with managing multiple projects simultaneously ', ' 1 year with APIs', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software']

issue documentation and audit reports', 'Contribute to successful completion of the annual plan (integrated, application & IT audits) ', ' Execute concurrent projects while consistently meeting Description: ['Please note that at this point, we are only able to consider candidates in the central Texas area.\xa0 Apologies for the inconvenience!', 'As a result of growth in our analytics, insights & reporting (AIR) practice, we are looking to bring on new associates, offering the opportunity to develop their analytics skills while providing valuable guidance to our clients and client service teams. Description: ['Overview', 'The Orchard is a leading music distribution company operating in over 40 markets worldwide - distributing music from independent artists including Ozuna, Skepta, Jorja Smith, John Prine, and Kelsea Ballerini. At The Orchard, the focus is to provide a comfortable, social and engaging environment to encourage productivity and creativity.', 'The Orchard is hiring a Technical Data Analyst, Analytics to join our New York team.', 'Responsibilities', 'Reporting to the Director, Analytics based in New York, NY, The Orchard has an immediate opening for a full-time Technical Data Analyst, working on data modeling, analytics architecture, and the development of our set of internal BI tools. This person will be responsible for understanding business requirements as communicated by internal stakeholders, translating them into technical solutions, and executing on the work required to accomplish those solutions. Success in this position requires a strong ability to communicate and collaborate within the team and with internal stakeholders across The Orchard.', 'Qualifications', ' 2-4 years experience working as an analyst with a focus on technical solutions', ' SQL Expert', ' Extensive experience with data modeling', ' Familiarity with Python or other scripting language', ' Familiarity with BI tools such as Looker, Tableau, etc', ' Experience using dbt, Jenkins (or other chron scheduling tool), or LookML a plus', 'Responsibilities', ' Liaise with engineering teams to ensure current systems are being leveraged', ' Build upon a set of existing data models to meet internal user needs', ' Understand business needs and facilitate technical solutions that provide efficient and streamlined access for business users', ' Prioritize business requests and accurately scope out the level of effort from a development perspective', ' Organize and maintain existing code base in existing git repository', ' Create systems that allow for analysts to collaborate on code base', ' Provide subject matter expertise in collaboration with the product and engineering teams to provide best in class analytic solutions for our clients.', 'The Ideal Candidate Has', ' A passion for data, especially for creating efficient and scalable models', ' An ability to extract the essence of a business request across various disciplines and translate those needs into a data solution', ' The ability to work independently and effectively communicate successes and roadblocks across various teams', ' Curiosity about unfamiliar data sets, and once they become familiar, new ways to model that data to create self-service analytics solutions', ' Working knowledge of the music industry, and an understanding of the current music consumption landscape', 'About The Orchard', 'The Orchard is a leading music distribution company operating in over 40 markets worldwide. With a comprehensive artist & label services offering including full-service marketing, sync licensing, comprehensive video services, transparent data analysis, advertising, rights management, digital and physical distribution and more, The Orchard empowers creators and businesses to grow and adapt in the dynamic global industry. For further information, visit www.theorchard.com.', 'The Orchard is committed to providing equal employment opportunity for all persons regardless of age, disability, national origin, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity or expression, pregnancy, veteran or military status, marital and civil partnership/union status, alienage or citizenship status, creed, genetic information or any other status protected by applicable federal, state, or local law.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Restaurants']

Name: Senior Data Analyst, YouTube
Description: ['Minimum Qualifications', ' ', "Bachelor's degree in an analytical field or equivalent practical experience. ", ' ', 'Experience analyzing datasets using relational databases including SQL queries, database definition, and schema design.', ' ', 'Preferred Qualifications', ' ', 'Experience with one or more programming languages (e.g., Python, Java, C++, R, etc.).', ' ', 'Experience building ETLs and machine learning pipelines.', ' ', 'About The Job', 'Go-To-Market and Support Solutions (GSS) is a global team working to ensure our users get the most out of YouTube. We provide dedicated and scaled support, strategic go-to-market plan development, partnership resources, product and policy insights based on user feedback, and scaled partnership management to ensure that all partners can thrive within the YouTube ecosystem. We ensure products get to market, support users when they need help and capture user feedback to drive product excellence and market fit.', 'Tier 2 (T2) represents the majority of partners in YouTube’s monetization program, YouTube Partner Program, who do not have access to a partner manager. The mission of the T2 organization is to scalably grow and drive partner satisfaction with YouTube, ensuring a healthy, thriving and happy ecosystem of monetizing partners. This team is responsible for the proactive and reactive scaled managed experience of all T2 partners. This team reports to the GTM & Support Solutions lead.', 'At YouTube, we believe that everyone deserves to have a voice, and that the world is a better place when we listen, share, and build community through our stories. We work together to give everyone the power to share their story, explore what they love, and connect with one another in the process. Working at the intersection of cutting-edge technology and boundless creativity, we move at the speed of culture with a shared goal to show people the world. We explore new ideas, solve real problems, and have fun — and we do it all together.', 'Responsibilities', ' ', 'Make business recommendations (e.g. cost-benefit, forecasting, experiment analysis) using effective presentation skills, conveying findings at multiple levels including executive leadership, managers, and peers through visual displays of quantitative information.', ' ', 'Build and prototype analysis pipelines iteratively to provide insights at scale. ', ' ', 'Conduct non-routine end-to-end analyses, including data gathering from large and complex data sets, processing, analysis employing advanced statistical and ML methods, with ongoing deliverables to improve the quality of YouTube’s scaled offering to Tier 2 partners.', ' ', 'Utilize excellent interpersonal skills to be able to work cross functionally with business leaders, marketing, operations, data science, strategy, and product teams in order to identify opportunities, design, and assess improvements to YouTube’s business.', ' ', "At Google, we don’t just accept difference—we celebrate it, we support it, and we thrive on it for the benefit of our employees, our products and our community. Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing this form .", 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Services', 'Internet']

Name: Lead Data Analyst
Description: ['Description', 'JOIN US AS A LEAD ANALYST – TESTING AND MEASUREMENT', 'About Us', 'Behind one of the world’s best loved brands, is a uniquely capable and brilliant team of data analysts, scientists, product owners and engineers. The Testing and Measurement team drives continuous innovation and business growth through experimentation using testing and measurement philosophy for Target stores, Target.com and Target Mobile. The Testing and Measurement team plays a key role in identifying, testing and measuring the top growth opportunities at any given time. We’re here to help Target improve guest experience, whether guests shop in store, on Target.com or on Target mobile apps.', 'A role with Target’s Testing and Measurement team is a chance to help develop our in-house strength for getting the maximum value from Target’s many data assets. We see data as a product, and as an opportunity to experiment, to refine our approach to new guest experiences. This is how we bring to life what wasn’t possible yesterday, and generate new revenue sources for Target in the process. Our purpose is to accelerate testing across the enterprise to fuel the continuous innovation that we believe is the key to exceeding guest expectations in Target stores, on Target.com and on Target Mobile. Together, we positively impact changes across various initiatives, processes and interdependencies that require exceptional data collection, testing, measurement and analysis — ultimately leading to quicker and more meaningful decision-making at Target.', 'About This Career', 'This requires someone passionate about data, testing, measurement, feature experimentation and its application to improve both business strategies, as well as our in-house testing and measurement solutions', 'You will monitor and analyze data reports/Dashboards/pipelines and do RCA & troubleshooting of issues that arise using prescriptive and predictive analytics.', 'You will work on data sourced from data platforms, tools, algorithm models and extract findings/insights. Can Isolate, Identify and communicate data issues and own data quality for the data produced.', 'You’ll define data to be collected for measuring the success of new testing and measurement product features. Also, provide recommendations based on data analysis to optimize instrumentation and tracking.', 'You will work independently with partners to define problems and create solutions using testing methods, data analysis, data mining, predictive modeling, optimization and machine learning.', 'This requires strong problem-solving skills and working knowledge of query optimization on large data sets.', 'You’ll work with all data and analysis completion in our Hadoop ecosystem.', 'About You', 'BA/BS in a quantitative field Statistics, Mathematics, Compute Science or equivalent work experience', '3+ years of work experience in analytics, consulting, product or data engineering', 'Adept at predictive modeling ', 'Advanced SQL experience writing complex queries ', 'Hands on experience with analytics tools: Hadoop, Hive, Spark, Python, R, Domo and/or equivalent technologies ', 'Able to support conclusions with analytical evidence using descriptive stats, inferential stats and data visualizations ', 'Experience working with Product teams and business leaders to develop product roadmaps and feature development ', 'Intellectually curious, high energy and a strong work ethic ', 'Ability to collaborate well with others to find solutions for complex problems ', 'Extensive problem solving and analytical skills ', 'Exceptional oral and written communication skills ', 'Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)', 'Target will provide reasonable accommodations (such as a qualified sign language interpreter or other personal assistance) with the application process upon your request as required to comply with applicable laws. If you have a disability and require assistance in this application process, please visit your nearest Target store or Distribution Center or reach out to Guest Services at 1-800-440-0680 for additional information.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Retail']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Arlington, VA - Kaimetrix, L.L.C. is seeking a professional ', ' Data Analyst ', ' to support our Federal Government customer, ', ' Defense Travel Management Office (DTMO)', ' .', 'The ', ' Data Analyst ', ' is responsible for a wide range of tasks, from creating data sets, reports, providing data for use by DTMO Business Intelligence tool (Tableau), assisting in data integration, data quality and dashboard development to support performance management.', 'The Following Tasks Are Required', ' Document the organization’s current business process flows ', ' Identify and document functional requirements for information systems ', ' Develop project documentation and user training materials according to program specifications ', ' Produce database development/data extraction using Structured Query Language (SQL) skills to create reporting queries and perform analysis on the database ', ' Assist in data integration using standard techniques ', ' Ensure all products delivered demonstrate expert level technical writing skills, both to document reporting/design requirements and communicate effectively with customers and vendors (e.g. data dictionaries)', ' Analyze and implement data quality improvements (e.g. using DataFlux)', ' Recommend best practices in commercial operational and financial travel data ', ' Apply project management skills to oversee implementation of new data sources and oversee minor projects (systemic data correction, table modification and data population)', ' Support the implementation, expansion and maintenance of a performance management framework aligned to the DTMO strategic plan that cascades, manages, and tracks DoD Travel Enterprise performance. ', ' Provide expert understanding of the principles and methods for evaluating program or organizational performance using financial and nonfinancial measures to include identification of evaluation factors, metrics, and outcomes. ', ' Support the development, implementation and maintenance of strategic and operational performance metrics to assist the government in measuring the effectiveness and efficiency of the DoD Travel Enterprise including key performance indicators (KPIs), performance reports, and dashboards for managers, executive leadership, and other stakeholders to track program performance and assess the overall health of the DoD Travel Enterprise. ', 'Education/Experience', " Bachelor's degree in a related field ", '4+ years of experience as a Data Analyst ', ' Strong experience with SQL to include writing queries ', ' Minimum 1 year experience with DataFlux preferred ', ' Active Secret clearance or higher', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Defense & Space', 'Computer Software']

Name: Investment Data Analyst (SAI)
Description: ['Job Description', 'The Investment Data Analyst will be responsible for providing scaled, easily consumable data for SAI and its business partners. The Analyst will also contribute extensively to the production of Quarterly Reviews (QRs). Name: Data Analyst - Portfolios
Description: ["Bloomberg runs on data, and in the Global Data team we're responsible for acquiring it and providing it to our clients. We collect, analyze, process and publish the data which is the backbone of our iconic Bloomberg Terminal- the facts and figures which ultimately move the financial markets. We apply problem-solving skills to identify innovative workflow efficiencies and we implement technology solutions to enhance our systems, products and processes- and all this while providing platinum customer support to our clients.", 'The Portfolios team in Global Data is responsible for the data management of Mutual Funds and ETF portfolio holdings, as well as public portfolios such as government investment pools, Collateralized Loan Obligation and etc. As a result, the group maintains relationships with market participants to directly source unique, value-added content while leveraging technology to acquire and process publicly available information. Overall, this aggregated, cleansed, and normalized data fuels functions like {HLDR}, {PORT}, supports News, and enables our clients to follow the money flows.', "What's the role?", 'The Portfolios team is looking for a highly motivated individual with a passion for client engagement, research and technology. The team is responsible for procuring, managing and analyzing data for our holdings product, which provides information to the market with point-in-time updates.', "You will be responsible for researching new data sets to expand the coverage of our product, building database schema and configure ETL software to on-board new data sets, designing and analyzing internal processes to identify opportunities for improve efficiency and perform quality control. You'll need to combine of subject-matter-expertise and technical skills to generate premium content such as data-driven news stories and provide customer support for users of Bloomberg products such as the Professional Service, News and Enterprise Solutions by resolving inquiries in a timely manner.", 'We need you to have:', "Bachelor's degree, preferably with combined studies in Information Systems and Finance or related business and STEM field", 'At least two years of relevant work experience', 'Excellent communication and customer service skills and experience in building strong relationships with clients and stakeholders', "Strong understanding of data processing paradigms and associated tools and technologies in Global Data's technology stack", 'Applied proficiency with one or more programming/scripting languages (e.g. Python, R, JavaScript, Java) as well as SQL', 'Effective research skills and excellent attention to detail', 'Knowledge on the Funds and Holdings industry', 'Legal authorization to work full-time in the United States and will not require visa sponsorship now or in the future', "What we'd love to see:", 'Experience working in an Agile development team', 'Experience using statistical and machine learning methods to solve real-world problems', 'Desire to innovate and lead change', 'If this sounds like you:', "Apply! If we think you are a good match, we'll get in touch to let you know the next steps.", 'We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Financial Services', 'Information Services', 'Information Technology and Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Job Title: Data Analyst', 'Department / Company: Customer Service / Amway', 'Location: Ada, MI', "What's Special About This Job", "The Customer Service team is based at our World Headquarters in Ada, Michigan and provides support to our Independent Business Owners (IBO's) in North America. This dedicated and customer focused team is the first contact our IBO's and their customers have to address questions and concerns. In this role you will support the entire Customer Service operation from a data analytics perspective. If you enjoy seeking answers to unasked questions, and discovering hidden trends, this role will take advantage of your curious mind.", 'How You Would Contribute To The Role', "As a Data Analyst for Customer Service, you will analyze data for the entire operation. You will segment and understand who is contacting the department and why, look for trends and potential issues, and create and generate efficiencies for Customer Service. You will partner with Marketing, Sales, IT and Logistics to gather and understand data. You will be seen as a thought leader regarding analytics for the department, keeping abreast of the industry and making sure the team is aware of new tools, software and processes to keep them on the cutting edge of data analytics. This key role will have significant impact on creating a high functioning organization, around data insights and analytics. Your understanding of how to capture and structure data, and passion for the world of analytics will keep this team moving forward, making it easy for IBO's and customers to do business with the company.", 'What skills and background will be important to be successful:', " Minimum 3 years' experience in an analytical role", ' Experience with CMP, or similar CRM tools is preferred', ' Expertise with Tableau, SQL, Alteryx, and/or other data analytics tools', ' Personality to challenge status quo', ' Ability to offer thought leadership and strategic recommendations for improvements', ' Talent to communicate across cultures, with the ability to influence stakeholders', ' Background in lean or Six Sigma is helpful', ' BS degree in Business, Statistics, Mathematics, or a related field', ' This position is not eligible for sponsorship', '* This role is NOT eligible for Sponsorship *', 'If you can see yourself as part of this collaborative environment, visit our web site to apply: www.amway.jobs', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Computer Software', 'Consumer Goods']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Description/Job Summary', 'AgFirst Farm Credit Bank', ' provides financing, as well as a range of technology and other services, to a network of agricultural lenders in the United States and Puerto Rico. Name: Research Data Analyst
Description: ['Department: ', 'MED-Center for Healthcare Studies', 'Salary/Grade: ', 'EXS/7', 'Job Summary', 'The Research Data Analyst will be hired into the Center for Health Services & Outcomes Research , within the Institute for Public Health and Medicine (IPHAM) at Northwestern University.', 'This person will work with an NIH funded team on topics broadly related to bleeding into the brain (intracranial hemorrhage), the most deadly form of stroke. Major research questions include deep learning to automatically extract information (e.g., predicting which patients will get worse or respond to specific treatments), predict complications (e.g., predicting seizures), and improving analytic models. Collaborating investigators include informaticists, neurologists, neurosurgeons, hematologists, and outcomes scientists. This person will work semi-independently to obtain and clean data, perform analyses, and assist in the writing of results. There are opportunities to participate in authorship of manuscripts, new grant applications, and learn new skills.', 'Provides expertise in data management, quality assurance, analysis and reporting. Establishes data accuracy and validity derived from a variety of systems. Performs data analysis using statistical techniques. Researches and analyzes information using multiple databases and creates reports of data and results. Assists in the preparation and delivery of decision support reports to both internal and external customers.', 'Specific Responsibilities', ' Strategic Planning ', ' ', ' Partners with clients to define requirements based on business objectives ', ' Administration ', ' ', ' Designs and prepares documentation for qualitative and quantitative data analysis. ', ' ', ' Discuss findings with senior management. ', ' Development ', ' ', ' Interprets results using a variety of techniques, ranging from simple data aggregation to more complex statistical analysis. ', ' ', ' Manages complex databases. ', ' Performance ', ' ', ' Completes data cleaning and organizes data files for analysis. ', ' ', ' Reviews data and identifies quality issues. ', ' ', ' Presents findings in an appropriate manner. ', ' Supervises ', ' ', ' Provides work direction and/or supervises staff such as team members, students, etc. ', ' Miscellaneous ', ' ', ' Performs other duties as assigned. ', 'Minimum Qualifications', ' ', " Successful completion of a full 4-year course of study in an accredited college or university leading to a bachelor's or higher degree; OR appropriate combination of education and experience. ", ' ', ' 2 years data analysis/report writing or similar experience required. ', ' ', ' Infrastructure (extends across applications)', ' ', ' Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Powerpoint, Access, Outlook) ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' Programming Languages and Frameworks', ' ', ' Python ', ' ', ' R ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' Compliance', ' ', ' HIPAA ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' Analytical', ' ', ' critical thinking ', ' ', ' data mining ', ' ', ' data modeling ', ' ', ' problem solving ', ' ', ' ', ' Minimum Competencies: (Skills, knowledge, and abilities.) ', ' ', ' Two years’ experience in data-intensive research ', ' ', ' Proficiency in R, Python, or similar ', ' ', ' Excellent English oral and written communication ', 'Preferred Qualifications', ' ', ' Master or PhD degree in a quantitative field ', ' Preferred Competencies: (Skills, knowledge, and abilities) ', ' ', ' Experience in completing analysis for an academic lab ', ' ', ' Expertise in processing neuroimaging data (e.g., computed tomography) ', ' ', ' Expertise in natural language processing ', ' ', ' Expertise in machine learning (e.g., scikit-learn in Python, CARET package in R) ', 'Northwestern University is an Equal Opportunity, Affirmative Action Employer of all protected classes, including veterans and individuals with disabilities. Name: Data Analyst, Operations Engineering
Description: ['Invenergy drives innovation in energy. Powered by decades of entrepreneurial experience and unparalleled execution, we solve the energy challenges facing our customers and communities. We are Invenergy.', 'Job Description', ' Invenergy believes inclusion drives innovation ', 'Diverse teams are better teams. The perspectives and experiences that people from different backgrounds bring to an organization drive better decisions and improved business results. Invenergy employees are inclusive and welcoming of all colleagues of all backgrounds, genders, races, sexual orientations, religions and abilities.', 'Position Overview', 'The Data Analyst, Operations Engineering provides technical support to a large operating fleet of renewable energy projects by transforming data into actionable insights & business intelligence, optimizing fleet performance and guiding data-driven decisions.', 'Responsibilities', 'Detect and diagnose performance issues in a large fleet of wind, solar, and energy storage facilities', 'Develop predictive models to detect major equipment problems, preventing down time', 'Evaluate the effect of software changes and parameter modifications on equipment performance', 'Calculate key operating metrics and statistics to measure asset performance', 'Contribute to internal, commercial, and regulatory reporting requirements', 'Collaborate with operations stakeholders to perform investigative analysis', 'Develop architecture & maintain databases of critical wind and solar equipment information', 'Required Skills', 'Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Applied Mathematics, Statistics, Data Science, Computer Science, or related discipline', 'One to three years of work experience', 'Moderate programming/coding experience. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['As a Data Analyst within HealtheIntent Data Analytics, you design analytic solutions and analyze the relationship between data sets and clinical workflows to be consumed for direct insights for internal and external clients. You access and compile data sets from various sources for exploratory and pre-defined analyses; audit data sets for completeness, validity, and other pertinent data health measures; and support evaluation of data sets for analytical possibilities and pitfalls. You also work with clients on technology, process, and training to enhance their analytical capabilities while focusing on the relationship between analytics and driving clinical and financial health care improvements. Finally, you will be responsible for communicating complex findings to non-technical internal and external clients.', 'Qualifications', ' Basic Qualifications ', ' Bachelor’s Degree in Information Systems, Management Information Systems, Mathematics, Statistics, Actuarial Science, Analytics, or related field, or equivalent relevant work experience ', ' At least 1 year of data analysis work experience including data management, transformation and visualization, or successful completion of Cerner’s Analytics Learning Lab ', 'Preferred Qualifications', ' At least 1 year experience with SQL and Tableau ', ' Expectations ', ' Willing to travel up to 20% as needed ', ' Must currently reside in or be willing to relocate to the Kansas City Metropolitan area ', 'Additional Information', 'Applicants for U.S. based positions with Cerner Corporation must be legally authorized to work in the United States. Verification of employment eligibility will be required at the time of hire. Visa sponsorship is not available for this position.', 'Some Cerner positions may be obligated to comply with client-facing requirements and occupational health requests, including but not limited to, an immunization set, an annual flu shot, an annual TB screen, an updated background check, and/or an updated drug screen.', 'Relocation Assistance Available', 'No', 'Company Overview', 'Cerner is a place where people are encouraged to innovate with confidence and focus on what is important – people’s health and the care they receive. We are transforming health care by developing tools and technologies that make it more efficient for care providers and patients to navigate the complexity of our health. From single offices to entire countries, Cerner solutions are licensed at more than 25,000 facilities in over 35 countries.', 'Cerner’s policy is to provide equal opportunity to all people without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ancestry, marital status, veteran status, age, disability, pregnancy, genetic information, citizenship status, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other legally protected category. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Kristen Jeena, MBA', 'Kristen Jeena, MBA', 'Senior Global Recruitment Manager at Care.com', 'Care.com is a consumer tech company with heart. We’re on a mission to solve a human challenge we all face: finding great care for the ones we love. We’re moms and dads and pet parents. We have parents and grandparents so we understand that everyone, at some point in their lives, could use a helping hand. Our culture\xa0and our products\xa0reflect that.\xa0', '\xa0Here, entrepreneurs, self-starters, team players,\xa0and big thinkers unite behind a common cause. Here, we’re applying data analytics, AI and the latest technologies to solve universal problems and connect people in new ways. If you like having autonomy, if you thrive on collaboration and building new things, and if you’re all about using your talent for good, Care.com is the place for you.\xa0\xa0', 'What Your Days Will be Like:\xa0', '\xa0', 'The Data Analyst will be part of our centralized Analytics team at Care.com, which serves multiple departments and business units for their analytical and business intelligence needs. The Analytics team works closely with business and technical teams, overseeing data structures and quality while also ensuring that data is properly leveraged to inform business decisions.', 'The Data Analyst will work with various departments across Care.com to understand their analytical questions, then collect, manipulate, and analyze data from different sources using a variety of techniques - ranging from simple data aggregation to complex data mining. S/he will interpret & present analytical results to different business stakeholders.', 'The ideal candidate will have 4 years of professional experience\xa0as a Data Analyst and a degree in a quantitative field. S/he will enjoy working with data, demonstrate strong business judgment and be able to prioritize in a fast-paced environment.', 'What You’ll be Working on:\xa0\xa0', 'Support the business on general analysis and strategic projects; meet with stakeholders to understand analytical needs and define metrics/KPIs/reports', 'Ensure on-time & accurate delivery of regular KPIs, reports and forecasts', 'Perform data analysis on user behavior to inform product features', 'Maintain deep and up-to-date knowledge of the data warehouse; troubleshoot data inconsistencies', 'Translate business needs into analytical tasks, documenting & presenting results', 'Build and maintain dashboards to track product usage and performance', 'Interpret results using a variety of techniques, ranging from simple exploratory data analysis to statistical modeling', 'Demonstrate a level of independence in driving analysis', 'What You’ll Need to Succeed:\xa0', 'A minimum of 4 years of professional work experience outside of academic schooling', 'Analytically oriented with ability to interpret trends and correlations', 'Strong knowledge of database & data warehousing concepts', 'Experience writing complex SQL queries', 'Knowledge of A/B testing and statistical principles (e.g. regression)\xa0', 'Experience with R, Python, or related programming language', 'Microsoft Excel proficiency, including pivot tables, look up functions and charts', 'Experience with Tableau or other reporting/BI tools', '\ufeff', '**Care.com supports diverse\xa0families and communities and seeks employees who are just as diverse. As an equal opportunity employer, Care.com recognizes the power of a diverse workforce and encourages applications from individuals with varied experiences, perspectives, and\xa0backgrounds.**', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Analyst', 'Industries', 'Internet']

Name: Marketing Data Analyst
Description: ['Marketing Data Analyst', 'Marketing | US - San Francisco Office', 'About The Company', 'In today’s highly connected digital world, understanding, managing and securing the identity of individuals and things is essential to safety and success of both businesses and their customers. Billions of people connect from anywhere, use a wide variety of devices and expect a seamless yet secure experience.', 'The ForgeRock mission is to provide the most simple and comprehensive Identity and Access Management Platform to help our customers deepen their relationships with their consumers and improve the productivity and connectivity of their employees and partners. Our identity solution enables great digital experiences and is embedded with a rich set of security, privacy and consent features. We deliver our platform through both cloud services and on-premises software.', 'Our customers are some of the biggest companies, organizations, and even countries in the world. On any given day, it’s likely that the ForgeRock Identity Platform helped keep your data safe, gave you access to stuff, and supported trusted relationships between you, companies and the devices you were using.', 'ForgeRock is headquartered in San Francisco, but we are a global company with offices in the following cities: Vancouver, WA; Austin, TX; Munich, Germany; London & Bristol, UK; Grenoble & Paris, FR; Oslo, NO; Singapore and Sydney, Australia. Please read more about us at forgerock.com or follow ForgeRock on Twitter at http://www.twitter.com/forgerock.', 'The Role', 'In this role, you will be the go-to-person for all things related to marketing reporting and analytics for our global marketing team. You will need to have high proficiency in Salesforce reporting and dashboards. Also, you will need expertise in advanced Excel features that enables to combine different data sources and create insights.', 'This will be a full-time permanent role based in our headquarters in San Francisco.', 'Responsibilities', ' ', 'Create and update reports and dashboards in Salesforce', ' ', 'Partner with Digital Marketing and other marketing teams to provide the insights they need to optimize marketing campaigns.', ' ', 'Create ad-hoc operational reports for marketing stakeholders', ' ', 'Perform deep dive into data to find causes and patterns', ' ', 'Identify opportunities to optimize results in all aspects of Marketing functions through analytics', ' ', 'Required Skills & Qualifications', ' ', 'Expertise in using Excel to combine data, creating pivots, and producing charts.', ' ', 'Experience in digital advertising analytics - especially PPC and display ads', ' ', 'Experience in Salesforce reporting and dashboards', ' ', 'Knowledge of Salesforce revenue funnel framework', ' ', 'Ability to collaborate with multiple stakeholders', ' ', '2+ years of relevant experience', ' ', 'Undergraduate degree in a quantitative discipline with a high GPA', ' ', 'Life At ForgeRock', 'We believe in and facilitate a flexible, collaborative work environment. We’ve grown enormously, but remain true to the innovative, can-do startup values that got us here. Most important of all, we keep hiring talented, smart, fun, and genuinely nice people because that’s who we want to succeed with every day. Below are just a few of the great things we have to offer at ForgeRock:', ' ', 'A great team of smart, fun and genuinely nice individuals.', ' ', 'Awesome company culture focused around providing a flexible and collaborative work environment', ' ', 'Regular office bonding events, from lunches and happy hours to group offsites and hack-days', ' ', 'Well-stocked fridges, whether you’re hungry or thirsty', ' ', 'Competitive benefits and perks', ' ', 'We’re Mac-friendly!', ' ', 'Generous employee referral bonus program', ' ', 'Amazing offices across the globe – San Francisco HQ; Vancouver, WA; Austin, TX; Munich, Germany; London & Bristol, UK; Grenoble & Paris, FR; Oslo, NO; Singapore, Australia & counting!', ' ', 'ForgeRock is the collective sum of all our individual experiences, backgrounds and influences and we pride ourselves in growing and learning together. We are committed to building an inclusive and diverse environment where everyone’s individuality is respected and everyone has an Identity. In recruiting for new colleagues, we welcome the unique contributions you can bring and encourage you to be your best self.', 'We are an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex including sexual orientation and gender identity, national origin, disability, protected Veteran Status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable federal, state, or local law.', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Marketing', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Data Analyst
Company: Midland Credit Management, an Encore Capital Group Company
Description: ['Here at MCM, we recognize and value success: for our consumers, for our communities, for you as an individual, and for us as a team. We support your career aspirations and provide the benefits you need to live the fulfilling life you want. You make a difference for us through your attitude and achievements and we will always strive to make a difference for you. Be part of MCM’s amazing journey, where your success is valued!', 'The Data Analyst is primarily responsible for managing department databases for the Inventory Management department and ensuring data quality is achieved and maintained. This includes establishing processes to monitor data quality and resolve any irregularities by assessing impacts, alerting stakeholders and driving progress toward resolution. The Data Analyst works with business stakeholders to help define user requirements, test and implement new systems and processes to support business needs. This person also develops and runs analyses, tools and ad-hoc reports to support business needs and opportunities. The role works closely with teams across multiple geographies across the globe. The Data Analyst will use tools such as SAS, SQL Server, Excel as well as source systems and best practices to accomplish these objectives. The person will also document best practices and add to and maintain a resource library for analyst teams.', 'Responsibilities', 'Write SQL and SAS code to implement technical solutions to execute business strategy / processes.', 'Develop and maintain the monitoring of reports and analytical tools to ensure accuracy, identify trends / issues / opportunities.', 'Perform ad hoc data extraction, analyses and segmentations as required.', 'Work with IT to test new data repositories to support the business.', 'Skills & Experience', 'Required Qualification(s):', 'Bachelor', 'Quantitative field (Economics preferred)', 'Strong desire to design and develop data processes and reports to support business initiatives.', 'Appropriately communicate technical concepts with people of varying degrees of technical understanding.', 'Basic understanding of databases, SQL, data mining techniques', 'Eager desire to learn data management concepts and terminology including data warehouse concepts', 'Proficiency with MS Office (Excel, PowerPoint)', 'Position Status', 'Full time', 'Established in 1953, Midland Credit Management, Inc. (MCM), a wholly-owned subsidiary of Encore Capital Group, Inc ., is a specialty finance company providing debt recovery solutions for consumers across a broad range of assets. We are the market leader in portfolio purchasing and recovery in the United States, and we lead the industry with consumer-centric practices that drive results. We have operations in India, Costa Rica, and 35 US Sites.', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Union is a digital-first agency that partners with ambitious and progressively-minded clients to deliver powerful digital brand experiences. Our work – whether it’s a fully-enabled corporate platform, branded connected-device experience, playful touchscreen kiosk, edgy product microsite or a tightly-woven client acquisition campaign – always combines results-driven enterprise-level strategy, industry insights research, award-winning design, rich-media content and leading-edge technology.', "We’ve worked hard to establish an open, collaborative and creative agency environment over the past decade, and we are continuing to grow. Candidates should have 2+ years of industry experience and have Adobe Analytics experience. Candidates should be authorized to work in the U.S. at this time.", 'This person will be responsible for using online Analytics tools to pull data, using critical and analytical thinking to uncover valuable insights and recommendations. This person will be collaborating with team members to create reports and to provide proactive insights and recommendations to internal stakeholders and clients. They will be responsible for providing the exploration and analysis needed to determine the best digital strategies.', 'Requirements', "What we're looking for", ' ', 'Keen understanding of how the digital medium is consumed by the general population', ' ', 'Up-to-date knowledge of current digital marketing trends', ' ', 'Excellent interpersonal and communication skills', ' ', 'Deep experience and certified with Google Analytics', ' ', 'Deep experience with Adobe Analytics/Site Catalyst', ' ', 'Experience with other Analytics platforms and best practices', ' ', 'Experience with leveraging Analytics tools to improve site performance and/or digital marketing initiatives', ' ', 'Self-motivated people with the ability to juggle multiple projects', ' ', 'Ability to work effectively within a team to develop marketing solutions that emerge from a strategic foundation', ' ', 'Meticulous attention to detail and overall product quality', ' ', 'Confidence in presenting work and ability to interact comfortably with the team and clients', ' ', 'Ability to conceive and develop solutions individually as well as in a collaborative environment', ' ', 'Commitment not to just fulfilling an assignment, but in adding value, pushing the boundaries and creating work that makes a difference', ' ', 'Team player (those great personality types that people love to work with)', ' ', 'Benefits', ' ', 'Tight Knit Team', ' ', 'Inspiring Work', ' ', 'Matching 401K', ' ', 'Third Thursdays', ' ', 'Paid Time Off', ' ', 'Profit Sharing', ' ', 'Studiodays', ' ', 'Health Benefits', ' ', 'Professional Development', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Contract', 'Job function', 'Analyst', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Online Media', 'Internet']

Name: Business / Data Analyst
Description: ["As a member of our Business Analysis team, you'll play a crucial role in identifying, improving and developing technology solutions that drive our strategic goals. This is a tremendous opportunity to learn about high-priority initiatives and collaborate with colleagues throughout the firm. Working at the intersection of business and technology, you'll sharpen your understanding of business processes and data analysis, while continuing to develop your leadership, management and communication skills. No matter where your career ultimately takes you, you'll make a meaningful impact and lasting connections with outstanding colleagues and mentors.", 'This role requires a wide variety of strengths and capabilities, including:', 'BS/BA degree or equivalent experience', 'Active experience writing and executing complex SQL queries against very large Oracle databases', 'Experience or knowledge with Big Data Technologies is a plus', 'Experience with Data Analysis using Python or a like-language with the ability to quickly learn Python', 'Strong understanding of data from both a Business and Technical perspective (data relationships, etc.)', 'Experience with test planning and test execution', 'Strong organizational and analysis skills (including root-cause analysis)', 'Strong communication skills (written and verbal) are required', 'Proven ability to work collaboratively and develop meaningful relationships across lines of business, a wide range of stakeholders, and development teams to achieve common goals', 'Experience with Domain Driven Design and Domain Modeling is a plus ', 'Financial Services experience using Customer/Account and Transaction data and/or Anti-Money Laundering (AML) experience is desired, but not required', 'Our Corporate Technology team relies on smart, driven people like you to develop applications and provide tech support for all our corporate functions across our network. Your efforts will touch lives all over the financial spectrum and across all our divisions: Global Finance, Corporate Treasury, Risk Management, Human Resources, Compliance, Legal, and within the Corporate Administrative Office. You’ll be part of a team specifically built to meet and exceed our evolving technology needs, as well as our technology controls agenda.', 'When you work at JPMorgan Chase & Co., you’re not just working at a global financial institution. You’re an integral part of one of the world’s biggest tech companies. In 20 technology centers worldwide, our team of 50,000 technologists design, build and deploy everything from enterprise technology initiatives to big data and mobile solutions, as well as innovations in electronic payments, cybersecurity, machine learning, and cloud development. Our $10B+ annual investment in technology enables us to hire people to create innovative solutions that will are transforming the financial services industry.', 'At JPMorgan Chase & Co. we value the unique skills of every employee, and we’re building a technology organization that thrives on diversity. We encourage professional growth and career development, and offer competitive benefits and compensation. If you’re looking to build your career as part of a global technology team tackling big challenges that impact the lives of people and companies all around the world, we want to meet you.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['About Us', 'We were founded in 2015 by entrepreneurs who saw the opportunity to reinvent the $100 billion small business insurance industry by using data, design, and technology. Today CoverWallet is the easiest way for businesses to understand, buy, and manage insurance online, and we have grown to more than 300 employees around the world. CoverWallet is one of the fastest-growing InsurTech companies and was named one of the promising startups for the CNBC Upstart 100 in 2018, won the 2017 Best Insurtech Solution from the Benzinga Awards and was named “One of the Most Entrepreneurial Companies in America” by Entrepreneur Magazine.', 'Job Summary', 'The Data Analyst will be responsible for building robust analytical platforms to support data-driven initiatives across the company. In this role, you will deliver strategic analysis on high priority initiatives across the entire organization. You will be working closely with Product, Marketing, Sales, and Operations in providing them with visibility to real-time data. You will be expected to deliver data-driven insights that will play an integral role in defining the company’s data model and improving our ETL processes.', 'You will receive a competitive salary and work in a highly collaborative environment. We are a fast-paced, growing firm that is the perfect place for a goal-oriented, hardworking individual who is looking to make a difference. We expect massive growth over the next few years, which means you can expect plenty of opportunities for advancement.', 'Essential Job Functions', ' ', 'Present data-driven insights to the executive team that impact the strategic direction of the company.', ' ', 'Work cross-functionally with Product, Sales, Operations, and Marketing to provide them with visibility to real-time data on existing and new processes. ', ' ', 'Define the data model that captures the key drivers of the value of our business processes and makes it easy to analyze and combine different data sources.', ' ', 'Develop operating models to help executive leadership gain a better understanding of the key revenue drivers.', ' ', 'Collaborate with the Data Engineering team to develop automated tests that monitor our data ingestion process.', ' ', 'Education', 'Qualifications:', ' ', '1-3 years of experience in an analytics role.', ' ', 'Bachelor’s Degree in a quantitative field.', ' ', 'Technical', ' ', 'Highly proficient in SQL.', ' ', 'Experience using visualization tools, preferably Looker, Tableau, or Power BI.', ' ', 'Experience working in Agile environments, preferably with Jira and Asana.', ' ', 'Extra Credit - Exposure to data modeling and transformation tools like dbt.', ' ', 'Extra Credit - Working experience with data analysis and building data pipelines with Python. ', ' ', 'Professional', ' ', 'Strong written and verbal communication skills.', ' ', 'Problem solver with excellent analytical skills.', ' ', 'Ability to work in a fast-paced environment.', ' ', 'Comfortable working on multiple projects simultaneously.', ' ', 'Strong quantitative reasoning skills and experience using data to provide insights to executive leadership and other departments. ', ' ', 'CoverWallet is an Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, or other applicable legally protected characteristics', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Computer Software', 'Insurance', 'Financial Services']

Name: Business Data Analyst
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ["Hi, we're Oscar. We’re hiring a Business Data Analyst to join our Risk Adjustment team in our New York office.", 'Oscar is a technology-driven, consumer-focused health insurance startup founded in 2012 and headquartered in New York City. Our goal is to make health insurance simple, transparent, and human. We need your help to do so.', 'About The Role', 'In this role, you will assist in key operations for a core Oscar insurance function called Value Capture. Under the Value Capture umbrella exists Risk Adjustment and Quality which are the only operations that can affect Oscar’s bottom line after we’ve set premium rates. You’ll build and refine workflows, tracking progress to meet critical CMS deadlines. You’ll help manage data for health systems, vendor partners, and internal stakeholders. You’ll identify inefficiencies and recommend tactical program improvements. This position requires you to be data and operationally savvy.', 'Your role will be focused on supporting core value capture operations. You’ll work cross functionally with the Network, Data, Actuarial, and Population health teams on both medical record retrieval and member engagement. From analyzing provider data and abstracting patient information from a medical record to optimizing member outreach, you’ll be a key partner in delivering actionable insights.', 'You will report into the Senior Manager, Risk Adjustment.', 'Responsibilities', ' ', 'You’ll build dashboards to monitor progress of Value Capture programs and escalate issues with key stakeholders.', ' ', 'You’ll design and operationalize member engagement campaigns and monitor their success', ' ', 'You’ll triage chart retrieval issues from vendors and build tools/workflows to assist in obtaining charts.', ' ', 'You’ll review current retrieval processes and audit procedures to get ready for Risk Adjustment Data Validation (RADV).', ' ', 'You’ll report on RA and Quality programs to other areas of the organization, both financial and operational in nature.', ' ', 'You’ll assist, on an ongoing basis, the development of policies and procedures for Value Capture programs under the Affordable Care Act and Medicare.', ' ', 'You’ll think creatively about what’s possible for Value Capture programs and Oscar’s analytics and reporting tools/infrastructure. ', ' ', 'Requirements', ' ', '2+ Years experience working in SQL ', ' ', 'BA/BS Degree ', ' ', 'Use data analysis to come up with creative solutions to complex problems and produce tangible results', ' ', 'Enjoy experimenting and iterating on ways to solve a problem and building programs from the ground up ', ' ', 'Be able to put together a project plan and work throughout the company to hold teams accountable and drive results', ' ', 'A passion for understanding complex issues with a data driven approach', ' ', 'Bonus Points', ' ', 'Background in healthcare, tech or risk adjustment', ' ', 'Knowledge of RA or Quality measures ', ' ', 'Life At Oscar', "At Oscar, being an Equal Opportunity Employer means more than upholding discrimination-free hiring practices. It means that we cultivate an environment where people can be their most authentic selves and find both belonging and support. We're on a mission to change health care -- an experience made whole by our unique backgrounds and perspectives.", 'We encourage our members to care for their whole selves, and we encourage our employees to do the same with comprehensive medical benefits, generous paid-time off, paid parental leave, retirement plans, company social events, stocked kitchens, wellness programs, and volunteer opportunities.', 'Reasonable Accommodation', 'Oscar applicants are considered solely based on their qualifications, without regard to applicant’s disability or need for accommodation. Name: Senior Data Science Analyst
Description: ['The Company', "At Adobe, we’re changing the world. How? We give people the tools to bring their ideas to life and create content that makes life more fun and work more substantial. We give businesses and organizations the power to truly engage their customers. We're the ones behind the alluringly designed content that streams across your laptop, TV, phone, and tablet every day — and we’re the ones who harness the massive power of big data to help companies move from data to insight and insight to action by delivering content that people crave most.", 'The Opportunity ', 'This is a high impact, highly visible role well suited to individuals with a highly quantitative, inquisitive bent of mind. The ideal candidate will be able to work autonomously and will have a technical background with strong communication and project management skills.', 'As a Product Analyst you will be responsible for helping different businesses and teams achieve operational and execution efficiencies using data. Your leadership and interpersonal skills will allow you to engage with product management, customer success, marketing, and sales teams to understand and distill their business intelligence needs and deficiencies. Your strong data ETL skills will help you combine disparate sources of data so that they can be analyzed and your understanding of statistics will help in analyzing the data, providing useful actionable insights for the various teams. Your success is predicated on providing insights that enable digital marketing businesses to lower customer churn, identify product feature utilization, and facilitate upsell and cross sell opportunities.', 'What You’ll Do', 'Manage the data collection, analysis, and delivery of critical metrics for a digital marketing business', 'Collaborate with technical teams to gain insight to where data is stored and how it can be extracted', 'Analyze customer usage data and derive insights for product, customer success, and marketing teams', 'Standardize insight generation and help build automated self-service tools for the same', 'Own and lead relationships with stakeholders across digital marketing businesses', 'Mentor junior team members by providing constructive mentorship', 'What You Need To Succeed', '3 - 5 years relevant experience', 'Degree in engineering, statistics, mathematics or related disciplines are strongly preferred. MS/PhDs are preferred', 'Basic prototyping skills in R, Python, Spark or similar language are required', 'Ability and preference to work in a rapidly changing and less defined business environment', 'Very strong project management skills are required. The ability to work with disparate teams, often in different geos, prioritize tasks and following up on them is critical for success in this role', 'Experience with machine learning, artificial intelligence, and/or econometrics is strongly preferred', 'Knowledge of the digital marketing industry preferred but not required', 'At Adobe, you will be immersed in an exceptional work environment that is recognized throughout the world on ', 'Best Companies lists', '. You will also be surrounded by colleagues who are committed to helping each other grow through our unique ', 'Check-In', ' approach where ongoing feedback flows freely.', "If you’re looking to make an impact, Adobe's the place for you. Discover what our employees are saying about their career experiences on the Adobe Life blog and explore the meaningful benefits we offer.", 'Adobe is an equal opportunity employer. We welcome and encourage diversity in the workplace regardless of race, gender, religion, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or veteran status.', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software']

Name: Marketing Data Analyst
Description: ['Marketing Data Analyst', 'Marketing | US - San Francisco Office', 'About The Company', 'In today’s highly connected digital world, understanding, managing and securing the identity of individuals and things is essential to safety and success of both businesses and their customers. Billions of people connect from anywhere, use a wide variety of devices and expect a seamless yet secure experience.', 'The ForgeRock mission is to provide the most simple and comprehensive Identity and Access Management Platform to help our customers deepen their relationships with their consumers and improve the productivity and connectivity of their employees and partners. Our identity solution enables great digital experiences and is embedded with a rich set of security, privacy and consent features. We deliver our platform through both cloud services and on-premises software.', 'Our customers are some of the biggest companies, organizations, and even countries in the world. On any given day, it’s likely that the ForgeRock Identity Platform helped keep your data safe, gave you access to stuff, and supported trusted relationships between you, companies and the devices you were using.', 'ForgeRock is headquartered in San Francisco, but we are a global company with offices in the following cities: Vancouver, WA; Austin, TX; Munich, Germany; London & Bristol, UK; Grenoble & Paris, FR; Oslo, NO; Singapore and Sydney, Australia. Please read more about us at forgerock.com or follow ForgeRock on Twitter at http://www.twitter.com/forgerock.', 'The Role', 'In this role, you will be the go-to-person for all things related to marketing reporting and analytics for our global marketing team. You will need to have high proficiency in Salesforce reporting and dashboards. Also, you will need expertise in advanced Excel features that enables to combine different data sources and create insights.', 'This will be a full-time permanent role based in our headquarters in San Francisco.', 'Responsibilities', ' ', 'Create and update reports and dashboards in Salesforce', ' ', 'Partner with Digital Marketing and other marketing teams to provide the insights they need to optimize marketing campaigns.', ' ', 'Create ad-hoc operational reports for marketing stakeholders', ' ', 'Perform deep dive into data to find causes and patterns', ' ', 'Identify opportunities to optimize results in all aspects of Marketing functions through analytics', ' ', 'Required Skills & Qualifications', ' ', 'Expertise in using Excel to combine data, creating pivots, and producing charts.', ' ', 'Experience in digital advertising analytics - especially PPC and display ads', ' ', 'Experience in Salesforce reporting and dashboards', ' ', 'Knowledge of Salesforce revenue funnel framework', ' ', 'Ability to collaborate with multiple stakeholders', ' ', '2+ years of relevant experience', ' ', 'Undergraduate degree in a quantitative discipline with a high GPA', ' ', 'Life At ForgeRock', 'We believe in and facilitate a flexible, collaborative work environment. We’ve grown enormously, but remain true to the innovative, can-do startup values that got us here. Most important of all, we keep hiring talented, smart, fun, and genuinely nice people because that’s who we want to succeed with every day. Below are just a few of the great things we have to offer at ForgeRock:', ' ', 'A great team of smart, fun and genuinely nice individuals.', ' ', 'Awesome company culture focused around providing a flexible and collaborative work environment', ' ', 'Regular office bonding events, from lunches and happy hours to group offsites and hack-days', ' ', 'Well-stocked fridges, whether you’re hungry or thirsty', ' ', 'Competitive benefits and perks', ' ', 'We’re Mac-friendly!', ' ', 'Generous employee referral bonus program', ' ', 'Amazing offices across the globe – San Francisco HQ; Vancouver, WA; Austin, TX; Munich, Germany; London & Bristol, UK; Grenoble & Paris, FR; Oslo, NO; Singapore, Australia & counting!', ' ', 'ForgeRock is the collective sum of all our individual experiences, backgrounds and influences and we pride ourselves in growing and learning together. We are committed to building an inclusive and diverse environment where everyone’s individuality is respected and everyone has an Identity. In recruiting for new colleagues, we welcome the unique contributions you can bring and encourage you to be your best self.', 'We are an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex including sexual orientation and gender identity, national origin, disability, protected Veteran Status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable federal, state, or local law.', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Marketing', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Reporting Data Analyst
Description: ['Reporting Data Analyst', 'El Segundo', 'Position Overview', 'Apollo Insurance Solutions Group seeks an Investment Reporting Analyst for its El Segundo, CA-based headquarters.
