Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['What makes conversations great? Is it the balance of leading and listening, inferred by talk/listen ratios and word reuse between parties? Are all interruptions created equal? Do you close sales deals faster by setting action items in the call? If tackling these questions with data on our AI Research team fascinates you, please read on!', 'Who We Are', "At Dialpad, we're a team of doers. Founded by the creators of Google Voice, our team focuses on personal excellence, high-quality execution and building best-in-class software. We like to think outside the box... and when that doesn't work, we reinvent it. We don't settle for the status quo, and that's reflected in everything we build.", "With $120 million in funding from ICONIQ Capital, Google Ventures, Andreessen Horowitz, Scale Ventures and other top VC's, Dialpad attracts top talent from iconic companies like Microsoft and Google as well as powerhouse startups like Hootsuite, Weebly and Anaplan. Every member of our team plays an essential role in creating dynamic products that combine design and mobility-- while also working with you whenever productivity strikes.", 'About The Role', 'The AI Research team is currently dedicated to the question: "What makes great sales conversations?" Our proprietary dataset of audio, call transcripts and conversation outcomes positions us to surface never-seen-before insights in this fascinating question. We are looking for a Data Analyst who will join and support the AI Research team by making data easily accessible and by testing hypotheses on data. The ideal person has excellent critical thinking skills, great attention to detail, and a strong sense of initiative, collaboration and helpfulness.', "The work is a mix of database administration, data analysis, business intelligence and hypothesis testing. Ideally, you have experience running SQL queries on large data sets, are curious about what makes great conversations, have some knowledge of machine learning practices and data requirements and are comfortable operating in an agile environment. If you're inspired by innovation and you like working with a smart, talented, generally awesome team, we'd love to hear from you!", 'Responsibilities', ' ', 'Acquire and clean data sets to support AI Research experiments', ' ', 'Streamline access to data and simplify query logic by building views', ' ', 'Ability and desire to understand the point of view of key stakeholders, including the AI Research team and our end users. Includes participating in some customer interviews and learning about sales/support workflows. ', ' ', 'Test hypotheses with data', ' ', 'Given a use-case be able to recommend and source the required data independently', ' ', 'Requirements', ' ', '1+ years experience as a data analyst or similar quantitative role. ', ' ', 'Excellent organizational, analytical, and research skills', ' ', 'Excellent communicator and listener', ' ', 'Curiosity about what makes great conversations', ' ', 'Strong sense of initiative, collaboration and helpfulness', ' ', 'Flexible with regards to changing priorities & business needs', ' ', 'Proficient in SQL', ' ', 'Experience with Python', ' ', 'Bonus points for', ' ', 'Coursework in Statistics ', ' ', 'Background in communication, biological sciences, computational linguistics or dealing with human data', ' ', 'Experience with B2B sales and support workflows', ' ', 'About Us', "Joining our team means collaborating with people that aren't just passionate about their work but about Argentine tango, musicals, sushi burritos, comic books - you name it. Because if you're going to redefine the status quo, you need a group of people hungry to do more, to see more, and be more than where they started.", "There is no idea too crazy and no task too small — we work together to make things we're proud of.", 'Compensation & Equity', "Teamwork makes the dream work. We recognize that our dedicated team members are what make our success. That's why we offer competitive salaries in addition to stock options.", 'Healthcare', "An apple a day keeps the doctor away - and it doesn't hurt that we offer 100% paid medical, dental, and vision plans for all employees.", 'Reimbursements', 'We offer a monthly stipend to help cover your cell phone, home internet, and even gym membership costs.', 'Education', "We believe in your future as much as you do! That's why we offer a yearly stipend for continued learning and education expenses.", 'Office Meals', 'Bon Appetit! Enjoy catered lunches, free snacks & drinks (both healthy and unhealthy - no judgment!)', 'Location, Location, Location', 'San Francisco <> San Ramon <> Austin <> Raleigh <> Vancouver <> Kitchener <> Tokyo <> New York <> Bangalore. From coast to coast, our offices are nestled in active and growing downtown areas', 'Dialpad is an equal opportunity employer; we believe in creating a community of inclusion and an environment free from discrimination or harassment.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Senior Data Analyst
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['At Rockstar Games, we create the games we would want to play ourselves.', 'A career at Rockstar is about being part of a team working on some of the most creatively rewarding, large-scale projects to be found in any entertainment medium. You would be welcomed to a friendly, inclusive environment where you can learn, and collaborate with some of the most talented people in the industry.', 'Rockstar New York is seeking an experienced data analyst to join our growing Analytics practice and help build Rockstar’s business intelligence capacity. Successful candidates will work with analytics and product leadership to assure that the most relevant possible real-time and historical data is identified, tracked, analyzed, and made actionable across all of our titles. This is a full-time permanent position based out of Rockstar’s unique game development studio in the heart of downtown Manhattan.', 'What We Do', 'The Rockstar Analytics team provide insights and actionable results to a wide variety of stakeholders across the organization in support of their decision making.', 'We work together with a number of departments to design and implement data and pipelines.', 'We collaborate as a global team to develop cutting-edge data pipelines, data products, data models, reports, analyses and machine learning applications.', 'Responsibilities', 'Partner with analysts and live producers to identify strategic business questions, key metrics, and actionable insights.', 'Provide consumer-ready recommendations, insights and reporting to Analytics team leadership, live producers, product managers and partner groups.', 'Effectively translate statistical findings into actionable recommendations for senior leaders on game and business teams.', 'Research and develop state-of-the-art data mining and statistical modeling solutions to understand game design, system performance and key business behaviors, such as player engagement.', 'Drive needle moving improvements via hands-on exploration of data, dashboards, statistical analysis and predictive modeling.', 'Combine qualitative and quantitative driven insights with game knowledge to recommend potential avenues to the game and business teams.', 'Drive requirements for data collection and for data modeling with data engineers', 'Work within a team of data analysts and engineers.', 'Qualifications', '5+ years in a similar position or an analytics role in the marketing, finance, forensics, or technology fields.', 'Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field (Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Operational Research, Business Intelligence or any other relevant field).', 'Graduate degree (MBA, MSc or master’s, PHD), an asset.', 'Extensive knowledge of data analysis techniques, languages, software and systems (SAS, R, Matlab, Python, SPSS, Tableau) required.', 'Extensive knowledge in SQL (or a SQL-like language) required.', 'Experience with Vertica and Hadoop, an asset.', 'Game industry experience strongly desired.', 'Skills', 'Story telling.', 'Ability to develop and maintain good relations and communicate with people at all hierarchical levels.', 'Strong problem-solving skills.', 'Ability to reconcile technical and business perspectives.', 'Autonomy and entrepreneurship.', 'Strong team spirit.', 'Passion for Rockstar Games and our titles.', 'How To Apply', 'Please apply with a CV and cover-letter demonstrating how you meet the skills above. If we would like to move forward with your application, a Rockstar recruiter will reach out to you to explain next steps and guide you through the process.', 'Rockstar is proud to be an equal opportunity employer, and we are committed to hiring, promoting, and compensating employees based on their qualifications and demonstrated ability to perform job responsibilities.', 'If you’ve got the right skills for the job, we want to hear from you. We encourage applications from all suitable candidates regardless of age, disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, religion, belief, or race.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Our National Operations group is seeking a qualified individual who is passionate about data and\xa0data-driven insights to join our team. The ideal candidate will be a generalist, excited about performing the\xa0roles of a data steward, data visualization, and data engineer, and supporting the enterprise with data quality\xa0and transparency initiatives. Significant opportunity to grow in the role, as we progress on our data analytics\xa0journey, with the overall objective of transforming Suffolk into a leader in data analytics within the construction\xa0industry. The ideal candidate would be excited to work in a dynamic environment, and committed to our vision\xa0as Suffolk continues its “Build Smart” journey. This is the perfect opportunity to become a part of an innovative\xa0and energetic team that will help Suffolk transform its construction operations through sophisticated application of data\xa0analytics.', '\xa0', 'Responsibilities', 'Data steward: Assess, improve and maintain critical data assets for construction operations ', 'Monitor the state of data quality within scope of responsibility', 'Establish goals for data quality improvement', 'Identify the best approaches for resolving data quality issues', 'Formulate business rules governing use of the data, perhaps including security and data life cycle management', 'Work with data stewards in other units to develop policies and best practices', 'Data engineer: Extract, transport, and transform data', 'Maintain records of data sources for enterprise-critical data', 'Collaborate with IT to understand best data sources for new business applications', 'Build and maintain simple, low-code applications for collecting and distributing governed data', 'Data visualization: Build and maintain dashboards', 'Support manager and business units in the design, development and maintenance of dashboards to drive data transparency', 'Monitor operations of dashboards in production, ensuring timeliness and accuracy of data displayed', 'Qualifications:', 'Bachelors Degree ', 'Passion for construction required; experience / background preferred', 'An understanding of how data is used within business processes and its impact', 'Exposure to data quality concepts, best practices and tools', 'Relentless focus on data precision and vigilance around appropriate conclusions', 'Communication and conflict resolution skills to help reconcile the different points of view and requirements that clash during cross-team and cross-organization efforts', 'Experience in translating business requirements to technical requirements and documentation', 'Experience in scripting / data science languages, ideally SQL, Python and / or R', 'Experience with building low-code applications in Microsoft PowerApps, Flow, and / or other applications a plus', 'Experience with building data visualizations in Microsoft PowerBI, Tableau, and / or other applications', 'Experience with business applications, e.g., Microsoft Excel, Access and Office Suite', 'Experience with ETL tools, e.g., Alteryx a plus', 'Experience with software development or programming a plus', 'Necessary Attributes:', 'Demonstrates Suffolk’s core values of hard work, professionalism, integrity, passion and caring', 'Proactive self-starter with the ability to work with minimal oversight', 'Meticulous and organized', 'A team player with excellent collaboration skills', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Strategy/Planning', 'Industries', 'Construction']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Medscape, a division of WebMD, develops and hosts physician portals and related mobile applications that make it easier for physicians and healthcare professionals to access clinical reference sources, stay abreast of the latest clinical information, learn about new treatment options, earn continuing medical education credits and communicate with peers. ', ' All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or veteran status.', ' ', 'WebMD is currently seeking a Data Analyst. This position will work within the BI team and has responsibility for deriving insights, analyzing trends, developing and delivering reporting including dashboards, and contributing to a data driven strategy and leading data projects. We are searching for someone with strong analytic capabilities and success in deriving insight from data. Your background should include dashboard design, data visualization, automated reporting applications, coding, testing, debugging, file maintenance routines and documentation of both database design and Tableau reporting platforms. To be successful, you will need technical knowledge of all phases of enterprise reporting systems applications.', 'In this role you will:', ' ', 'Analyze different aspects of the business based on requirements and the intended audience. This can include root-cause analysis, making recommendations and delivering key metrics; ', 'Build data models and define KPIs that allow the business to better understand trends, growth, and opportunities; ', 'Empower stakeholders in a self-serve manner by conceptualizing, building, and delivering dashboards based on a set of requirements or needs; ', 'Communicate effectively with internal stakeholders and support them to better understand user activity on the site;\xa0\xa0 ', 'Manage projects and ad-hoc tasks from inception to delivery; ', 'Present findings from data analysis to peers, management, and leadership; ', 'Develop implementation plans and timelines; ', 'Develop Data Warehouse structures and reports; ', 'Manage, run, and refresh schedules for dashboards and reports; ', 'Perform bug fixing, maintenance and upgrades to code; ', 'Maintain documentation for design, development and reporting work; ', 'Translate business requirements into technical designs. ', 'Qualifications:', ' ', '3+ years’ experience in a data intensive role including providing data analysis and developing reports using enterprise reporting tools ', "Bachelor's degree in information technology, computer science, or a related quantitative field or an additional 4+ years of business/data analysis experience ", '1+ years’ experience creating dashboards using Tableau or other similar data visualization tools and data warehousing applications ', '3+ years’ experience coding complex SQL queries and logic.\xa0 ', '1+ years’ manipulating data in a Unix environment, preferably Linux ', 'Preferably 1+ years’ of web analytic experience, Omniture experience is a Plus ', 'Demonstrable experience in RDBMS or MPP databases and related tools such as DB Visualizer or Toad ', 'Advanced experience with Excel ', 'Experience following established internal guidelines dealing with database objects, dashboard looks, and coding practices while meeting tight deadlines', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Analyst', 'Engineering', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Internet', 'Online Media']

Name: Senior Data Analyst
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Christine Easow', 'Christine Easow', 'Senior Data Analyst', 'As part of the Thinx Analytics Team, the ideal candidate will be responsible for supporting the overall analytics strategy and organization which delivers information, insight, and recommendations to optimize Thinx’s overall business, with heavy emphasis on e-commerce.', 'The primary directive for the person who fills this position will be taking responsibility for how the Looker BI platform is utilized.\xa0This includes building Explores from our AWS-hosted data sources (web analytics, Shopify, marketing platform data, etc.) and the views, looks and dashboards that flow from them.', 'The related secondary goal will be helping us consolidate and optimize the data we store in our Redshift data store.\xa0We need to blend and aggregate the data we collect for faster and better reporting and analysis.', 'Finally, the analyst will also work on ad hoc and deep dive analyses for our internal partners, primarily marketing, merchandising and product teams, giving them data-driven insight into improving our business.\xa0\xa0', 'Key to these responsibilities is that we are looking for someone to provide insightful solutions and analysis followed by active recommendation, not merely fill a mechanical reporting role. We are looking for a creative thinker who can help us continue moving forward, improving our customer experience.\xa0\xa0', 'SKILLS & EXPERIENCE', '4+ years reporting/analysis experience at an online retailer, ecommerce setting, publisher, online agency or like environment.', 'Intermediate experience with Looker to create Explores and reports.', 'Intermediate experience with SQL, Hive or like database querying language.', 'Experience and/or desire and aptitude to learn ETL scripting for our Redshift data store and Shopify.', 'Knowledge of Adobe Analytics, Heap, Google Analytics or like web analytic tools.', 'Experience with BI/data visualization platforms such as Tableau, Power BI or Datorama is highly desirable.', 'Strong project management and communication skills.', 'Strong conceptual/analytical/creative thinker.', 'Strong data interpretation and communications skills; ability to summarize and present complex findings clearly and concisely to various management levels.', 'Provide insights and recommendations to increase site conversion and drive site improvements. Identify traffic trends by channel, abandonment issues and opportunities for improving site conversion rates.', 'Provide analytic support to measure sales performance, analyze promotional results.\xa0Provide data to determine measure marketing efforts effectiveness.\xa0', 'Research and recommend enhancements to web design/functions and CRM systems.', 'About Thinx', 'We empower every body* through innovative solutions and social change. From first periods to post-menopause and all the leaks in between, we create solutions that champion and support bodies throughout all stages of life. Our period underwear, Thinx (BTWN) and Thinx, and our absorbent underwear for bladder leak protection, Speax, are expertly designed with our signature technologies to help eliminate the anxiety and discomfort that come with leaks at different ages. But our work doesn’t stop there: we’re also driving social change to make a difference for generations to come.', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Analyst', 'Engineering', 'Industries', 'Apparel & Fashion']

Name: Project Manager / Data Analyst
Description: ['We are seeking an energized Project Manager / Data Analyst with Healthcare and Finance experience to join the Siemens Financial Services group. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Note: The FBI offers Data Analyst opportunities throughout the majority of the Agency’s 56 Field Offices.', ' ', '\xa0 ', 'As an FBI Data Analyst, you will use your technical skills to contribute to the mission of the FBI — to protect the American people and uphold the Constitution of the United States. In addition to technical expertise, our Data Analysts must show initiative and be open to working in both team and individual settings.  ', '\xa0 ', 'Data Analysts at the FBI manage vast amounts and varieties of data associated with criminal and national security investigations. You will clean, standardize, enrich and visualize data using computer programming and statistical analysis so investigative teams can derive more meaningful insights from their data. ', '\xa0 ', 'As a Data Analyst, you will work on a variety of projects and threats, making every day different from the next. One day you could be visualizing geospatial data to illustrate a surveillance subject’s daily routines and pattern of life, while the next you could be consolidating and normalizing inconsistent information to help identify persons of interest in an investigation. You may be required to testify in court about the procedures and methods used to obtain data and to prepare and furnish authoritative oral and written reports on opinions and findings to stakeholders within the law enforcement community. ', '\xa0 ', 'As a Data Analyst you will: ', 'Plan, develop, and administer data for the utilization, storage, cleaning, conditioning and retrieval of data. ', 'Design and complete analytics for complex data projects involving broad and varied subject matter. ', 'Analyze data collection gaps and recommend modifications for collection methods. ', 'Employ programming languages to normalize, manipulate and enrich datasets, including composing scripts to automate recurring or continuous manual data processes affecting multiple squads and/or programs. ', 'Utilize various methodologies to evaluate data, determine relevant patterns and identify boundaries for application of data in qualitative and quantitative analyses. ', 'Present visualizations and data analysis findings to executive management and external audiences. ', '\xa0 ', '\xa0 ', 'TECHNICAL QUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS:', ' ', 'Skill in high-level programming languages (e.g., Python or R) to manipulate data. ', 'Ability to assess patterns, trends, outliers and apply statistical methods to analyze data. ', 'Ability to standardize, enrich and visualize data in graphs, charts and other graphics for various audiences. ', ' ', 'Pay levels for this position range from GS-7 through GS-13. ', '\xa0', ' ', ' ', 'KEY REQUIREMENTS:', ' ', 'Must be a U.S. citizen. ', 'Must be able to obtain a Top Secret clearance. ', 'Must complete form FD-887, Request for Access to Sensitive Compartmented Information (SCI). ', 'Must pass an FBI polygraph examination. ', 'Must pass an FBI-administered urinalysis drug test. ', 'Must be in compliance with the FBI Employment Drug Policy:', 'No use of marijuana within the last three years. ', 'No use of any other illegal drug in the past 10 years. ', 'No selling, distributing, manufacturing or transporting of any illegal drugs. ', 'No use of a prescription drug or a legally obtainable substance in a manner for which it was not intended within the last three years. ', '\xa0 ', 'In addition, you: ', 'Must never have been convicted of a felony. ', 'Must not be in default on a student loan insured by the U.S. government. ', 'Must be registered with the Selective Service System (males only, exceptions apply). ', ' ', ' ', 'EDUCATION REQUIREMENTS: ', 'Undergraduate or graduate degree in any of the disciplines listed below or an undergraduate or graduate degree that provided at least 24 combined semester hours in these disciplines and experience in the development or adaptation of applications, systems or networks: ', 'Computer Science ', 'Engineering ', 'Information Science ', 'Information Systems Management ', 'Mathematics ', 'Operations Research ', 'Statistics ', 'Technology Management ', '\xa0 ', 'All applicants will be rated on the following competencies:', ' ', 'Analytical Thinking ', 'Coding ', 'Advanced Mathematical Reasoning ', 'Technology Application ', 'Communication ', 'Interpersonal Ability ', 'Problem Solving/Judgment ', ' ', ' ', 'HOW TO APPLY', ' ', 'STEP 1:', ' Click on the “Apply” button to be directed to the FBIJobs Careers website.  ', 'Please note: ', 'Must', ' ', 'use the Mozilla Firefox web browser when applying to FBIJobs.gov job openings and Talent Networks. ', '\xa0', ' ', 'STEP 2: ', ' Click the “Start” button to begin.  You will be prompted to either Sign In to continue or to register with FBIJobs if you don’t already have an account. ', ' ', 'STEP 3: ', ' Follow the step-by-step process to submit your interest. You will be guided through each step.  You must complete all sections of the form ', 'AND ALL REQUIRED DOCUMENTS MUST BE ATTACHED ', 'to successfully submit your interest. ', ' ', 'Your resume, specifically noting relevant work experience and associated start and end dates. ', 'Other supporting documents: ', '  ', 'College transcripts, if qualifying based on education, or if there      is a positive education requirement. ', ' ', 'Portfolio of sample work demonstrating strong graphic design and drawing/forensic art skills. ', '  ', 'Veterans: DD 214; Disabled Veterans: DD 214, SF-15 and VA letter      dated 1991 or later. ', ' ', '\xa0 ', 'Please see instructions on the site for attaching documents.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Analyst', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Security and Investigations', 'Computer & Network Security', 'Information Technology and Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ["ABC Supply, a 13-time winner of Gallup's Great Workplace Award, is currently seeking a talented Business Intelligence Data Analyst at their National Support Center in Beloit, WI.", 'Reporting to the Manager of Pricing and Merchandising Analysis, this associate will manipulate data to create actionable outputs and reports. These outputs will support decision making and suggest actionable conclusions throughout key areas of pricing and merchandising.', 'Responsibilities', ' Retrieve, manipulate, and validate pricing and merchandising data into actionable outputs both in conjunction with our SQL data warehouse team and on your own.', ' Automate various reporting, email distribution, and light application tasks in SQL, Access, Excel, and Outlook using Python and PowerShell.', ' Help automate and run existing programs that aid customers in earning reward dollars directly from manufacturers (includes monthly report generation and running automated email distributions).', ' Support company-wide implementation of pricing resets by automating and managing analytical tools and processes that assist field pricing teams in making more informed pricing decisions.', ' Provide rebate and net cost reporting to accounting, vendor relations, and senior management - both standardized and ad-hoc.', ' Author, schedule, and run recurring reports, dashboards, and quarterly review materials.', ' Run ad-hoc analysis to answer complex business questions as needed.', 'Requirements', " Bachelor's Degree required (Computer Science, Mathematics, Analytics, or Statistics preferred)", ' Proven ability to develop in SQL.', ' VBA, PowerShell, and/or other computer code required.', ' Intermediate Microsoft Excel skills including vlookups, formulas, and pivot tables required', ' Proven ability to manipulate data and run ad hoc analysis (2+ years experience)', ' Experience using Python, R, Crystal Reports, and/or Tableau preferred.', 'Skills & Traits', ' Strong data manipulation and problem-solving skills required.', ' Self-directed time and project management skills required.', ' Ability to work independently or in a group setting with a complex flow of information.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Building Materials', 'Transportation/Trucking/Railroad']

Name: Data Analyst II
Description: ['Bayside Solutions is seeking a ', 'Data Analyst II', " to be part of our client's team in South San Francisco. This is an opportunity to work with the largest privately held pharmaceutical corporation in the world and ranks among the world's 20 leading pharmaceutical corporations.", 'Our Client\'s culture is highly collaborative, offers an environment that encourages employees to expand their knowledge in order to make a profound impact on patients\' lives. This could explain why their company has been recognized as one of the "Top Twenty Employers" in biotechnology and pharmaceuticals by Science Careers.', 'Our Company Bio: Bayside Solutions was founded in 2001, Bayside was recognized as one of the fastest growing professional staffing companies in Northern California. The numbers tell the story: We have close to a 100% client retention rate, 700% growth in four plus years and over 95% repeat business. Our dedication to building partnership relationships with both our clients and our recruits is the key to our phenomenal success.', 'You can find additional information on our company website at www.baysidesolutions.com.', 'Data Analyst II', 'Job Benefits:', 'An opportunity to join a patient-focused organization that is driven to develop, manufacture and commercialize medicines to treat life threatening conditions.', 'Work for a company that is local to the bay area and recognized as a leader of innovation.', 'Competitive compensation commensurate with experience.', 'This position is eligible for medical, vision, dental benefits, paid sick time, and 401K.', 'Summary of Responsibilities: ', 'The Drug Safety Data Analyst / Business Systems Analyst reports to the Principal Project and Execution Manager and is part of the Project and Execution Group in US Drug Safety. The Data Analyst is responsible for analyzing and trending a variety of datasets across USDS, including areas in: Compliance and Training, Safety Case Management and Project Tracking as part of the Project Portfolio Management. The role of the Data Analyst is to provide analytic support by developing a USDS metrics dashboard to the USDS Leadership Team in order to further understand project status and trends within safety reporting and ultimately result in more efficient and improved pharmacovigilance processes.', 'Write, modify and maintain programs that perform complex data analyses', 'Responsible for data transfers, including documentation and correspondence with internal and external partners', 'Manage data from multiple sources', 'Develop programs to provide ad-hoc reports for data review to support USDS across the department: Compliance and Training, Case Management, Portfolio Management', 'Design and develop a USDS Dashboard on Project Tracking, Compliance and Training metrics', 'Design and develop Excel macros, Qlikview or Tibco Spotfire visualizations', 'Programming activities and usage for data management and data review', 'Develop and maintain Excel, Qlikview or Tibco Spotfire programs including programming practice', 'May collaborate members of the leadership team to address internal and external data needs/gaps', 'Summary of Qualifications:', 'BS/MS/MPH in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics or equivalent', 'Minimum 3 years in Pharma Industry preferred', 'Strong Excel programming skills required', 'Strong Visualization programming skills: Qlikview or Tibco Spotfire', 'Experience in programming with large datasets and developing programs, testing and documentation', 'Extensive experience of handling external data', 'Knowledge of developing reporting or other systems using Excel and SAS', 'Experience in SAS programming a plus', 'Working knowledge of statistical research methodology', 'Good understanding of data cleaning process', 'Works effectively, independently and collaboratively', 'Demonstrates initiative and accountability', 'Strong organizational skills, detail oriented, ability to adapt to change', 'Ability to interact effectively in a multifunctional, multidisciplinary team setting', 'Understands the business, scientific, and regulatory aspects of the organization', 'Ability to balance competing interests of various stakeholders and strive for achieving mutually beneficial and compliant solutions', 'Influence decision makers', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Analyst', Name: Business Intelligence Data Analyst - Data Visualization
Description: ['Parker Hannifin', 'Founded in 1917, Parker Hannifin Corporation is a $14.3 billion, global company.', "With annual sales of $14.3 billion in fiscal year 2019, Parker Hannifin is the world's leading diversified manufacturer of motion and control technologies and systems, providing precision-engineered solutions for a wide variety of mobile, industrial and aerospace markets. The company has operations in 50 countries around the world. Parker has increased its annual dividends paid to shareholders for 63 consecutive fiscal years, among the top five longest-running dividend-increase records in the S&P 500 index.", "Parker’s engineering expertise and broad range of core technologies uniquely positions the company to solve some of the world’s greatest engineering challenges. By partnering with customers, Parker improves their productivity and profitability and seeks new ways to solve humanity's biggest challenges.", 'Department Marketing Statement', 'Parker Aerospace is a global leader in the research, design, integration, manufacture, certification, and lifetime service of flight control, hydraulic, fuel and inerting, fluid conveyance, thermal management, lubrication, and pneumatic systems and components for aerospace and other high-technology markets. The company supports the world’s aircraft manufacturers, providing a century of experience and innovation for commercial and military aircraft.', 'Major Duties', 'Business Analyst Position Summary', 'We are looking for a Business Intelligence Analyst – Data Visualization who will be the vital link between our information technology capacity and our business objectives. ', 'They will be key in supporting and ensuring the successful completion of reporting and analytical deliverables.', 'The role of the Business Intelligence Analyst includes the extraction, cleansing, integration and transformation of data into valuable business information in the form of reports or dashboards. ', 'The analyst will need to perform necessary analyses to provide valuable information, insights and opportunities to the business teams.', 'The analyst may also assist the business in implementing new solutions by determining and documenting the requirements of a project, program or function. These requirements would then be integrated into recommendations for tools, processes and skillsets required to meet the business needs.', 'Responsibilities', 'Essential Functions: ', 'Translate stakeholders requirements into reporting deliverables', 'Dashboard and report generation', 'Develop performance metrics', 'Deliver standard and ad hoc reports and analyses', 'Participate in evaluating new technologies to ensure the advancement of technology architecture and data within organization Business Intelligence needs', 'Qualifications', ' Degree in technical or business curriculum ', ' 1-4 years of data analysis experience', ' Must be professional in conduct and practice', ' Ability to work in a team environment', ' Creative, responsive and adaptive in a dynamic environment', ' Must have the aptitude and desire to learn new competencies and skills', ' Adhere to all established company policies, procedures, and safety rules as outlined', ' Ability to work 40 hours per week; bearing in mind some overtime may be required', ' Extensive experience and working knowledge of computers, especially in data extraction/reporting software', ' Expertise in delivery technologies and data access, including familiarity with metadata, data organization, data integration, data quality assessment and data profiling', ' Working knowledge of data preparation, governance and quality ', ' Proven experience in eliciting requirements and testing', ' Familiarity with accounting and finance practices and principles', ' Ability to independently, resourcefully, and creatively research and implement new solutions', ' Working knowledge of analysis and reporting tools', ' Interpersonal communication skills', ' Ability to frequently communicate orally, write, read, comprehend, reason, and perform basic mathematic calculations and analysis', ' Experience with Excel analytics, WebFocus, SQL Server or similar', ' 1-2 years of Power BI and Tableau experience is preferred', 'TYPICAL MENTAL AND PHYSICAL DEMANDS', 'While performing the duties of this job, the employee is required to sit. The employee frequently is required to use hands to operate a computer and talk and hear. The employee is occasionally required to stand and walk. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision. Also expected of the employee is regular attendance, the ability to work cooperatively and professionally with others and members of the public, and the ability to manage multiple tasks at once. Overnight, long distance travel may be required, based on the individual needs of the position.', '(The essential functions have been provided as examples of types of work performed by employees assigned to this job classification. The Company reserves the right to modify the work assignments and/or to make reasonable accommodations so that qualified employees can perform the essential functions of the job. The physical and mental demands described above are representative of those required to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.)', 'Equal Employment Opportunity', 'Parker is an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer. Parker is committed to ensuring equal employment opportunities for all job applicants and employees. Employment decisions are based upon job related reasons regardless of race, ethnicity, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, age, national origin, disability, gender identity, genetic information, veteran status, or any other status protected by law. U.S. Citizenship/Permanent Resident is required for most positions.', '(“Minority/Female/Disability/Veteran/VEVRAA Federal Contractor”)', 'If you would like more information about Equal Employment Opportunity as an applicant under the law, please go to http://www.eeoc.gov/employers/upload/eeoc_self_print_poster.pdf', 'and', 'http://www1.eeoc.gov/employers/upload/eeoc_gina_supplement.pdf', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Advertising', 'Public Relations', 'Marketing', 'Industries', 'Aviation & Aerospace', 'Electrical/Electronic Manufacturing', 'Industrial Automation']

Name: Manufacturing Data Analyst
Description: ['Overview', 'Clearwater Paper Corporation (NYSE: CLW) is a $1.7B company that manufactures quality consumer tissue, away-from-home tissue, parent roll tissue, and bleached paperboard and pulp at manufacturing and converting locations across the nation. Working at Clearwater Paper provides an opportunity to enrich your career through challenging and meaningful work and ongoing training and development—all in a supportive environment. We know our success depends on your success.', 'Responsibilities', 'The Manufacturing Data Analyst supports our Consumer Product (Tissue) Division and is responsible for the preparation, analysis and validation of data compiled in the generation of diverse performance, costs, and financial metric reports. A member of the Mill Operations team and reporting into the Director of Manufacturing, this role works with five manufacturing facilities to manage multiple intenseness of Manufacturing Execution Systems (MES) inclusive of identifying opportunities to improve our ERP System (JDEdwards). A key focus area for the role is to identify opportunities to improve consistency in the quality of performance and production data analytics derived from multiple systems.', 'Data Management & Reporting', ' Develop data quality rules inclusive of developing, measuring and implement data governance standards ', ' Collaborate with IT to ensure data warehouse(s) performance supports SLA’s with division to ensure meeting manufacturing performance and productivity reporting cadence ', ' Collaborate with business leaders to identify critical business performance metrics to develop and maintain a balanced performance scorecard ', ' Perform data profiling tasks; analyzing key data in multiple systems in order to clarify structure content, relationships, and derivation of rules ', ' Process Management ', ' Develop procedural process guides to ensure data accuracy, yielding consistency in quality reporting ', ' Evaluate existing suite of reporting tools and process; documenting and streamlining reporting processes ', ' Implement routines to Extract/Load/Transform (ETL) data from various systems ', ' Technical Continuous Improvement ', ' Lead in collaboration with IT the design and documentation of key data processes; identify data owners and stewards ', ' Partner with Manufacturing leaders to create ad-hoc queries; seeking to automate and standardize reporting ', ' Proactively lead the identification of opportunities to develop and enhance analytical tools (Cost, Financial, Performance and Production) ', 'Qualifications', 'Key Competencies & Attributes', ' Strong understanding of critical financial business metrics; ability to develop and leverage drive data to quantitative and analytical reporting to support business decisions ', ' Able to think strategically and act tactically ', ' Demonstrated ability to work in a matrixed and highly collaborative environment to influence change and core processes ', ' High degree of business curiosity; quick learner with a proactive and agile mindset ', ' Optimistically looks toward future for opportunities to innovate and improve ', ' Exceptional communication skills (written and verbal); leading and presenting complex materials for various audiences ', ' Change management skills; aligning and bringing others along ', 'Required Education And Related Experience', ' Bachelor’s degree in Computer Information Systems, Data Science, Analytics, Statics, Information Systems or related field required ', ' Minimum of six years’ experience with data management, data integrity, data warehouse architecture and design ', ' Minimum of six years’ experience with manufacturing BI reporting or related industry reporting ', ' Experience with SQL Server, Master Data, JDE, MES ', 'Skills And Abilities (technical/professional Skills, Expertise And Qualifications)', ' Microsoft Certifications in Access, SQL Databases ', ' Demonstrated commitment to ongoing personal development through continuing education, coaching and developing others ', ' Highly adept performing at a fast pace communicating and collaborating across multiple stakeholders ', ' Confident and proficient in navigating in an automated environment with proficiency in MS Office Suite, multiple business intelligence databases ', 'Illustrative Functions', ' Eye fatigue due to long hours of computer work ', ' Office enviornment with occasional exposure to manufacturing enviornment ', ' Less than 10% travel occasional business meetings ', 'Each and every one of our employees contributes to the success of our company by showing up every day with a commitment to improving ourselves, the company and our communities.', 'Find out from our employees what they like about working for Clearwater Paper.', ' What do you like most about working at Clearwater Paper? ', 'I enjoy how the people at Clearwater Paper focus on being great. We do not settle for mediocrity. We work hard to continue to make the company better, even though it is already a great place to work.', ' What do you like most about working in your department or function? ', 'The company has given me the opportunity to serve as the sustainability representative for my location—Lewiston, Idaho. In this capacity, I have had the chance to work with employees companywide and interact with the Avista Technical Advisory Committee and represent the company by speaking at site-wide meetings and external industry conferences. The company also has provided excellent mentoring experiences and opportunities for me to professionally develop and become more knowledgeable in my chosen career field.', 'At Clearwater Paper we are driven by purpose, grounded in values, and connected to communities; Learn more here', 'Options', 'Apply for this job online Apply', 'Share', 'Email a friend this job Refer', 'Sorry the Share function is not working properly at this moment. Please refresh the page and try again later.', 'Share on your newsfeed', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Consumer Goods', 'Paper & Forest Products']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ["Race Winning Brands is a leader in developing high performance racing engine components with record setting brands including Wiseco Pistons, K1 Crankshafts & JE Pistons. We're looking for a Data Analyst to join our Applications team. The Applications team is a multi-discipline group specifically tasked with using technology and creative skills to solve challenging business problems and provide support across all brands in the organization.", 'As a Data Analyst, you will play a critical role in supporting our ERP system and Data Warehouse. Solid SQL skills (T-SQL, SSIS, SSRS) are highly desired for this role for performing ETL activities, creating dashboards and reports, bulk updates, and digging deeper into complex cases as needed.', 'Responsibilities', ' Perform Data Analysis Activities (T-SQL, SSIS, SSRS) to support ERP system and Data Warehouse', ' Develop/enhance SQL and Power BI reports/dashboards', ' Develop and run bulk SQL upload scripts, update stored procedures and views as required', ' Performance Tuning and Optimization using monitoring and troubleshooting tools', ' Utilize business data to provide all departments with actionable insights', ' Work with other IT or business staff to complete projects as needed', ' Provide daily support using ticketing system as necessary', 'Minimum Qualifications', ' 2 years of relevant work experience', ' Working knowledge of Microsoft SQL Server', ' Proven ability to be customer focused', ' Proficiency with Microsoft Office applications', ' Excellent verbal communication and written skills', 'Preferred Qualifications And Skills', ' 3+ years of experience supporting production SQL databases (T-SQL, SSIS, SSRS)', ' Experience with Microsoft Power BI', ' Analytical and problem-solving skills including the ability to investigate, assess,', 'and recommend solutions to moderately complex situations', 'SDL2019-256', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Automotive', 'Machinery', 'Mechanical or Industrial Engineering']

Name: Junior Metrics and Data Analyst
Description: ['Summary', 'IAP is seeking a Junior Metrics and Data Analyst, based out of Bahrain, to develop and maintain a metrics and analysis database needed to track and report metrics for Chief of Naval Operations (CNO) Availabilities and Continuous Maintenance Availability (CMAVs) completions for Commander, Naval Surface Force, Atlantic.', 'Essential Job Functions: (not limited to duties as described performs related duties as requested)', ' ', 'Develop and maintain metrics and analysis database to track and report metrics for CNO Availabilities and CMAVs completions. At times these metrics may require frequent updates to support management decisions and Flag level briefs. The database should have a report generator capability for identified users to print reports without analyst assistance.', ' ', 'Develop, update and maintain CNO Availability and CMAV trend reports. Analyze trend reports and provide recommendations.', ' ', 'Develop and propose data sources and metrics for determining the root causes of CNO Availability extensions. Develop and maintain database to track and report metrics for CNO Availability extension root cause analysis once identified. As part of the root cause analysis, assist in determining strategies to mitigate CNO Availability extensions.', ' ', 'Develop and maintain database to track and report metrics for CNO Availability growth and new work root cause analysis once identified.', ' ', 'Function as the database manager for the metrics and analysis database. Ensure the database can update/interface with the Command Readiness Dashboard.', ' ', 'Coordinate with Modernization managers to track and analyze modernization installation operational impact and return on investment (ROI) for tracked alterations. Maintain this data in the metrics and analysis database.', ' ', 'Develop graphs, charts and reports summarizing results of assigned analyses.', ' ', 'Generate PowerPoint presentations outlining results and recommended actions.', ' ', 'Extract data from various databases to include but not limited to NMD, NDE, OARS, FSC, MRDB (Corona), MFOM (NIPR/SIPR), EDFS, ELAR, EARRTS, VAMOSC, LogiQuest, One Touch, Haystack, and ships CSMPs to perform exploratory data analysis.', ' ', 'Use metrics analysis to support optimal levels of forward staged MCM/PC material. Track key material assets and validate that local quantities are supported by historical needs and track inventories, which are not formally held in the supply system.', ' ', 'Education & Experience: (or equivalent )', ' ', 'Two years of experience in Microsoft Access database design and management', ' ', 'Two years of experience in data analysis support for complex projects', ' ', 'License & Certifications', ' ', 'Microsoft Technology Associate (MTA) certification preferred', ' ', 'Knowledge & Skills', ' ', 'Proficient and experienced with Microsoft Office, especially with Access, Excel and PowerPoint.', ' ', 'Knowledge of Visual Basic for Applications (VBA)', ' ', 'Physical Demands/Working Environment', 'See Workfit or Physical Demands Job Analysis', 'Travel', 'Position is based 100% in Bahrain. Estimated travel from Bahrain will be to government sites including, but not limited to Norfolk, VA, San Diego, CA or Mayport, FL to attend conferences, as needed.', 'Security Clearance: Secret', 'Job Location TBD, Bahrain Position Type Full-Time/Regular', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Finance', 'Accounting/Auditing', 'Finance', 'Industries', 'Banking', 'Insurance', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst - Healthcare Analytics
Description: ['Eclaro International is currently recruiting for ', 'Data Analyst (Healthcare Analytics)', ' ', 'for one of our clients in ', 'Saint Louis', ', ', 'MO', '.', ' ', 'Job Description:', 'Position Purpose: The Data Analyst (Healthcare Analytics) will have the opportunity to make a significant impact through the discovery, development, and implementation of leading-edge analytics that answer important business questions. The analyst will collaborate with key corporate and health plan business partners for the purpose of identifying and delivering robust reporting and analytics capabilities to drive improved business performance.', 'Interpret and analyze data from multiple sources including claims, provider, member, and encounters data. Identify and assess the business impact of trends', 'Develop, maintain, and troubleshoot complex scripts and reports developed using SQL, Microsoft Excel, or other analytics tools', 'Lead the planning and execution of large-scale projects and new reporting tools, translating business goals into actionable solutions', 'Identify and resolve data, process, and technical issues and communicate root-cause with stakeholders as appropriate', 'Partner cross-functionally at all levels of the organization and effectively, both verbally and visually, communicate findings and insights to non-technical business partners', 'Independently engage with business leaders to understand market-specific levers and constraints', 'Leverage enterprise reporting tools to rapidly deliver data-driven insights and recommendations', 'Research key business problems and proactively identify opportunities for cost and utilization improvements through quantitative analysis', 'Communicate and present data-driven insights and recommendations to both internal and external stakeholders, soliciting and incorporating feedback when required', 'Mentor junior analysts on analytic best practices and business need fulfillment. Delegate tasks to junior analysts, providing guidance and validation where required', 'Qualifications:', 'Education/Experience:', "Bachelor's degree in business, economics, statistics, mathematics, actuarial science, public health, health informatics, healthcare administration, finance or related field or equivalent experience. Master's degree preferred. 5+ years of experience working with large databases, data verification, and data management or 3+ years IT experience. Healthcare analytics experience preferred. Experience with table creation and indexing, query optimization, and utilization of stored procedures. Description: ['Job Description', 'Savos Investments, a division of AssetMark, Inc., provides advisors and their clients with risk managed, multi-asset portfolios and strategies to meet a wide variety of investment goals. ', 'Position Summary', 'The Investment Data Analyst role is responsible for data preparation and analysis related to research and reporting within the Investments Team at Savos. The Data Analyst will work closely with the CIO and Director of Quantitative Investing to understand the goals of each analysis, manage the analytics process, and document results.', 'Responsibilities', 'Translate desired research or reporting output into the required input data for analysis', 'Source, validate and organize required data for reporting or research study', 'Document data processes and procedures for recurring tasks', 'Perform data transformation and statistical analysis per the study outline', 'Develop appropriate data visualizations to illustrate key findings of analysis', 'Assist with development of research best practices for robust and efficient analysis', 'Required Qualifications', 'Attention to detail and ability to quality check your own work; sense check plausibility of results', 'Data cleansing and validation', 'Proficiency with data manipulation and one or more relevant scripting languages', 'Fundamentals of statistical analysis and ability to find new techniques as necessary', 'Ability to prioritize and manage multiple requests and escalate tradeoffs needed to meet deadlines', 'Reliability, flexibility and constructive attitude toward change', 'A team player who will thrive in a small company environment', 'Bachelor’s degree from a fully accredited 4-year college or university', 'Preferred Qualifications', 'Degree in a quantitative field of study', 'CFA Charterholder or progress towards CFA', 'Experience with pandas, R, excel/VBA or equivalent', 'FactSet or Bloomberg proficiency', 'At Savos, we come to work every day driven to develop purpose-built, outcome-oriented investment solutions. It takes a certain mix of talent, passion, and dedication to join our team. If you want an exciting, challenging, and fulfilling career, Savos might be the place for you.', 'AssetMark, Inc. is a leading strategic provider of groundbreaking investment and consulting solutions created to serve independent financial advisors and help them create great outcomes for their clients. Through a consistent program of engagement, education and community-building, AssetMark brings like-minded advisors together to share their ideas, experiences and solutions. This collaboration guides our development of investment, client relationship and practice management tools that advisors can tap to help clients achieve their investment objectives and life goals.', 'We are always seeking bright, creative, energetic individuals who want to learn and grow with the company. AssetMark is an innovative organization, delivering the best services in the industry. We offer a rewarding work environment, competitive salaries, full benefits, and excellent opportunities for career growth. We are headquartered in the San Francisco Bay Area. We also have regional offices in Phoenix, AZ, Encino, CA, Atlanta, GA, Chicago, IL, and State College, PA. Become a part of our growing team today!', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Now hiring a Data Analyst in Boston, Massachusetts!', 'Job Description', 'Trillium Technical is seeking a Data Analyst in the Boston, MA area. To meet envisioned demand for new analytic work, we are seeking contractors for Healthcare Data Analyst roles for the remainder of Calendar Year 2020. Under the general direction of a Manager of Analytics or designee, the Healthcare Data Analyst Contractor will lead and develop datasets and analyses for assigned projects as well as develop/deliver any related reports required.', 'This position will provide information to leadership regarding the state of our operations and require the access, manipulation, and reporting on healthcare claims and administrative data in our Data Warehouse. The Healthcare Data Analyst will utilize subject matter expertise as well as exceptional analytic and coding skills with a customer service focus to design and deliver analytic products that meet or exceed client expectations.', 'Duties', ' Lead and guide the development of analyses and produce reports using a variety of healthcare related data which support the development, implementation and monitoring of programs/projects.', ' Manipulate and build large datasets from data sources (e.g. claims and encounter data) to support analyses through use of efficient SAS/SQL code which will produce answers to complex business questions.', ' Deploy complex qualitative and quantitative analysis techniques utilizing SAS and SQL', ' Develop project-specific analytic plans, data manipulation and collection efforts; may include: claims analysis, interviews, focus groups, and surveys involving clients, state agency personnel, and other key informants.', ' Create testing measures and/or algorithms to test and analyze large amounts of data.', ' Design and implement data management and quality control procedures, including writing technical requirements and documentation of data sets.', ' Prepare and deliver all data analysis reports. Develop and present summary reports, ongoing project evaluations and oral and written presentations as requested by client, stakeholders and senior leaders to better inform decision making', ' Provide interpretation of data to key stakeholders and leadership; including identifying and reporting data patterns and abnormalities and presenting analyses of key metrics and trends.', ' Responsible for database development and ongoing management to ensure data integrity and accuracy/quality of reporting, as well as report writing functionality.', ' Communicate with all appropriate parties to ensure that the project’s objectives, scope, and expected deliverables of each project phase are understood.', ' Plan, coordinate, and review activities related to data collection and analysis to meet deadlines.', ' Review and monitor compliance with the federal and state regulations.', ' Perform other duties as required.', 'If you’re interested in this Data Analyst opportunity and meet the qualifications, please apply today!', 'Qualifications', ' Advanced knowledge and use of data mining software tools such as SAS, SQL, or Tableau.', ' Advanced SAS/SQL programming skills.', ' Exceptional analytic and problem-solving skills.', ' Demonstrated experience/skills in appropriate computer, statistical or database applications.', ' Familiarity with coding systems (i.e., ICD10) and hospital billing systems (DRGs).', ' Excellent attention to detail and time management/organization skills to manage multiple priorities.', ' Demonstrated ability to research issues and resources', ' Demonstrated ability to write reports, journal articles and/ or other technical documents.', ' Excellent communication skills, both oral and written.', ' Interpersonal skills necessary to interact successfully with a wide range of individuals', 'Trillium has been recruiting and placing professionals for over 30 years. From Fortune 100 companies to small businesses, our philosophy remains the same: to achieve excellence by providing quality employees and an uncompromising level of service. We believe in honesty, integrity, and a simple philosophy of providing value to our customers and our employees. We strive to be unsurpassed in the recruitment and placement of quality and skilled professionals. Trillium is an Equal Opportunity Employer.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Automotive', 'Staffing and Recruiting']

Name: Data Science Analyst
Description: ['Data Science Analyst\xa0', '\xa0', 'About Ware2Go', 'Ware2Go is changing the warehousing, fulfillment, and supply chain landscape. We connect businesses of all sizes to enterprise-grade solutions and assets that help them compete on previously impossible levels — combining a completely on-demand warehouse network with the technology and tools that allow merchants to compete through their supply chain.', 'www.ware2go.co', 'We build our culture around people that:', 'Seek excellence in everything they do', 'Thrive in a fast-paced, high energy workplace', "Value efficiency and respect other people's time", 'Are team players and have a strong work ethic', "Don't forget to have fun and be positive", 'Position Summary:', 'The ideal candidate is a self-directed, experienced data scientist who believes in demonstrating how data can be used to help our customers.\xa0We are looking for a motivated, hands-on Data Science Analyst to support our Merchant enablement tool set with a heavy data-driven approach and operational mindset. This person will play a critical role in supporting the development of the Supply Chain Toolset. Collaborating with members of the Sales & Marketing and Warehouse Operations teams, the Data Science Analyst will work cross-functionally to support strategic initiatives. He/She will establish and maintain a data dictionary and work directly with department heads and other staff to gather reporting requirements and establish dashboards.', 'Key Responsibilities', 'Refine and develop descriptive reports and other deliverables to support data-driven decision-making.', ' Work closely with development team to understand available data. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Quest Analytics is one of the fastest growing SAAS healthcare employers in the Healthcare software space in the US. Healthcare providers and insurance companies rely on our software to help them audit their networks to comply with federal regulations. We’re the industry-leading healthcare network management partner. That’s why more than 400 of America’s health plans and healthcare organizations, as well as more than 500,000 providers, nationwide trust our enterprise services to provide consumers with convenient access to an adequate network of doctors and hospitals and an up-to-date, accurate directory of providers.', 'We have an opportunity for a curious and methodical Data Analyst to join our team in our new Overland Park, KS location in Corporate Woods. For the right candidate, we may also be open to remote work opportunities.', 'As a Data Analyst at Quest Analytics you will provide analytical support to the Provider Content team that is responsible for managing and mastering the healthcare provider data used to measure the accuracy, adequacy, and accessibility of health plan networks. There are two primary areas of focus. The first is analysis to support the daily operations of campaigns targeted at obtaining primary source attestations of data quality. The second is analysis to support the development of data management and governance rules that can be applied to create a high quality, high integrity master data set that acts as the foundation of all Quest products.', 'The ideal candidate will have the technical skills to access and manage the data, the analytical skills to draw insights that directly address business problems and needs, and the communication skills to share those insights with both business and technical audiences.', ' Responsibilities Include But Are Not Limited To ', 'We offer you the opportunity to work with a committed and experience technical team on an advanced data delivery platform.', 'The Role', 'Performing analysis to identify target populations for outreach campaigns', 'Analyzing attestation data to demonstrate success overall, by cohort, by client, and in demographic slices', 'Running analysis on healthcare provider and organization to determine:', ' How to identify the same entity across sources', ' How to determine the best source of information for each data element', ' How to define entities, relationships, and ', 'Performing in-depth data investigations related to campaigns or projects', ' Interpreting results of analysis and communicate findings back to teammates in a clear manner', 'Providing actionable recommendations for improving data quality or integrity', 'Generating ideas to improve outreach campaign (fax/email/post/call)', 'Working with development and operations teams on solving business and data problems', 'Working with client service to understand and address client concerns around data or deliverables', 'Requirements', 'Bachelor’s degree; preferably in data analytics or computer engineering', 'A minimum of 5 years experience in a related position ', 'Experience working with large datasets', 'Experience with data tools such as Databricks and Spark', 'Intermediate to advanced SQL skills', 'Familiarity with best practices of data management and governance', 'Ability to work independently and as part of a team', 'Strong communication skills', 'Experience with BI tools such as Looker', 'Experience with Python, R, Scala, or Java preferred', 'Experience with healthcare data preferred', 'Ready to Evolve?', 'We want smart, driven individuals to help us create Quest Analytics future. If you invest yourself in your work, live with enthusiasm, and thrive on results, we want to know you.', " What's In It For You ", 'Great benefit package with:', '100% paid HDHP Health plan, Dental, Vision for Employee tier and cost sharing for all other tiers', 'Company matching 401(k)', 'Generous PTO and 9 Holidays', 'Paid Life, Short and Long Term Disability', 'Paid maternity / paternity and much more', 'Flexible work arrangements so you can balance work/life', 'Competitive salary and success sharing bonus', 'The opportunity to get in on ground floor and grow and learn as the company grows', 'Work at in a fun, flexible, casual environment', 'Ability to telecommute when needed', 'Remote work may be available for certain jobs', 'Plus, the free gourmet coffee to fuel the brainpower necessary to conquer your goals, and free drinks and snacks.', 'Apply TODAY!', 'Visa sponsorship is not available at this time.', 'Quest Analytics provides equal employment opportunities to all people without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, ancestry, marital status, veteran status, age, disability, sexual orientation or gender identity or expression or any other legally protected category.', 'Applicants must be legally authorized to work in the United States. Verification of employment eligibility will be required at the time of hire.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Financial Services']

Description: ['Job Description', 'Title', ': Data Analyst - Healthcare', 'Location', ': Boston MA', 'Duration', ': Long term', 'Position Summary', 'The Healthcare Data Analyst will utilize subject matter expertise as well as exceptional analytic and coding skills with a customer service focus to design and deliver analytic products that meet or exceed client expectations.', 'Duties', ' ', 'Lead and guide the development of analyses and produce reports using a variety of healthcare related data which support the development, implementation and monitoring of programs/projects.', ' ', 'Manipulate and build large datasets from data sources (e.g. claims and encounter data) to support analyses through use of efficient SAS/SQL code which will produce answers to complex business questions.', ' ', 'Deploy complex qualitative and quantitative analysis techniques utilizing SAS and SQL', ' ', 'Develop project-specific analytic plans, data manipulation and collection efforts; may include: claims analysis, interviews, focus groups, and surveys involving clients, state agency personnel, and other key informants.', ' ', 'Create testing measures and/or algorithms to test and analyze large amounts of data.', ' ', 'Design and implement data management and quality control procedures, including writing technical requirements and documentation of data sets.', ' ', 'Prepare and deliver all data analysis reports. ', ' ', 'Develop and present summary reports, ongoing project evaluations and oral and written presentations as requested by client, stakeholders and senior leaders to better inform decision making', ' ', 'Provide interpretation of data to key stakeholders and leadership; including identifying and reporting data patterns and abnormalities and presenting analyses of key metrics and trends.', ' ', 'Responsible for database development and ongoing management to ensure data integrity and accuracy/quality of reporting, as well as report writing functionality.', ' ', 'Communicate with all appropriate parties to ensure that the project’s objectives, scope, and expected deliverables of each project phase are understood.', ' ', 'Plan, coordinate, and review activities related to data collection and analysis to meet deadlines.', ' ', 'Review and monitor compliance with the federal and state regulations.', ' ', 'Perform other duties as required.', ' ', 'Qualifications', ' ', 'Advanced knowledge and use of data mining software tools such as SAS, SQL, or Tableau.', ' ', 'Advanced SAS/SQL programming skills.', ' ', 'Exceptional analytic and problem-solving skills.', ' ', 'Demonstrated experience/skills in appropriate computer, statistical or database applications.', ' ', 'Familiarity with coding systems (i.e., ICD10) and hospital billing systems (DRGs).', ' ', 'Excellent attention to detail and time management/organization skills to manage multiple priorities.', ' ', 'Demonstrated ability to research issues and resources', ' ', 'Demonstrated ability to write reports, journal articles and/ or other technical documents.', ' ', 'Excellent communication skills, both oral and written.', ' ', 'Interpersonal skills necessary to interact successfully with a wide range of individuals.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Financial Services', 'Hospital & Health Care']
