Name: Data Analytics Specialist
Location: South San Francisco, California, United States
Description: ['As a Data Analytics Specialist you will work with clinical trial data to support Pharma Development, helping to generate new evidence and insights into our medicines to support of R&D. You will work with peers across the organization including biostatisticians, scientists, and bioinformaticians using patient level clinical data combined with digital sensor data to answer scientific questions.', 'We are looking for someone with a passion for data who can take a broad scientific question and distill insights through code, whether that be creating an interactive visualization, a predictive model, or using inferential statistics. This includes the ability to understand the challenges and limitations of the data and thinking of innovative solutions for manipulating and aggregating our data in preparation for analysis. As our projects are done in partnership with other team members and stakeholders, a collaborative and entrepreneurial mindset is critical.', 'We are a small global team of analysts, and you will collaborate regularly with our team members and stakeholders in South San Francisco, Welwyn, Basel, Mississauga, and Shanghai. As a Data Analytics Specialist, you will support and lead both molecule and non-molecule projects. For molecule-specific projects, you will work with the biometrics study team on tasks such as employing advanced analytical methodology to answer exploratory scientific questions, building interactive displays to promote quicker and more efficient methods for data interrogation, developing solutions to innovate biometrics workflow from data receipt to insights generation, and embedding new ways of working into the teams. Non-molecule work could involve scientific software development in R, internal infrastructure building, and supporting or leading cross-functional analytical projects.', 'As you onboard, you will receive comprehensive mentoring to develop good coding practices along with our reproducible workflow using R packages and GitHub. Additionally you will be encouraged to attend and present at industry conferences to continuously develop your data science skill set and expand your network. At Genentech, your continued growth is important, and you will be supported through continued learning opportunities including courses, seminars,and workshops.', 'If you are proud of contributing and feel you have the commitment to teamwork and innovation that we are seeking, then Genentech is the organisation for you. In return we offer a competitive salary plus the excellent benefits you would expect from a blue-chip organisation, including a genuine interest in your development and progression.', 'Required Education And Experience', ' Advanced degree in biostatistics, statistics, computer science, mathematics, or the biological sciences ', ' Advanced hands-on R programming experience, preferably in support of clinical trial analysis ', ' 3+ years of experience applying statistical inference and machine learning methodologies to scientific data ', 'Preferred Skills And Experience', ' Has a good foundation in computer science and has strong knowledge in computational statistics including statistical learning ', ' Has experience performing complex data manipulation in preparation for analysis ', ' Is familiar with established interactive data visualization packages such as Shiny, plotly, etc. ', ' Has experience building packages in R ', ' Has passion for reproducible and reusable analysis by packaging modular code, using version control, or using containerized computing environments ', ' Is comfortable being an advocate and resource for analytic or development best practices ', ' Is familiar with the regulatory framework and guidelines for pharma products ', ' Is able to communicate with colleagues possessing varying technical backgrounds and can negotiate effectively ', ' Is able to explain technical concepts to a non-technical audience; enjoys sharing learnings and mentoring peers ', ' Has good knowledge of English in a business environment ', 'This is a local hire only designated position, as relocation assistance is not available for the position', ' Roche is an equal opportunity employer. ', 'Research & Development, Research & Development > Clinical Development', "Roche is an equal opportunity employer and strictly prohibits unlawful discrimination based upon an individual's race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin/ancestry, age, mental/physical disability, medical condition, marital status, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.", 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Other', 'Industries', 'Hospital & Health Care']

A Company analyst will be all of the above and enjoy working as part of a dynamic team in a fast-paced environment.', 'General Duties', 'Pull digital, email, and print subscriber audiences, counts, and profiles via our database access tool, SQL', 'Create custom targets and lists for marketing program fulfillment', 'Provide stakeholders with cross-platform campaign delivery and performance insights', 'Work with stakeholders across brands and verticals to develop high-value audiences', 'Respond to inquiries or RFPs regarding availability, based on custom targeting parameters', 'Work with and support Privacy Policy Coordinator and Company Global Compliance team', 'Required Skills', '4-year college degree', 'Experience using SQL and working in large data environments preferred', 'Strong communication and analytical skills, in order to effectively derive and share business insights from data sets', 'Ability to work independently and within a cross-functional team', 'Very strong prioritization skills', 'Willingness to learn and share knowledge in a collaborative environment', 'Experience supporting direct marketing activities in a data warehouse environment', 'Strong customer-service orientation and a keen attention to detail', 'What happens next?', 'If you are interested in this opportunity, please apply below and we will review your application as soon as possible. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ["At The Scion Group, we're changing the way people see student housing. It's bigger than beds and buildings. It's about providing an experience for students to explore the best years of their lives. It's about creating communities — both on and off campus — that feel like less like a place and more like a home.", 'The Scion Group is in search of a Data Analyst for our Business Intelligence team to help us explore and understand our growing business data sets. The Data Analyst will extract, combine and build models from various data sets to further expand on performance metrics and influence company business decisions. This position will primarily focus on the transform phase of the ELT (Extract, Load, Transform) process, combining raw data from multiple sources within a data warehouse and transforming it into dimensional models used for business intelligence.', 'The Day-to-Day', ' ', 'Understand the day-to-day issues that our business faces, which can be better understood with data', ' ', 'Research, explore and analyze large data sets to determine patterns and rules for organizing them.', ' ', 'Communicate and present results of analyses to management and other stake-holders.', ' ', 'Create, maintain, and optimize data models and architecture within a data warehouse.', ' ', 'Collaborate with both software engineers and business analysts to translate business requirements into technical specifications.', ' ', 'Handle projects from the idea stage to production deployment.', ' ', 'Troubleshoot integrity issues and validate result sets.', ' ', 'Bridge communication gaps between technical and non-technical individuals.', ' ', 'Recommend and implement process improvements and best practices.', ' ', 'Create and maintain technical documentation.', ' ', 'Develop and maintain ELT processes.', ' ', 'Examples Of Projects You Might Work On', ' ', 'Merge customer experience data with property management data to help determine how we can continually improve the experience of our residents.', ' ', 'Integrate a new dataset to increase the granularity of existing data models.', ' ', 'Utilize social media and reputation data to drive customer sentiment analysis.', ' ', 'Aid our business analysts modeling and projecting revenue data.', ' ', 'Work closely with Human Resources and Talent teams to develop new analytics that will allow us to better understand the employee lifecycle.', ' ', 'About You', 'Curious - Takes on challenges with ambiguity and makes sense of them. Enjoys uncovering themes, synthesizing obscure connections & problem-solving. Willing to experiment and stops at nothing to develop solutions.', "High Integrity - Takes accountability for work output and willing to do whatever's necessary to make sure findings are supported by fact.", "Team-oriented - With an all-in approach, you're eager to lend support wherever and whenever. After all, sharing knowledge, learning and building consensus with others is the recipe for the best possible results.", ' ', 'Technical degree is preferred, but not required.', ' ', 'Highly proficient in SQL programming and building and analyzing data sets.', ' ', 'Proficient with relational databases and JSON structured data.', ' ', 'At least 1 year of experience modeling data within data warehouses and/or databases.', ' ', 'Familiar with data warehouse design (e.g. dimensional modeling) concepts.', ' ', 'Ability to optimize SQL queries to improve performance.', ' ', 'Prior experience with version control, issue tracking, build/release management and data visualizations.', ' ', 'Familiar with Amazon web services or other cloud-based systems.', ' ', 'Familiar with a complex programming language such as Ruby, Python, JavaScript, etc.', ' ', 'Prior experience with designing data integrations and ELT processes is a plus. ', ' ', 'Next Steps', 'We will reach out to candidates we feel are suitable for the position. A written code review is part of how we will get to know you - this is a great opportunity to showcase your talent!', 'The Scion Group LLC provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, religion, creed, national origin, color, gender, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, physical or mental disability (as long as the employee/applicant is otherwise qualified for the job with or without a reasonable accommodation), genetic information, HIV/AIDS status, marital status, uniformed service, veteran status, pregnancy or other legally protected status or category under federal or state law. The Scion Group LLC complies with applicable state and local laws governing nondiscrimination in employment in all locations in which the Company has properties. This policy applies to all terms and conditions of employment, including hiring, placement, promotion, termination, layoff, recall, transfers, leaves of absence, compensation, training and other terms and conditions of employment. The Scion Group LLC is committed to the principles of equal employment opportunities.', 'IND4', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Financial Services', 'Real Estate']

Description: ['Already an employee? You must apply through our internal portal: click here', 'Data Analyst', 'Date: Mar 18, 2020', 'Location:', 'Milwaukee, WI, US', ' ', 'Requisition ID: ', '10824', 'A Career In Beer', 'Our purpose at the Molson Coors Beverage Company is to delight the world’s beer drinkers. So, if you get fired up about making a real difference as part of a winning team like we do, we want to hear from you.', 'The Headlines', 'In the role of ', 'Data Analyst', ' working in ', 'Milwaukee, WI ', 'you will be part of the North America IT team. Name: Data Analyst Consultant, Asset Management
Location: Washington, District of Columbia, United States
Description: ['Job Description', ' The Company ', "WSP USA, is one of the world's leading engineering and professional services firms, dedicated to serving our clients. With nearly 7,000 people in 100 offices across the U.S., we partner with our clients to help communities prosper.", 'Our Asset Management and Business Advisory practice brings internationally recognized leadership to the USA critical infrastructure sectors – driving organization and asset performance, reducing risks and managing whole life costs of the assets we depend on every day.', ' The Role ', 'We are seeking a dynamic, detail-oriented, self-motivated Data Analyst to both support and drive continued growth in our digital services. You will join an established team that is a leader in providing asset management and business advisory services across the country and beyond.', 'We are looking for self-starters who can contribute to our success. The Data Analyst will have experience establishing databases and data structures, and working with applications including GIS, Excel, SQL and other data modeling tools to support business decision making. Ideally the individual will have experience in managing large data sets and will be familiar with the quality control requirements associated with transitioning and cleansing data.', 'We are looking for forward thinkers who can help grow our digital services. Individuals with interest or knowledge in data analytics, machine learning, and AI will thrive well in the environment we are creating.', 'It is preferred that the individual has experience in the critical infrastructure sectors – transportation, water and power utilities – but we will consider applicants with experience and knowledge in both commercial, military, manufacturing, facilities and other sectors.', 'Primary Roles And Responsibilities', ' ', 'Can work within a multi-disciplinary team to support, and/or lead the delivery of complex consulting projects across sectors – with a particular focus on the infrastructure verticals', ' ', 'Independently perform data collection, cleansing/transitioning and analytical processes and produce high quality reports. Understanding of QA/QC measures for data governance and able to support implementation of such measures both internally and with clients.', ' ', 'Actively contributes to and able to engage with clients (both internally and externally)', ' ', 'Job Requirements', 'Required Attributes', ' ', 'Bachelor’s degree in relevant field, with graduate degree preferred', ' ', '5+ years’ experience in directly relevant endeavors', ' ', 'Proven experience in consulting or a comparable role in an organization where the individual has held a role responsible for managing data, information or the deployment of technologies to manage assets.', ' ', 'Strong interpersonal skills and high emotional IQ - A strong team player who can get things done, can provide leadership when needed or be led when required.', ' ', 'A good understanding of infrastructure and a working knowledge of how to structure data systems for effective use.', ' ', 'A good understanding of technologies used to support data and information management – including GIS, Excel, SQL, Oracle.', ' ', 'Preferably an understanding of Enterprise Asset Management Systems – including Maximo, Infor and other systems.', ' ', 'Familiarity with national and international practices and standards', ' ', 'An ability to share knowledge informally and formally and coach and support more junior consultants.', ' ', 'Must have authorization to immediately work in the United States', ' ', ' Location ', 'The asset management team works nationally and the candidate should be available to travel. The preferred home location for this posting is in Washington, DC.', 'About WSP USA', "WSP USA is the U.S. operating company of one of the world's leading engineering and professional services firms. Dedicated to serving local communities, we are engineers, planners, technical experts, strategic advisors and construction management professionals. WSP USA designs lasting solutions in the transportation, buildings, energy, water and environment sectors. With nearly 9,500 people in 150 offices across the U.S., we partner with our clients to help communities prosper. www.wsp.com/usa", 'WSP provides a comprehensive suite of benefits including medical, dental, vision, disability, life, and retirement savings focused on a providing health and financial stability throughout the employee’s career.', 'At WSP, we want to give our employees the challenges they seek to grow their careers and knowledge base. Your daily contributions to your team will be a key piece in our meeting client objectives, goals and challenges. Are you ready to get started?', 'As a federal contractor and recipient of federal funds, WSP USA is a drug free workplace and Equal Opportunity Employer - Race/Age/Color/Religion/Sex/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity/National Origin/Disability or Protected Veteran Status', 'The selected candidate must be authorized to work in the United States.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Civil Engineering', 'Oil & Energy']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['hi there, thanks for stopping by.', 'What follows is a bit lengthy, but will give you a better idea of what we do, what we value and how we work.', 'What We Do', 'You know those websites that make it impossible to add an item to your cart, sign up for a newsletter or enter your credit card information? Sooo frustrating, right?! Instead of buying the pants or entering your email, you throw up your hands, mutter a curse word or two and immediately head over to YouTube to watch cat videos.', 'At surefoot, we make life easier for web surfers and shoppers like you.', 'We ease user frustrations, improve conversions and craft data stories that help our clients make sound, data-informed business decisions.', 'How, you ask?', 'In short, we formulate hypotheses based on data from sources like Google Analytics, HotJar and customer service data, which allow us to identify the biggest friction points on our clients’ sites. Then, we validate or invalidate our hypotheses in the form of A/B tests, whose results we (you) analyze to determine the optimal site experience.', 'Data Analyst Role And Requirements', 'As a data analyst at surefoot, your human interaction will mostly consist of conversations with our strategic directors and clients. However, your primary interactions will be with our clients’ datasets. We’ll look to you to analyze the results of our clients’ tests and distill that hard data into digestible “data stories” that can be universally understood by everyone from the intern to the CEO.', 'In other words, some of your time will be spent crunching numbers while the other portion will be spent translating those numbers to English, helping “non-numbers speaking people” understand what the data means.', 'If you’re still with us, here are the requirements:', 'must-haves', '4-5+ years of professional experience in data analysis and statistics', '3+ years of deep experience with Google Analytics', 'preferably GAIQ certified', 'working knowledge of statistical frameworks and concepts pertinent to A/B testing, including Frequentist and Bayesian statistics, p-values, confidence intervals, minimum detectable effect, etc.', 'top notch communicator with good writing skills, grammar and grasp of the English language', 'demonstrated expertise communicating results and actionable insights from in-depth analysis to decision makers', 'experience developing Keynote or Google Slides presentations with a strategic focus', 'exceptional organizational skills and attention to detail (e.g., if you found an error in this job description, it is still bugging you)', 'self-motivation, ability to work independently and remotely', 'strong desire to continuously learn and grow', 'craves feedback and accepts it with gratitude', 'high emotional intelligence', 'hobbies outside of work', 'nice-to-haves', 'experience with A/B testing or personalization', 'experience writing SQL, wrangling spreadsheet data, and analyzing data using R or Python', 'experience with tools like Optimizely, Dynamic Yield, VWO, HotJar, Mixpanel', 'interest in the outdoors or staying active (many of our clients fall into the outdoors and active lifestyle industry)', 'funny GIF library, good emoji usage, sense of humor', 'nitty gritty details', 'Base salary: $90,000 to $110,000 (depending on experience) + benefits (health, paid vacation and holidays, self care bonuses, all-hands trips, fully remote team)', 'The position is open to U.S. (W2) and Canadian-based (independent contractor) applicants only. No Visa sponsorship is provided.', 'our values and culture', 'Our values are extremely important to us and we stake the company on them. This means that even the Grand Poobah of analysts won’t be considered if our values don’t align.', 'be nice and do the right thing.', ' We firmly believe that this world could use a bit more kindness so we strive to infuse it throughout our interactions – with clients, each other, our communities and all those we meet. Doing the right thing means we refuse to waiver on doing what is best for our business or our clients, even if it means less upside for us.', 'own your mistakes, learn from them and move on.', ' Our preferred path is to “fail fast”. In other words, identify your mistakes, take ownership, discuss what you learned, identify solutions for ways to correct them so they don’t happen again and move on.', 'dedication to your craft and our clients.', ' While we do track how many hours are spent working on each client, we value output over hours. As long as you’re a US citizen, we don’t much care where you work from. However, we do care a whole damn lot that your work is done with efficiency, precision and pride.', 'channel your inner entrepreneur and make it easy for people to say “yes”. If a process isn’t working or hindering you in some way, don’t wait to be asked to fix it. Instead, like Nike says, Just Do It™. Make it work for you. Experiment. You’re a smart, capable person so don’t ask permission. Arrive with a well-thought-out solution that makes it easy for everyone to say “yes” to, you smarty, you.', 'ready to apply?', 'Since we are a remote team, we have a somewhat atypical interview process. For the first step of the interview phase, we ask applicants to show basic competency in the necessary skill sets.', 'If all is well there, you’ll move on to phase two which involves a Zoom video call to get to know one another a bit better. If we’re feeling good about that, we’ll contact your references.', 'And finally, if your references check out and confirm you’re not a stabber, we’ll ask you to do some actual paid work with us to determine fit for both parties.', 'To apply, compose an email to click apply and click apply with the following:', 'your responses to these 3 short exercises: https://sf.surefoot.me/qlknJs', 'any relevant experience you have with a/b testing, data analysis, user research, etc.', 'contact info for 3-4 references (will only be contacted if you move through phase 1)', 'All applicants will receive a response. surefoot is an equal opportunity employer and we are committed to building a company that embraces and celebrates diversity and inclusion. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Apparel & Fashion', 'Retail']

Provide support in the following areas: (1) establishment of the governance framework for the HCS implementation effort; (2) supporting the prioritization of pilots and reporting on pilot execution; (3) formal communications on HCS pilots with the Navy organizations that will participate in the pilot(s), and (4) coordinating meeting spaces, meeting schedules, and other administrative support.', 'Job Description And Responsibilities', 'Support the design of the governance model, processes, procedures, initiative owners used to manage the execution of the pilots.', 'Deliver bi-weekly status reports (progress, risks, cost, schedule)', 'Support development of multi-year rollout plans for successful pilots, approved by the ASN M&RA and the SECNAV/UNSECNAV.', 'Identify program performance metrics', 'Develop high-level ROI/Business case for each of the', 'five anchors based on the pilots aligned to each anchor', 'Establish details/deadlines/business case for each pilot', 'Develop performance measurement method and metrics for each pilot', 'Establish/Maintain process to identify/mitigate barriers to success, dependencies, etc.', 'Required Skills And Qualifications', 'Security Clearance: ', 'Secret', 'U. Name: Data Analytics Engineer
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Alyson Basso', 'Alyson Basso', 'Head Of Talent at Dig', 'About the role:', 'DIG is looking for a Data Analytics Engineer to join our growing Data team. You will work to build batch and real-time data pipelines that support DIG’s analytics, business intelligence, data science and reporting needs.\xa0', 'DIG’s Data team prides itself on agility and collaboration,\xa0 with each member building a deep understanding of their allocated function or domain (i.e. Finance, Labor, Supply, Marketing, Product) and working on the end-to-end data lifecycle - from stakeholder requirements to ETL and data modeling. In this role you will take charge of ETL development and advisory for the Data team, while also contributing to modeling as needed. If you are looking for an opportunity to build your data engineering expertise and drive impact by empowering colleagues to make data-powered decisions, this is the role for you!\xa0', '\xa0', 'You Will:', 'Serve as the team’s ETL expert, leading the majority of pipeline work, and provide support and training for other Data Engineers', 'Design, build, and maintain custom ETL pipelines', 'Design best practices for big data processing, modeling, and warehouse development', 'Build automated data validation tools to check for data accuracy and quality', 'Assess the value and quality of new data sources', 'Take ownership over the full data life cycle of your allocated domains by:', 'Understanding the data requirements of your key stakeholders through regular meetings and goal setting sessions', 'Developing the vision and roadmap to provide visibility for stakeholders and the Data team', 'Conducting the required ETL and data modeling and maintenance, as needed', 'Participate in building DIG’s data capacity as a key stakeholder in all team projects. Problems we’re excited to tackle in 2020 include:\xa0\xa0', 'Consolidating customer data across all DIG channels to enhance the customer experience', 'Analyzing how customers interact with our digital products to inform product development and enhance user experience', 'You Have:', '3+ years of relevant work experience in data engineering, data analysis, or business intelligence', 'Experience building, maintaining, and scaling ETL pipelines', 'Experience designing scalable, efficient data architecture and models', 'High-level of proficiency in ', 'Python', ' preferred (comparable programming languages will be considered)', 'Knowledge of ', 'relational databases ', '(we use BigQuery)', 'Proficiency in ', 'SQL', '. Experience in LookML ', 'is a plus', 'Proficiency in ', 'Linux operating system', ' command lines (i.e. bash)', 'Knowledge of GIT, Github, Jira, and Scrum', 'Proficiency in analytical packages (i.e. Pandas, SciPy, etc.) ', 'is a plus', 'Experience working in agile methodology and applying Agile to data engineering is a plus', 'Excellent communication skills\xa0', 'Passion for high quality and accurate work', 'Work perks:', 'Aside from your standard job description fare (competitive salary, medical, dental, vision) we also offer:', 'Macbook lan, based on availability', 'Flexible vacation time', 'Phone reimbursement', 'Equinox gym membership, based on eligibility', 'Commuter benefits', 'A (hypo-allergenic) dog-friendly HQ (they’re amazing stress-relievers)', 'Complimentary DIG lunch everyday', 'About us:', 'DIG is a farm-to-table food company with over 25 locations in New York and the Northeast, serving seasonal vegetables and culinary comfort food on an urban scale.', 'The company is built on a culture of driven curiosity and ambitious innovation, finding and implementing new solutions to offering simple, healthy, affordable meals. Our mission is to build a better food system (one vegetable at a time) that offers a better deal to customers, cooks, and farmers alike.', 'Since getting started in 2011, we have focused on the essentials of our mission- building kitchens, training chefs, and developing one-on-one relationships with over 50 partner farms. The next few years will be a period of expansion, as we open in new cities and use the platform we’ve built for a better conversation around sourcing, cooking, and the business of food.', 'And did we mention free DIG for all employees? We strongly recommend the sweet potatoes.', 'DIG believes in the power of a shared table to bring people together as we are committed to building a culturally inclusive team. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['About Northeastern', 'Founded in 1898, Northeastern is a global research university and the recognized leader in experience-driven lifelong learning. Our world-renowned experiential approach empowers our students, faculty, alumni, and partners to create impact far beyond the confines of discipline, degree, and campus.', 'Our locations—in Boston; Charlotte, North Carolina; London; Portland, Maine; San Francisco; Seattle; Silicon Valley; Toronto; Vancouver; and the Massachusetts communities of Burlington and Nahant—are nodes in our growing global university system. Through this network, we expand opportunities for flexible, student-centered learning and collaborative, solutions-focused research.', 'Northeastern’s comprehensive array of undergraduate and graduate programs— in a variety of on-campus and online formats—lead to degrees through the doctorate in nine colleges and schools. Among these, we offer more than 195 multi-discipline majors and degrees designed to prepare students for purposeful lives and careers.', 'About The Opportunity', 'The Northeastern community has a tradition of giving back, and each day, we witness the impact of our community’s remarkable generosity. Our students are pursuing co-ops in all corners of the globe, growing their cultural fluency and preparing to thrive in the world. Our faculty are delivering leading-edge scholarship, teaching and mentoring tomorrow’s leaders. And our researchers are pioneering new lines of inquiry, accelerating discovery in emerging fields. Northeastern University Advancement and Prospect Development team play an integral role in engaging the Northeastern community to create a stronger, more sustainable, and bright future.', 'Responsibilities', 'The Data Analyst, Prospect Development, reporting to the Senior Director of Prospect Development, will be responsible for collecting, organizing, analyzing, and synthesizing complex data sets to assist in setting the strategy and reporting the outcomes for all advancement research operations. The Data Analyst will manage the unit’s Tableau Server environment through the development and maintenance of reports and dashboards; provide consultation and support to end users on the platform; oversee overall structure of the reporting environment regarding its organization and consistency across reports; build queries to extract and aggregate data from various sources; and, monitor and clean large data sets to ensure reporting efficiency and accuracy. The Analyst will discover and communicate significant patterns, trends, and stories with Advancement data and provide recommendations based on analysis. They will report to leadership on key data for Prospect Management, Prospect Identification, and Research. Additionally, the Analyst will create and develop ongoing processes that ensure quality of data, perform computing tasks such as data transformation, integration, and management, and, manage regular data clean-up and hygiene projects.', 'The Data Analyst will be responsible for the analysis and utilization of techniques to inform effective engagement, solicitation, and moves management strategies, and will serve as a liaison between outside vendors, Advancement Information Services, and other internal and external partners. The work of the Data Analyst will inform a variety of Prospect Development operations including pipeline analysis, forecasting, portfolio optimization, and prospect identification. This position will work closely with members of the Advancement Research team, Advancement Information Services, and Northeastern’s various fundraising units to strategize, plan, coordinate and produce effective, data-driven solutions with the ultimate goal of increasing prospect engagement and fundraising revenue.', 'Preferred qualities are a strong background in Tableau, mathematics, statistics, and financial and behavioral data analysis.', 'Qualifications', 'Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, mathematics, statistics, or a related field & 2-5 years of data analysis, data gathering, and reporting experience required; project management skills and IT competency, especially with constituent databases preferred. The ability to communicate clearly and effectively with internal and external partners, meet deadlines, be self-motivated, and work independently. Accuracy, attention to detail and a customer service-oriented attitude. Ability to be a team player with proven relationship and influencing skills and ability to collaborate with colleagues from a variety of functional areas. Proven strategic and analytical thinker. Strong organizational skills, ability to multi-tasking, flexibility and adaptability to shifting priorities. Competency in problem solving. Excellent oral/ written communications and interpersonal skills; effective time management and organizational skills that are essential for success in this position.', ' Advanced practical experience with BI and data analysis software (Tableau, SPSS, MS Access, Excel, etc.) required.', ' Strong technical and interpersonal skills are essential, as well as the ability to think critically and analytically, work independently, and handle multiple tasks.', ' Demonstrated ability to understand various data structures and common methods in data extraction and transformation.', ' Demonstrated ability to analyze data, recognize patterns and provide informed recommendations for decision making.', ' Ability to summarize and present analytic work and findings in ways that are accessible to non-technical audiences required.', ' Creative problem-solving, superb attention to detail, and ability to manage multiple concurrent projects and activities required.', ' Excellent organizational and time management skills.', ' Understanding/familiarity of higher education and enrollment management a plus.', ' Experience with predictive modeling a plus.', 'Salary Grade', '11', 'Northeastern University is an equal opportunity employer, seeking to recruit and support a broadly diverse community of faculty and staff. Northeastern values and celebrates diversity in all its forms and strives to foster an inclusive culture built on respect that affirms inter-group relations and builds cohesion.', 'All qualified applicants are encouraged to apply and will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, religion, color, national origin, age, sex, sexual orientation, disability status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.', 'To learn more about Northeastern University’s commitment and support of diversity and inclusion, please see www.northeastern.edu/diversity .', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Nonprofit Organization Management', 'Higher Education', 'Research']

optimization ', 'Complete project objectives in time to meet project milestones in alignment with project plans ', 'Assist with the product backlog for all projects, solve problems for teams, and relates to analyzing large data sets ', 'An analytical mind and inclination for problem-solving in an evolving data environment ', 'Strong verbal and written communication skills with team members and Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Data Analyst', 'Two Sigma is a different kind of investment manager. ', ' Experience with Python (and/or Java) ', ' Experience with SQL and working with a relational database system, such as Microsoft SQL Server. Description: ['Summary of Duties At Thurston County Public Health and Social Services, our mission is working together to achieve the highest level of health and well-being for everyone. Description: ['Data Business Analyst Summary:', 'Signature Consultants is seeking a Business Analyst with Technical skills or a Data analyst with technical skills for one of our larger financial clients in the Charlotte area. The ideal candidate will have 5-7 years of experience and will also have worked in an agile environment.', 'Overview:', 'Resource will be responsible for analyzing business requirements & processes across multiple applications & groups within legal technology. This will include understanding data across the space and defining how to present that data to end users to improve transparency and empower the end user to make more informed decisions based on the data presented. If we are unable to procure this resource in a timely fashion, it will prevent the project from starting on time and achieving the desired business goals in 2020. Resource will be working on 30 different applications and will need to be able to pull the data from them. ', 'Requirements & Responsibilties:', 'Provide simultaneous support as a business, process, and data analyst across the legal space, including multiple applications.', 'Comprehend, document, and analyze business processes. This will include review for potential improvement & automation. Consider all potential data sources and the needs of the LOB when analyzing these processes.', 'Ability to relate seemingly unrelated data to create a comprehensive concept showing relevant information to the end user.', 'Ask insightful and probing questions regarding the department and how processes fit with legal & regulatory requirements.', 'Building long-term, productive relationships with business and technical partners, including QA, development, and the UX team.', 'Gathering requirements from the line of business for translation into a technical solution, including gap analysis as needed.', 'Writing stories using BDD (Behavior driven design), the INVEST approach, and vertical slicing to support the developers/QA staff & maximize delivered business value.', 'Interfacing with developers and QA to understand the proposed solution, ensure that it meets the business needs, and working to implement that solution. Testing of newly developed code prior to production releases or during technical recovery exercises.', 'Support ongoing maintenance work with the core eDiscovery product.', 'Aid other team members as needed with their initiatives/BAU and/or vendor relationships, though this position is largely focused on in-house developed solutions.', 'Documented ability to thrive & produce quality results in an Agile/scrum environment.', 'Strong understanding of browser based applications', 'Strong ability to understand & document business processes in a highly complex and regulated environment.', 'Excellent understanding of relatioial databases, data structures, and the ability to associate data with specific roles in the legal department.', 'Strong understanding of both SQL & Oracle syntax to enable data extraction & analysis from various sources.', 'Technical understanding of servers, networks, firewalls and other hardware functionality & interactions.', 'Understanding of ETL jobs, including core functionality and appropriate use.', 'Extremely strong verbal & written communication skills', 'Intellectual curiosity', 'About Signature Consultants, LLC', 'Headquartered in Fort Lauderdale, Florida, Signature Consultants was established in 1997 with a singular focus: to provide clients and consultants with superior staffing solutions. For the ninth consecutive year, Signature was voted as one of the "Best Staffing Firms to Work For" and is now the 14th largest IT staffing firm in the United States (source: Staffing Industry Analysts). With 28 locations throughout North America, Signature annually deploys thousands of consultants to support, run, and manage their clients\' technology needs. Signature offers IT staffing, consulting, managed solutions, and direct placement services. For more information on the company, please visit ', 'www.sigconsult.com', '. ', 'Signature Consultants is the parent company to ', 'Hunter Hollis', ' and ', 'Madison Gunn', '.', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Contract', 'Job function', 'Analyst', 'Finance', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Banking', 'Financial Services', 'Information Technology and Services']

Name: Data Analyst, Supply Chain
Description: ['Duties and Responsibilities', ' ', 'Develop and maintain analytical tools aimed at streamlining the collection, consolidation, analysis, and feedback of supply chain related data.', ' ', 'Proactively identify inconsistencies in the data through your visualizations and with statistical tests', ' ', 'Manage routine collection, consolidation, and analysis of supplier capacity data and risk relative to supply capability in meeting the demand forecast.', ' ', 'Maintain and develop supply chain BOM programs to accommodate business needs of different department.', ' ', 'Deliver continuous improvement efforts with current applications to increase automation and scalability as well as make improve existing reports.', ' ', 'Communicate results and business impacts of insight initiative to stakeholders within and outside of the company', ' ', 'Candidate Requirements And Qualifications', ' ', 'Experience building and maintaining reports in Tableau required', ' ', 'Knowledge of SQL, VBA, R or Python preferred', ' ', 'SAP ERP(MM, FI, PP) experience preferred', ' ', 'Adept at merging data from a variety of sources in order to generate conclusions through analysis', ' ', 'Experience in forecasting, supply chain planning, logistics and service operations a plus', ' ', 'Ability to track and lead new and ongoing project activities', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Electrical/Electronic Manufacturing', 'Computer Software', 'Automotive']

Name: Senior Data Analyst -New York City
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['At Rockstar Games, we create the games we would want to play ourselves. A career at Rockstar is about being part of a team working on some of the most creatively rewarding, large-scale projects to be found in any entertainment medium. You would be welcomed to a friendly, inclusive environment where you can learn, and collaborate with some of the most talented people in the industry. Rockstar New York is seeking an experienced data analyst to join our growing Analytics practice and help build Rockstar’s business intelligence capacity. Successful candidates will work with analytics and product leadership to assure that the most relevant possible real-time and historical data is identified, tracked, analyzed, and made actionable across all of our titles. This is a full-time permanent position based out of Rockstar’s unique game development studio in the heart of downtown Manhattan. WHAT WE DO The Rockstar Analytics team provide insights and actionable results to a wide variety of stakeholders across the organization in support of their decision making. We work together with a number of departments to design and implement data and pipelines. We collaborate as a global team to develop cutting-edge data pipelines, data products, data models, reports, analyses and machine learning applications. RESPONSIBILITIES Partner with analysts and live producers to identify strategic business questions, key metrics, and actionable insights. Provide consumer-ready recommendations, insights and reporting to Analytics team leadership, live producers, product managers and partner groups. Effectively translate statistical findings into actionable recommendations for senior leaders on game and business teams. Research and develop state-of-the-art data mining and statistical modeling solutions to understand game design, system performance and key business behaviors, such as player engagement. Drive needle moving improvements via hands-on exploration of data, dashboards, statistical analysis and predictive modeling. Combine qualitative and quantitative driven insights with game knowledge to recommend potential avenues to the game and business teams. Drive requirements for data collection and for data modeling with data engineers Work within a team of data analysts and engineers. QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years in a similar position or an analytics role in the marketing, finance, forensics, or technology fields. Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field (Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Operational Research, Business Intelligence or any other relevant field). Graduate degree (MBA, MSc or master’s, PHD), an asset. Extensive knowledge of data analysis techniques, languages, software and systems (SAS, R, Matlab, Python, SPSS, Tableau) required. Extensive knowledge in SQL (or a SQL-like language) required. Experience with Vertica and Hadoop, an asset. Game industry experience strongly desired. SKILLS Story telling. Ability to develop and maintain good relations and communicate with people at all hierarchical levels. Strong problem-solving skills. Ability to reconcile technical and business perspectives. Autonomy and entrepreneurship. Strong team spirit. Passion for Rockstar Games and our titles. HOW TO APPLY Please apply with a CV and cover-letter demonstrating how you meet the skills above. If we would like to move forward with your application, a Rockstar recruiter will reach out to you to explain next steps and guide you through the process. Rockstar is proud to be an equal opportunity employer, and we are committed to hiring, promoting, and compensating employees based on their qualifications and demonstrated ability to perform job responsibilities. If you’ve got the right skills for the job, we want to hear from you. We encourage applications from all suitable candidates regardless of age, disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, religion, belief, or race. Name: Customer Service Data Analyst
Description: ['Customer Service Data Analyst', ' ', ' ', 'Our client is seeking a Customer Service Data Analyst to play an important role on a New Product Development Team providing a better customer experience in the rollout of an exciting new robot platform. ', ' ', 'As the first line of inquiry into problematic units installed in the field, they’ll expect you to have a strong background in analysis of large quantities of data coming in on a cloud platform, triaging SW issues in complex electromechanical systems, as well as documenting and communicating any issues found. ', ' ', 'Where:', '\xa0Bedford, MA', 'Benefits:', '\xa0Health, Dental, Vision ', 'The individual in this role will work as part of the Customer Care element of a product development team and will work closely with the Software Engineering and Systems Engineering teams. The successful candidate will have experience or capability to quickly learn all aspects of the robot SW. ', ' ', 'Essential functions include:', ' ', 'Work with service centers to triage and investigate problems with customer robots and communicate any issues found to the development team ', 'Download robot data from an IoT/cloud-based infrastructure and perform first-level data analysis ', 'Improve automated data processing tools ', 'Submit bug tickets and attach relevant robot data ', 'Scramble quick responses to any issues found ', 'Create links between different data sources using APIs ', ' ', 'Skills Required:', ' ', 'Familiarity with software ', 'Strong technical problem solving and analytical skills ', 'Demonstrated ability to take ownership of task execution and work with minimal supervision ', 'Experience with Linux and Windows Operating Systems, including writing terminal commands ', 'Experience determining and tracking product defects ', 'Strong organizational skills ', 'International and Domestic Travel Required ', ' ', 'Desired Qualifications:', ' ', '2+ years of work experience in related field ', 'Experience with data analysis of a large fleet of IoT connected devices ', 'Experience in software testing ', 'Experience in data analysis, especially in automating analysis processes ', 'Experience testing a consumer robot ', 'Experience with product defect tracking tools, including Jira (including using Jira APIs) ', ' ', 'About Our Client:', ' ', 'Our client is the the leading global consumer robot company, designing and building robots that empower people to do more, both inside and outside of the home. Founded by MIT roboticists who had the vision of making practical robots a reality. To date, they have sold over 20 million robots and globally employ more than 600 of the robot industry’s best and brightest. They are committed to fostering invention, discovery and technological exploration in the pursuit of practical and valuable robot products for the home.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Analyst', 'Customer Service', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Mechanical or Industrial Engineering', 'Computer Hardware']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['POSITION OVERVIEW: Data Analyst', 'DigiFlight, Inc., a fast growing Government contractor in Huntsville AL, is seeking a Junior/Mid-Level Data Analyst to support an active contract, working on Redstone Arsenal, Alabama. The candidate will directly support an AMCOM Project Manager and Project Office by reviewing incoming email, identify required actions, retrieve associated files, input into customer applications, and determine appropriate internal workflow processes duties. Must be proficient in the MS office software suite. Must be able to index and upload documents into a document repository. Assists customers in locating documents and associated data, to include providing one-on-one training to Project Office personnel. Reviews all correspondence to ensure they comply with AR 25-50. Determines appropriate disposition of completed actions and makes distribution using internal checklists and procedures. Analyzes and integrates data from the Project Office using a CD/DVD replicator, document scan station, CD/DVD library, and associated supplies and materials.', 'Candidate should demonstrate the ability to quickly grasp, understand and interpret key aspects of Army programs. Candidate should also be able to communicate, advise and help formulate solutions to senior Government leadership and work in a fast-paced, rapidly changing team environment, reacting quickly to changing requirements and schedules. Travel may be required (approximately 10%).', 'Qualifications', ' Current, active Secret clearance', ' Minimum of 4 years relevant experience', ' Demonstrated ability to independently act as a consultant, to set priorities, to organize tasks, monitor assignments, and ensure completion of assigned work', ' Strong capability operating Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook)', ' Basic understanding of USG acquisition process (DoD System Acquisition Life Cycle) and common documents', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Defense & Space', 'Computer Software']

Name: Market Data Services Analyst
Description: ['About Us', "Nasdaq (Nasdaq:NDAQ) is a leading global provider of trading, clearing, exchange technology, listing, information and public company services. Through its diverse portfolio of solutions, Nasdaq enables customers to plan, optimize and execute their business vision with confidence, using proven technologies that provide transparency and insight for navigating today's global capital markets. As the creator of the world's first electronic stock market, its technology powers more than 100 marketplaces in 50 countries, and 1 in 10 of the world's securities transactions. Nasdaq is home to approximately 4,000 total listings with a market value of approximately $15 trillion. To learn more, visit: http://www.nasdaq.com", 'Nasdaq Global Information Services leverages reliable, scalable technology and robust distribution channels to provide comprehensive index and market data solutions across asset classes and regions. We offer multi-asset class data sets, global infrastructure and flexible delivery methods that support clients of all sizes and types.', ' The Team ', 'The Nasdaq Market Data team is located globally with a team located in India, Europe, Philippines, and the U.S. All teams support the operations of NASDAQ’s Global Data Products. Nasdaq Global Data Products focus on creating innovative data products that provide superior market transparency to institutional, retail and individual investors, and are designed to meet industry challenges. Global Data Products is an award-winning source for market information worldwide.', 'Your Role And Responsibilities', 'The Market Data Analyst will analyze customers’ data requirements, and coordinate with market data vendors to ensure business needs are compliant with Nasdaq policies. The analyst will interact and build strong customer relationships with a variety of high profile clients as well as engage with various internal departments.', 'Completes basic, routine financial, analytical and database work relating to the company’s market data and billing systems.', 'Assists new clients on product reviews, approvals and invoicing by providing standard, preliminary information and data.', 'Contacts clients to collect delinquent reporting and payments promptly, escalating issues as needed', 'Responds to client inquiries on billing, data approval and product related questions, escalating issues as needed.', 'Works with providers and the audit team to prevent unauthorized distribution of company data.', 'Works with accounting and financial reporting team as necessary', 'Performs routine financial and data analysis.', 'Responds to basic technical and administrative inquiries, ensuring compliance with company’s entitlement, display and monthly reporting guidelines.', 'Ensures receipt of appropriate market data revenues from distributors and their subscribers through adhering to compliance activities.', 'You Will Need The Following Skills And Experience', 'Education Required: Bachelor Degree in Business or related discipline', 'Experience Required: At least 1 year', ' Excellent communication skills ', ' Ability to be organized and decisive while under pressure, when managing urgent and critical data feed and market data issues ', ' Team Player - able to interface/liaison effectively with a variety of technical/non-technical contributors throughout the organization ', ' Display’s a logical approach, critical thinking and analytical problem-solving skills with the ability to identify the root cause(s) of a problem ', ' Exceptional experience with Microsoft Office including Excel and PowerPoint ', ' Strong customer service skills ', ' And it would be great if you have experience with ', 'Proficient with Microsoft Access', 'Experience with Salesforce', 'Experience with Power BI/ Tableau', 'Sounds like you? Please follow through by clicking the “Apply” link and submitting your application. If your skills and experience are a match, we will be in touch soon, and in the meantime please visit our website and social media channels to learn more about our innovative business, inclusive culture and where a career at Nasdaq can take you.', 'Nasdaq is an equal opportunity employer. We positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of age, color, disability, national origin, ancestry, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, veteran status, genetic information or any other status protected by applicable law.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Financial Services']

Description: ['About Burning Glass', 'Burning Glass Technologies is a leading labor market analytics provider whose SaaS solutions play a growing role in closing the skills gap and informing educational needs for the workforce. S/he is able to work independently, multitask, and anticipate requests, and enjoys working in a busy, dynamic, and entrepreneurial environment.', 'Burning Glass Technologies is committed in providing equal treatment and opportunity to all individuals without regard to gender, gender identity or expression, marital status, age, race, religion, national origin, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Overview', 'Founded in 1925, CopperPoint Insurance Companies is a leading provider of workers’ compensation and commercial insurance solutions. With an expanded line of insurance products and a growing six-state footprint in the southwestern United States, CopperPoint embodies stability for policyholders in Arizona, California, Colorado, Nevada, New Mexico and Utah. CopperPoint Mutual Insurance Holding Company is the corporate parent of Arizona-based CopperPoint Insurance Companies, California-based Pacific Compensation Insurance Company and other CopperPoint Insurance Entities.', 'CopperPoint has an exciting opportunity for a Data Analyst for the Data Management division located in Phoenix, Arizona.', 'Responsibilities', ' Create modeling infrastructure and develop models for underwriting/risk selection, pricing/actuarial, finance/capital modeling and claims', ' ', ' Performs analyses of structured and unstructured data to solve moderately complex business problems, utilizing advanced statistical techniques and mathematical analyses', ' ', ' Uses data visualization to effectively communicate analytical results and support business decisions.', ' ', ' Documents projects including business objectives, data gathering and processing, detailed set of results and analytical metrics ', ' ', ' Evaluate, assess and recommend data sources and collection methods', ' ', ' Collect, Query, Cleanse, and Explore data', ' ', ' Examines and interprets large volumes of data in various forms', ' ', ' Create and maintain detailed data inventory', ' ', ' Integrates data across the organization', 'Qualifications', ' Strong analytical, problem solving and strategic thinking skills', ' ', ' Understanding of Analytical and Statistical methods, some experience with analytical software (R, Python, SAS, etc.)', ' ', ' Programming skills in Python/ R / Java or equivalent', ' ', ' Insurance industry experience, especially P&C or workers’ compensation, preferred but not required', ' ', ' Some actuarial experience, exposure or understanding preferred but not required', ' ', ' Ability to operate in fast paced environment', ' ', ' Excellent communication skills both verbally and in written form.', ' ', ' BS/BA college degree. The knowledge and skill levels acquired through undergraduate level studies especially in the areas of computer information systems, management information systems or data analytics and minimum of 2 years experience. ', 'CopperPoint’s culture of compassion extends to the community through employee volunteerism, corporate matching, Board service, program sponsorships and in-kind contributions. We empower employees by providing 12-hours of paid volunteer time annually and matching their personal contribution to the charities of their choice up to $500 per year. In 2018, CopperPoint employees reported 3,500 volunteer hours.', 'CopperPoint offers a competitive compensation package and comprehensive benefits package including major medical, dental, vision and a wide range of competitive benefits programs, generous matching contributions to your 401(k) plan, generous paid time off, tuition reimbursement and other education benefits and business casual dress. CopperPoint is an equal employment opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration without regard to race, color, sex, religion, age, national origin, disability, veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, marital status, ancestry or citizenship status, genetic information, pregnancy status or any other characteristic protected by state, federal or local law. CopperPoint maintains a drug-free workplace.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Insurance', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['About Us', "Function of Beauty was launched in January 2015, as the first truly customizable hair care offering. Our products are based on each customer's hair type and goals – everyone has unique hair; color, thickness, density, length, condition, age, and oiliness – through a careful, algorithmic process, each bottle of function of beauty shampoo, conditioner and leave-in treatment is customized to each person's needs, in their choice of color and fragrance, and printed with their name.", 'About The Role', 'We are looking for someone with a strong business mindset and proven advanced analytical skills. As a Data Scientist you will work at the intersection of strategy and data science to tackle problems and uncover business opportunities across the organization. You will report to the Vice President of Strategy and the Vice President of Engineering and collaborate closely with leadership across Product, R&D, Marketing, Operations and Engineering.', "What You'll Do", ' ', 'Work with complex datasets across our rich and varied platforms to perform analysis and design predictive models', ' ', 'Use data to discover business insights, uncover new opportunities, provide recommendations and influence decisions', ' ', 'Deepen our understanding of pattern/trends in customer behavior, support customer experience', ' ', 'optimization and improve both acquisition and retention', ' ', 'Work cross-functionally to ensure access to useful data and drive value creation', ' ', 'Promote a data-driven organization and empower teams with actionable data and with automated and intuitive KPI dashboards', ' ', 'Support our A/B testing activities in conjunction with the Engineering team', ' ', 'Constantly look for improvements in tools, data sources, data quality, and analytic techniques; build structure and process around data science initiatives and requests.', ' ', 'Who You Are', ' ', "You have a bachelor's degree in a quantitative field (math, data science, computer science, economics), Graduate degree a plus", ' ', 'You are an expert with MySQL and have experience with industry leading business intelligence tools, such as Mode, Periscope, Tableau, or Looker. Knowledge of Python is a plus', ' ', 'You have experience with creating and managing data warehouses, as well as the ETL/ELT work flow', ' ', 'You have 3+ years of experience in solving business problems by leveraging large datasets', ' ', 'Direct to Consumer startup experience a plus', ' ', 'You have proven ability to think creatively, solve strategic problems, learn quickly, work independently, handle ambiguity and clearly communicate results in a business-oriented manner', ' ', "You'll Love Working At Function Of Beauty Because", ' ', 'We care about our team members as people. We offer insurance coverage (health, vision, and dental), tax savings for retirement, and monthly reimbursements to incentivize you to work out.', ' ', 'Discounted products', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Computer Software', 'Consumer Goods']

Name: Data Informatics Analyst
Description: ['You could say Brightree by ResMed is a technology company. And that’s true. But Brightree is, at its heart, about people. Brightree helps streamline processes, improve efficiency, and increase profitability. For over fifteen years, organizations big and small have put their trust in us—for our wide-ranging solutions, our leadership, and our unmatched customer service. Going to work each day and creating new ways to positively impact our customers’ businesses and the lives of patients is just what we do. reporting and analytics as requested', 'Effectively communicate with internal and external customers in non-technical language', 'Identify and communicate the potential for enhanced business domain-specific data marts for consumption by analytic processes, reporting, and BI tools.', 'Ensure security and availability of information for our analytics consumers.', 'Collaborate effectively with stakeholders and subject matter experts to define and interpret requirements in non-technical language.', 'Be a key contributor in democratizing Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence innovation initiatives.', 'Leverage data to identify trends and patterns to articulate ROI for Brightree products and services.', 'Deliver Ad Hoc reporting and analytics as needed.', 'Commit to timelines and exceed customer expectations.', "Let's Talk About Skills And Qualifications", '2+ years experience', 'Passionate about people, learning, data, and creating business impact.', 'Fascinated by data and find reward in the analysis of business data/metrics to identify trends and implement solutions.', 'Creative, analytic problem solver with diligent attention to detail.', 'Excellent verbal and written communication skills.', 'Ability to collaborate on solutions and develop successful business partner relationships at all levels of an organization', 'Exposure to data management technologies including SQL Databases, data warehouses, data lakes, data marts, and NoSQL data stores.', 'Experience writing T-SQL and performance tuning queries.', 'Experience working with BI Tools (such as Tableau, Power BI, Sisense)', 'Experience with Sisense strongly preferred', 'Experience working with cloud technologies (Azure) a plus.', 'Experience in programming/scripting languages a plus; such as R, Python, NodeJS, AngularJS, VueJS, and .NET core.', 'Experience in Healthcare IT a plus.', "Bachelor's degree in any technology discipline, or equivalent experience.", 'Joining us is more than saying “yes” to making the world a healthier place. It’s discovering a career that’s challenging, supportive and inspiring. Where a culture driven by excellence helps you not only meet your goals, but also create new ones. We focus on creating a diverse and inclusive culture, encouraging individual expression in the workplace and thrive on the innovative ideas this generates. If this sounds like the workplace for you, apply now!', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Other', 'Industries', 'Computer Software', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Medical Devices']

Name: Jr. Counterterrorism Data Exploitation Analyst
Description: ['Job Description ', ' BAE Systems is seeking to hire multiple Jr. Counterterrorism Data Exploitation Analysts to help support counterterrorism intelligence integration on a multifaceted U.S. Government program. The ideal Jr. Counterterrorism Data Exploitation Analyst will leverage numerous analytic tools and databases to evaluate information that bolsters the U.S. Government’s response to and prevention of potential threats to the homeland and interests abroad.', 'Jr. Counterterrorism Data Exploitation Analysts are responsible for identifying, gathering, and extracting identity-based intelligence information that enhances and enriches data repositories. Jr. Counterterrorism Data Exploitation Analysts will be responsible for addressing intelligence gaps and data validation pertaining to terrorist identity records.', 'Typical Education & Experience ', 'Typically a High School Diploma and 4 years work experience or equivalent experience', 'Required Skills and Education ', 'Excellent reading comprehension skills', 'Experience with MS Office suite', 'Detail-oriented with a proficiency for researching, analyzing, and prioritizing intelligence reports and cables', 'Ability to work with IC tools and databases', 'Strong problem-solving, analytic, and written and oral communication skills', 'Excellent attention to detail and ability to accurately follow SOPs', 'Ability to work shift work/extended hours', 'Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to work well both independently and in a team environment', 'Preferred Skills and Education ', ' BA/BS degree ', ' Demonstrated knowledge of intelligence analysis and experience with synthesizing large amounts of data ', ' Familiarity with analytic tools ', ' Proficiency with software applications/databases used in support of research and analysis for the U.S. Government ', 'tno1', 'About BAE Systems Intelligence & Security ', 'BAE Systems Intelligence & Security, based in McLean, Virginia, designs and delivers advanced defense, intelligence, and security solutions that support the important missions of our customers. Our pride and dedication shows in everything we do—from intelligence analysis, cyber operations and IT expertise to systems development, systems integration, and operations and maintenance services. Knowing that our work enables the U.S. military and government to recognize, manage and defeat threats inspires us to push ourselves and our technologies to new levels. That’s BAE Systems. That’s Inspired Work. Equal Opportunity Employer/Females/Minorities/Veterans/Disabled/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity/Gender Expression. To see Inspired Work in action, visit www.baesystems.com and follow us on Facebook: www.facebook.com/baesystemsintel.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Defense & Space', 'Computer Software']

ability to identify and explain any insights or patterns within them', ' ', 'Strong expertise in designing, developing, and implementing reports, visualizations and dashboards', ' ', 'Knowledge of database design techniques and advanced SQL and NoSSQL skills', ' ', 'Proven skills in Business Intelligence analysis', ' ', 'Strong detail-orientation and excellent analytical and problem-solving skills', ' ', 'Desire to enhance development skills and research alternatives to accomplish tasks and drive innovation', ' ', 'Positive interpersonal and communication skills, including the ability to listen, ask probing questions, and ensure accurate understanding of internal client needs', ' ', 'Ability to function independently and within an agile team', ' ', 'Solid experience in exploratory data analysis and visualization', ' ', 'Experience collaborating with US Government Agencies, state or local governments, or commercial entities to develop IT service program maturity in accordance with Federal IT mandates and best practices.', ' ', 'Strong experience in ensuring customer satisfaction, problem resolution, and risk management on several medium to large projects.', ' ', 'Applicants should be able to develop application domain knowledge and provide subject matter expertise as needed over time.', ' ', 'Preferred Qualifications', ' ', 'Experience with Client Continuous Diagnostics and Mitigation (CDM) a plus', ' ', 'Experience with JSON and Unix commands a plus.', ' ', 'Experience in conducting assessments at an Enterprise by reviewing technical documentations, conducting interviews and workshops to identify gaps and developing a tailored solution is highly desired.', ' ', 'Developed data models and the ability to present to senior leadership and the client', ' ', 'Created Visualization using, Kibana. Name: Associate Data Analyst - VerityStream

Name: Data Analyst

Description: ['Summary of Duties At Thurston County Public Health and Social Services, our mission is working together to achieve the highest level of health and well-being for everyone. PHSS is inviting applications for a Data Analyst within our Treatment Sales Tax (TST) Office. The TST Office provides funding, performance measurement, and technical assistance to a range of mental health and substance use programs, including services for justice-involved individuals, youth, and families.', 'The Data Analyst is responsible for performance measurement and accountability-related activities in the Treatment Sales Tax (TST) Office. In coordination with the TST Program Manager, the incumbent will work with numerous partners to improve the quality and usefulness of performance management information related to mental health and substance abuse programs and services funded through TST. This position influences how TST funds are allocated through selection of performance measures and review of program performance.', 'The incumbent gathers and compiles data and information from various sources using a variety of methods and processes; checks for completeness, reasonableness, accuracy and comparability with other data, analyzes data; prepares a variety of summaries and reports detailing findings. Assists with development, management, implementation, planning and analysis of data projects. Develops and maintains tools to track performance data. Prepares tables, charts, graphs, statistical reports, and data visualizations. Assists and performs assessment, program evaluation, and statistical analyses. Provides timely and accurate responses to requests for information. Provides recommendations for improving data collection, analysis and reporting. Assists with meeting coordination, facilitation, and follow up.', 'While focused on Treatment Sales Tax, the Data Analyst may participate in a variety of other data-related projects and activities within Thurston County Public Health and Social Services.
