Name: Research Data Analyst
Description: ['General Summary/Purpose', 'About The MCH India Center', 'The Maternal and Child Health Center in India seeks to support efforts to achieve the child health-related United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) in India. The Center will focus on accelerating the introduction and effective implementation of existing child health interventions in India, with a particular focus on vaccine-preventable diseases and difficult-to-reach populations. Building public health capacity in India, and in West Bengal in particular, is a key outcome of this partnership. Model programs developed and established in West Bengal can be scaled up to other states and the entire country. The proposed approach is based on knowledge translation principles, which harnesses the strength of scientific evidence to inform health policy and practice.', 'Specific Duties & Responsibilities', 'The Research Data Analyst will oversee and manage research projects for the MCH India Center as well as research pilot grants extended to faculty outside of the Center. The position will Make important design and data collection methodology recommendations. Have primary responsibility for data collection, cleaning, management analysis, interpretation, and reporting. This includes the development and testing of data collection tools, recommendations as to appropriate evaluation measures, and managing the actual data. The Research Data Analyst will also assist in overall Center functions as needed.', 'The Research Data Analyst Will', ' serve as the project manager for research projects conducted within the Center;', ' supervise graduate students and part-time staff, as needed;', ' manage the day-to-day activities of MCH India Center qualitative, quantitative and mixed-methods research studies as needed, including preparing IRB documents and reports;', ' conduct data management and oversee data cleaning, entry, and quality checks;', ' conduct basic data analysis, including linear and logistic regression;', ' prepare reports to funders;', ' assist in the development of data collection tools, such as surveys, tracking sheets, and observation checklists;', ' help draft abstracts, manuscripts, and disseminate research findings to a primarily academic audience.', ' Perform miscellaneous related duties as assigned.', 'Minimum Qualifications (Required)', "Bachelor's degree in related discipline.", ' Three (3) years of related experience', "Additional education (Master's level) may substitute for required experience, to the extent permitted by the JHU Equivalency Formula: 18 graduate degree credits may substitute for one year of experience. Additional related experience may substitute for the required education on the same basis. For jobs where equivalency is permitted, up to two years of non-related college course work may be applied towards the total minimum education/experience required for the respective job. *", 'Preferred Qualifications', "Bachelor's degree in biology, statistics, nutrition, epidemiology, global health, public health or a related field", " Masters' degree in epidemiology, public health, global health or a related field.", ' At least one (1) year of experience coordinating global health, maternal and child health and vaccine related research projects', ' Experience in quantitative data analysis', 'Special Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities', ' Strong analytic skills including knowledge of research evaluation & data management', ' Experience with the Indian Healthcare System', ' Ability to work well with a range of partner organizations', ' Ability to travel to India and flexible times for teleconferences - would be preferred', ' Excellent project management and organizational skills', ' Outstanding oral and written communication skills', ' Proficiency in MS Office Suite', ' Working knowledge of a statistical software package, such as SAS, STATA, SPSS or R', ' Must be able to work independently in a fast-paced environment and meet project deadlines.', ' Must be self-directed with a team orientation.', ' Ability to speak/understand Hindi and Bengali is a bonus.', 'Classified Title: Research Data Analyst', 'Working Title: Research Data Analyst', 'Role/Level/Range: ACRP/04/MC', 'Starting Salary Range: $44,749 - $61,610/ commensurate with experience', 'Employee group: Full Time', 'Schedule: Monday-Friday 8:30a.m -5p.m/', 'Exempt Status: Exempt', 'Location: 05-MD:School of Public Health', "Department name: 60000552-IH - Int'l Vaccine Access Center (IVAC)", 'Personnel area: School of Public Health', 'The successful candidate(s) for this position will be subject to a pre-employment background check.', 'If you are interested in applying for employment with The Johns Hopkins University and require special assistance or accommodation during any part of the pre-employment process, please contact the HR Business Services Office at jhurecruitment@jhu.edu. For TTY users, call via Maryland Relay or dial 711.', 'The following additional provisions may apply depending on which campus you will work. Your recruiter will advise accordingly.', 'During the Influenza ("the flu") season, as a condition of employment, The Johns Hopkins Institutions require all employees who provide ongoing services to patients or work in patient care or clinical care areas to have an annual influenza vaccination or possess an approved medical or religious exception. Failure to meet this requirement may result in termination of employment.', 'The pre-employment physical for positions in clinical areas, laboratories, working with research subjects, or involving community contact requires documentation of immune status against Rubella (German measles), Rubeola (Measles), Mumps, Varicella (chickenpox), Hepatitis B and documentation of having received the Tdap (Tetanus, diphtheria, pertussis) vaccination. This may include documentation of having two (2) MMR vaccines; two (2) Varicella vaccines; or antibody status to these diseases from laboratory testing. Blood tests for immunities to these diseases are ordinarily included in the pre-employment physical exam except for those employees who provide results of blood tests or immunization documentation from their own health care providers. Any vaccinations required for these diseases will be given at no cost in our Occupational Health office.', 'Equal Opportunity Employer', 'Note: Job Postings are updated daily and remain online until filled.', 'EEO is the Law', 'Learn More', 'https://www1.eeoc.gov/employers/upload/eeoc_self_print_poster.pdf', 'School of Public Health - East Baltimore Campus', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Research', 'Analyst', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Nonprofit Organization Management', 'Financial Services', 'Hospital & Health Care']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Overview ', 'GSA National, an AssuredPartners company, has been helping government contractors ensure compliance and streamline costs since 1991 by providing consulting, compliance and administrative outsource services to the industry’s leading contractors. We specialize in the design, management, and administration of employee benefit programs for government contractors.', 'GSA National is looking for a Data Analyst, with 2 - 4 years of experience, to join our team in Fairfax, VA. This position will expose the candidate to innovative benefits technology designed and built by GSA National and its technology partners.', 'The ideal candidate for this position is a problem solver. As a Data Analyst, you will use your knowledge, skills, and abilities to solve organizational information challenges and will use your critical thinking skills to identify client requirements and translate those into detailed instructions for your internal and external team to execute. The ideal Data Analyst also has strong writing and communication skills and can build relationships with both their team members and client stakeholders.', 'The Data Analyst will perform a variety of critical tasks to support the day-to-day operations of a senior executive. You will closely work with Client Account Managers, Benefits Information Specialists, Sales, and Finance team members.', 'Responsibilities', ' Elicitation, organization, translation, analysis and prioritization of both business level and functional requirements. ', ' Assisting with strengthening existing client relationships and developing new business opportunities by participating in client or prospect meetings and working on proposals. ', 'Qualifications', ' Bachelor’s degree ', ' 2-4 years’ work experience ', ' Fluency in Microsoft Office suite (Outlook, Excel, Word, PowerPoint, Visio, etc.) ', ' Possessing knowledge, some experience, and capabilities in the development of solutions, recommendations or outcomes is a plus. ', ' Demonstrated leadership, analytical, organization, interpersonal, communication skills, and highly developed Microsoft Suite skills required. ', ' Ability to provide exceptional client service, research and resolve issues, and demonstrated commitment to continuous learning. ', ' Ability to work on multiple projects simultaneously.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'General Business', 'Information Technology', 'Consulting', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Insurance']

Name: Data Support Analyst
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['About Cubist', 'Cubist Systematic Strategies is one of the world’s premier investment firms. The firm deploys systematic, computer-driven trading strategies across multiple liquid asset classes, including equities, futures and foreign exchange. The core of our effort is rigorous research into a wide range of market anomalies, fueled by our unparalleled access to a wide range of publicly available data sources.', 'Job Description', 'We are passionate about data. We collaborate to build elegant, effective, scalable and highly reliable solutions to empower predictive modelling in finance.', 'Cubist’s Data Services group is looking for a Data Support Analyst to join our dedicated team. Our group is responsible for the timely delivery of comprehensive and error-free data to some of the most demanding and successful systematic Portfolio Managers in the world.', 'This exceptional individual will be a member of a small team of Data Scientists and Analysts who play a vital role in ensuring the smooth day-to-day implementation of a large research infrastructure, and the live production trading of billions of dollars of capital across global capital markets, including equities, futures, options and other financial instruments.', 'Job Responsibilities', 'Provide day-to-day support for various operational procedures', 'Project lifecycle management to help the team support PM teams seamlessly', 'Manage calendar and conference call schedule, make appointments, organize meetings and occasionally take and maintain meeting minutes', 'Assist Data team with interoffice travel arrangements, expenses etc.', 'Assist in organizing presentations', 'Interact with vendors on a daily basis', 'Coordinate with compliance team and legal team on new vendor trial/subscription process ', 'Assist with collecting and maintaining overviews and vendor content offering', 'Download trial datasets from vendor FTP sites or other delivery mechanism', 'Desirable Candidates', 'Bachelor’s degree required.', 'Strong PowerPoint, Visio, Word, and Excel skills. Access is a plus.', 'Financial industry experience preferred but not required.', 'Strong oral and written communication skills.', 'Excellent interpersonal skills; we seek a demonstrated ability to build relationships both internally and externally.', 'Attention to detail and a love of process.', 'Ability to exercise sound judgment in assessing and determining how to handle queries, calls and issues.', 'Ability to independently manage multiple long-term and short-term projects simultaneously.', 'Point72 is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Point72 is committed to the principles of equal employment opportunity for all employees and applicants for employment. Point72 complies with applicable, local, state and federal laws on the subject of equal employment opportunity.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['About Us', "CredSimple is a New York-based startup laser-focused on improving healthcare infrastructure with revolutionary technology.Instead of conducting a series of manual steps built on tedious data-entry, our platform automates the credentialing process and streamlines it from a three-month period to a matter of days. We're in it to have a profound, long-term impact and fundamentally change the way this critical part of the U.S. healthcare system works.", 'Mission', 'The mission of a data analyst @ CredSimple is to create and productize actionable insights from our data for both our clients and our internal teams. Develop strong relationships across the product, engineering, operations, and client success teams in order to deeply understand the data and the needs of our internal and external clients.', 'Outcomes', ' ', 'Support internal reporting and Business Intelligence needs', ' ', 'In the first six months, eliminate all manual reporting that the Client Success team does. Replace with automated professional reports that are user-friend and action-oriented data.', ' ', 'Find opportunities based on client requests for new data and analytics-driven products.', ' ', 'Standardize the library of internal operational reports into always-on dashboards that give insights on usage, trends, as well as areas the company needs to improve. These reports should provide actionable intelligence and create a narrative with data.', ' ', 'Forecasting and modeling - Generate forecasting models using baseline data and adjust over time to enhance precision and predictive capabilities.', ' ', 'Optimization - Use our workflow data to find opportunities for process optimization. Identify parts of our workflow that take too long, or could be faster if sequenced differently.', ' ', 'Early warning system - Build dashboards and/or analyses that flag anomalies and leading indicators of problems.', ' ', ' ', 'Collecting data and setting up infrastructure:', ' ', 'Ensure that data from disparate sources is gathered, organized, and maintained for ongoing reporting. This will require working with engineering to enhance our approach to data collection and organization. Develop routines that can be automated and easily modified to streamline the process of gathering, cleaning, and making data actionable/reusable for multiple purposes. ', ' ', ' ', 'Behavioral Competencies', ' ', 'Cross-team collaboration: Collaborate across teams including engineering, sales, finance, and client success to provide reporting and/or gather information required for analysis.', ' ', "Ownership of the outcomes: Help ensure we're asking the right question before setting off to find the answer. Not just order taking.", ' ', 'Curiosity and drive: Demonstrate curiosity and a well-developed drive to find answers to questions', ' ', 'Strategic thinking: Develop a vision to extend/improve our existing analytics and reporting infrastructure', ' ', 'Qualifications', ' ', '4+ years experience in a similar Data Analyst role. ', ' ', 'Experience building reports and dashboards backed by Postgres SQL databases.', ' ', 'Expert knowledge in Tableau.', ' ', 'Expert SQL query skills.', ' ', 'Strong analytical skills and the ability to develop actionable insights from raw data.', ' ', 'How To Apply', 'Please apply directly via our website https://www.credsimple.com/careers/', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Card Data Analytics
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Lisa Pelletier', 'Lisa Pelletier', 'Senior Talent Acquisition Specialist', 'In response to our strategic plans to grow our Business Credit Card portfolio, we are adding a key role to our Card Analytics Team. We are looking for the right individual to contribute to this exciting opportunity by providing deep industry expertise within our fast growing credit card business to help some of the most influential entrepreneurs and investors launch and grow their business globally. We serve companies in the innovation space that includes hardware, software, fintech, life science, as well as premium wine clients.', 'The core responsibilities of this position are to conduct the data / reporting analytics for underwriting the bank commercial cards and managing the portfolio efficiently score card / risk model development to predict commercial card performance automation enhancement for credit decisioning and execution proper and timely data reports of portfolio management. Key to this role is the ability to creatively develop dashboard and tools to enhance automation and reporting through leveraging the current banking data and expanding the data sources /analytics, monitor the BCC card portfolio performance timely to mitigate the portfolio credit risk while helping drive card revenue growth.', 'Qualifications', 'This individual will apply industry knowledge and subject matter expertise to effectively perform the following', 'Provide in-depth credit worthiness assessment on business credit card portfolio through developing score card, risk model and algorithms to predict commercial card performance. ', 'Data analytics and symmetrical review to enhance the automation capability / procedure of our card offer underwriting / portfolio management', 'Monitor both the business credit card portfolios’ credit improvement /deterioration to take risk action proactively. Provide meaningful data analytics on card fraud management and timely execution', 'Work with all business partners (IT, vendors, Data Analytics Team) to build, maintain card dashboard', 'The role is expected to conduct commercial data daily analytics and is expected to operate independently within the oversight of the Card Product Analytics Directors. . Data management, commercial card credit analysis and excellent communication skills are required to be successful in this role.', 'This individual will also need to develop strong internal relationships and work closely in partnership with IT, Data Analytics, Credit Administration, Card Product, and Payment Operation. The right individual will have both influence and exposure to the Credit and Payment Leadership Team.', 'The position requires deep expertise in data analytics of commercial loan portfolio management, particularly over small business credit card portfolios. Experience in underwriting / managing business credit card portfolio is a plus. Understanding the venture capital / start up ecosystem is a plus.', 'BS/BA Degree in Finance, Accounting, Statistics, Math or Economics with 3+ year direct work experience in data analytics on commercial card portfolio. Demonstrated expertise in commercial credit data management and reporting are required. Master’s degree is a plus. Prefer deep experience on data management in deferent data systems, especially commercial card systems (FD, TSYS, etc.)', 'Demonstrated proficiency working with computers and Microsoft Office applications (specifically, Outlook, Excel, Visio, Word, and PowerPoint).', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Business Development', 'Consulting', 'Product Management', 'Industries', 'Banking', 'Financial Services', 'Venture Capital & Private Equity']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ["Doximity is transforming the healthcare industry. Our mission is to help doctors be more productive, informed, and connected. As a Data Analyst, you'll work within cross-functional delivery teams alongside other analysts, engineers, and product managers in discovering data insights to help improve healthcare.", 'Our team brings a diverse set of technical and cultural backgrounds and we like to think pragmatically in choosing the tools most appropriate for the job at hand.', 'About Us', ' ', 'Here are some of the ways we bring value to doctors', ' ', 'Our data stack run on Python, Snowflake, Spark, and Airflow', ' ', 'Our web applications are built primarily using Ruby, Rails, JavaScript (Vue.js), and a bit of Golang', ' ', 'We have over 350 private repositories in Github containing our applications, forks of gems, our own internal gems, and open-source projects', ' ', "We have worked as a distributed team for a long time; we're currently about 65% distributed", ' ', 'Find out more information on the Doximity engineering blog', ' ', 'Our company core values', ' ', 'Our recruiting process', ' ', 'Our product development cycle', ' ', 'Our on-boarding & mentorship process', ' ', "Here's How You Will Make An Impact", ' ', 'Collaborate with a team of product managers, analysts and other developers to define and complete data projects from data ingestion, to analysis to recommendations.', ' ', 'Show off your engineering skills by creating data products from scratch and automating code so they can be re-used continually.', ' ', "Leverage Doximity's extensive datasets to identify and classify behavioral patterns of medical professionals on our platform.", ' ', 'Play a key role in creating both product and client-facing analytics.', ' ', 'Grow into a presentation/communication-focused role or dive deeper into more-involved technical challenges - the choice is yours.', ' ', 'About You', ' ', 'B.S. or M.S. in quantitative field with 2-4 years of experience.', ' ', 'Working knowledge of statistics and visualization.', ' ', 'Expert SQL skills with proven ability to create and to evaluate complex SQL statements involving numerous tables and complex relationships.', ' ', 'Fluent in Python and experience using common modules (numpy, pandas, statsmodels, matplotlib) for EDA.', ' ', 'Understanding of Object Oriented principles and testing as it relates to Data and Python.', ' ', 'Comfortable with UNIX command line interface and standard programming tools (vim/emacs, git, etc.)', ' ', 'Excellent problem solving skills and a strong attention to detail.', ' ', 'Ability to manage time well and prioritize incoming tasks from different stakeholders.', ' ', 'Fast learner; curiosity about and passion for data.', ' ', 'Preferred Qualifications:', ' ', 'Experience with Amazon Web Services products (EC2, S3, Snowflake).', ' ', 'Prior exposure to workflow management tools (Airflow).', ' ', 'Prior exposure to machine learning techniques (regressors, classifiers, etc).', ' ', 'Experience leveraging Apache Spark to perform analyses or process data.', ' ', ' ', 'Benefits', ' ', 'Doximity has industry leading benefits. For an updated list, see our career page', ' ', 'More info on Doximity', 'We’re thrilled to be named the Fastest Growing Company in the Bay Area, and one of Fast Company’s Most Innovative Companies. Joining Doximity means being part of an incredibly talented and humble team. We work on amazing products that over 70% of US doctors (and over one million healthcare professionals) use to make their busy lives a little easier. We’re driven by the goal of improving inefficiencies in our $3.5 trillion U.S. healthcare system and love creating technology that has a real, meaningful impact on people’s lives. To learn more about our team, culture, and users, check out our careers page, company blog, and engineering blog. We’re growing steadily, and there’s plenty of opportunity for you to make an impact.', 'Doximity is proud to be an equal opportunity employer, and committed to providing employment opportunities regardless of race, religious creed, color, national origin, ancestry, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, genetic information, marital status, sex, gender, gender identity, gender expression, pregnancy, childbirth and breastfeeding, age, sexual orientation, military or veteran status, or any other protected classification. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Description: ['Position Details Position Information Recruitment/Posting Title Data Analyst', 'Job Category Staff & Executive - Research (Laboratory/Non-Laboratory)', 'Department Center for State Health Policy', 'Overview', 'Rutgers Center for State Health Policy ( CSHP ), with a mission to inform, support and stimulate sound and creative state health policy in New Jersey and around the nation, is recruiting two highly skilled, full-time data analysts who will be assigned to work within the NJ Division of Medical Assistance & Health Services (DMAHS or Medicaid) Business Intelligence Unit ( BIU ) located in Hamilton Township, NJ. This arrangement builds on a long standing and productive relationship between CSHP and NJ Medicaid, and presents a unique opportunity for qualified analysts who desire to work with large and complex health care data systems and seek the broad technical and policy experience gained from working with colleagues in both an academic environment and a state government program.', 'Posting Summary', 'Rutgers, The State University of New Jersey, is seeking a Data Analyst for The Center for State Health Policy. This position works and trains under the direction of leadership within the Business Intelligence Unit ( BIU ), and the Assistant Director of Data Management at the Center for State Health Policy. The Data Analyst assists in the development, staffing, and operations of the BIU , expanding the current data analytic capabilities of NJ Division of Medical Assistance & Health Services ( DMAHS ) and enabling the rapid identification of emerging trends in enrollment, eligibility, service utilization, and other information needed to gain actionable intelligence on ways to improve the quality and efficiency of health care services delivered to clients within the NJ FamilyCare program.', 'Among the key duties of this position are the following:', 'Engages in detailed research projects undertaken at the request of the DMAHS Director/Assistant Commissioner or senior management to inform the future direction of the NJ FamilyCare program;', 'Participates in the development of business intelligence tools to support the Office of Business Intelligence, including interactive dashboards, slide presentations, standardized queries for various performance metrics, and other business intelligence deliverables;', 'Develops ad-hoc reports from the States data warehouse in response to requests for information made pursuant to the Open Public Records Act, press inquiries, and inquiries from various sources within State government, including for example, individuals from DMAHS , other DHS divisions (including DHS senior management), Department of Health, Department of Treasury, Department of Children and Families, and the Office of the Governor, provided that only HIPAA safe harbor de-identified information can generally be provided outside of DMAHS ;', 'Supports the Office of Business Intelligence and the States data warehouse in the linking of various data sets that may be useful for developing methods of healthcare quality improvement and cost containment in NJ FamilyCare; and', 'Provides assistance to various DMAHS business units in performing statistical sampling required by state or federal law or statute.', 'Performs tasks under general supervision and may be assigned a specific area of responsibility.', 'Position Status Full Time', 'Hours Per Week', 'Daily Work Shift', 'FLSA Exempt', 'Grade 06', 'Position Salary', 'Annual Minimum Salary prioritize and manage multiple projects and deadlines.', 'Ability to exercise sound judgement in making critical decisions.', 'Possess strong data hygiene skills with an understanding of best practices for validating own programs and output as well as being able to replicate and validate the work of other analysts.', 'Ability to establish and maintain productive and successful relationships with the appropriate agencies and external DMAHS vendors with regard to information processing requirements.', 'Knowledge of the development and maintenance of systems documentation within an academic or government agency setting.', 'Proven ability to work with the processes and technologies of other large administrative health and financial data.', 'Experience building NCQA Name: Data Analyst I
Description: ['Who is Cenlar?', 'You are.', 'Employee-owners have made Cenlar one of the nation’s largest mortgage subservicers. We have achieved success by empowering people with company ownership, real programs that provide avenues for advancement, and a great atmosphere that makes everyone look forward to the workday. Get your share of our success by considering the opportunity to join our team as a Data Analyst I.', 'Job Summary', 'Responsible for working with large and complex data sets (both internal and external data) to evaluate, recommend, and support the implementation of business strategies. Identifies and compiles data sets using a variety of tools (e.g. SQL, Access) to help predict, improve, and measure the success of key business to business outcomes. Responsible for documenting data requirements, data collection/processing/cleaning, and exploratory data analysis; which may include utilizing statistical models/algorithms and data visualization techniques. Incumbents in this role may often be referred to as Data Scientists.', 'Responsibilities', ' ', ' Day-to-day actions are focused on administering defined procedures, analysis and report preparation. ', ' ', ' Commands knowledge of data elements across the enterprise and industry – definitions, lineage and usage ', ' ', ' Executes creation of tabular operational reports and aggregation reports with medium to high complexity. We formed in April 2017, when Danone acquired WhiteWave Foods and united two companies in North America with a shared commitment to purpose, growth, and good food. Some of our loved & trusted brands include Dannon, Activia, Horizon Organic, Happy Family, International Delight, Silk, Vega, Oikos, Light & Fit, So Delicious Dairy Free, Stok, Two Good, Wallaby Organic, Left Field Farms, Good Plants Diary Free, Yo Crunch, Evian & Nutricia. And our benefits aren't too shabby either -- think flexible (unlimited) time off & up to 26 weeks of paid parental leave to name a couple!", 'Please join us in nourishing lives & inspiring a healthier world through food!', 'Learn more @ www.danonenorthamerica.com', 'About The Job', 'The Master Data Analyst will be responsible for monitoring Raw Materials, packaging materials, finish goods, vendor and customer master data with the purpose of improving data quality and timing. data creation process improvement', ' Identify, troubleshoot, and correct master data issue', ' Provide guidance for master data maintenance to cross functional teams responsible for entry of key Name: Data Analyst
Location: New York, New York, United States
Description: ['PeerIQ is transforming the way lending and securitization markets work. Meeting the needs across the credit funding cycle – from loan purchasing to financing to securitization – we work with industry leaders to unlock capital at scale. We aim to bridge the gap between originators and the capital markets so that investors can invest with confidence. Our employees come from the technology and financial sectors, combining the best of both to change the game of consumer credit.', 'PeerIQ is looking for a multi-talented, intellectually curious and process-minded Data Analyst with an in-depth understanding and hands-on experience supporting data processing routines (ETL processes) and validation of data quality. As such, you will play a key role in orchestrating and automating the data ingestion pipeline to make it more flexible while maintaining a high level of quality. You will also be expected to perform ad-hoc data analysis and data investigations and interact with internal teams and clients in order to resolve data issues. The ideal candidate will have worked in a data operations/analyst , preferably at an investment bank or asset manager as part of a fixed income operations/risk management team, role and will have a solid understanding of consumer credit and related securitized products.', 'You must have a strong sense of data ownership, passion for technology and automation, self-starter, and thrive in a fast paced, unstructured startup environment.', 'Responsibilities', 'Partner closely with data engineering to build highly configurable, scalable, robust data processing infrastructure and applications ', 'Build intuitive dashboards to empower other team members with actionable data', 'Provide analytical support to Client Delivery team with data onboarding for new clients and adhoc data analysis', 'Receive, inspect, validate, transform, clean, and load data received in a variety of formats (e.g., Excel, CVS, XML) from a variety of sources using various open-source applications (eg. Jupyter Notebook, PyCharm etc)', 'Identify erroneous or anomalous data and take action to correct or remove errors in order to restore data sets to reliable levels', 'Document process and methodology', 'Qualifications', 'B.S. in Business, Finance, Economics or related degree, with a demonstrated interest in fixed income markets', '2-3 years of experience working in leading financial institutions in an operations or risk management role, preferably dealing with large datasets', 'Working knowledge of corporate banking and capital market products', 'Experience working with a broad set of data integration technologies and databases', 'High proficiency with advanced Microsoft Excel ', 'Decent proficiency with Python and SQL ', 'Proficient skills in standard concepts, best practices, and procedures in designing data visualizations', 'Excellent verbal communication skills and attention to detail', 'Demonstrate sense of urgency in maintaining data integrity and experience automating recurring analyses', 'Strong work ethic', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Financial Services']

Name: Data Analyst Consultant, Asset Management
Location: Washington, District of Columbia, United States
Description: ['Job Description', ' The Company ', "WSP USA, is one of the world's leading engineering and professional services firms, dedicated to serving our clients. With nearly 7,000 people in 100 offices across the U.S., we partner with our clients to help communities prosper.", 'Our Asset Management and Business Advisory practice brings internationally recognized leadership to the USA critical infrastructure sectors – driving organization and asset performance, reducing risks and managing whole life costs of the assets we depend on every day.', ' The Role ', 'We are seeking a dynamic, detail-oriented, self-motivated Data Analyst to both support and drive continued growth in our digital services. You will join an established team that is a leader in providing asset management and business advisory services across the country and beyond.', 'We are looking for self-starters who can contribute to our success. The Data Analyst will have experience establishing databases and data structures, and working with applications including GIS, Excel, SQL and other data modeling tools to support business decision making. Ideally the individual will have experience in managing large data sets and will be familiar with the quality control requirements associated with transitioning and cleansing data.', 'We are looking for forward thinkers who can help grow our digital services. Individuals with interest or knowledge in data analytics, machine learning, and AI will thrive well in the environment we are creating.', 'It is preferred that the individual has experience in the critical infrastructure sectors – transportation, water and power utilities – but we will consider applicants with experience and knowledge in both commercial, military, manufacturing, facilities and other sectors.', 'Primary Roles And Responsibilities', ' ', 'Can work within a multi-disciplinary team to support, and/or lead the delivery of complex consulting projects across sectors – with a particular focus on the infrastructure verticals', ' ', 'Independently perform data collection, cleansing/transitioning and analytical processes and produce high quality reports. Understanding of QA/QC measures for data governance and able to support implementation of such measures both internally and with clients.', ' ', 'Actively contributes to and able to engage with clients (both internally and externally)', ' ', 'Job Requirements', 'Required Attributes', ' ', 'Bachelor’s degree in relevant field, with graduate degree preferred', ' ', '5+ years’ experience in directly relevant endeavors', ' ', 'Proven experience in consulting or a comparable role in an organization where the individual has held a role responsible for managing data, information or the deployment of technologies to manage assets.', ' ', 'Strong interpersonal skills and high emotional IQ - A strong team player who can get things done, can provide leadership when needed or be led when required.', ' ', 'A good understanding of infrastructure and a working knowledge of how to structure data systems for effective use.', ' ', 'A good understanding of technologies used to support data and information management – including GIS, Excel, SQL, Oracle.', ' ', 'Preferably an understanding of Enterprise Asset Management Systems – including Maximo, Infor and other systems.', ' ', 'Familiarity with national and international practices and standards', ' ', 'An ability to share knowledge informally and formally and coach and support more junior consultants.', ' ', 'Must have authorization to immediately work in the United States', ' ', ' Location ', 'The asset management team works nationally and the candidate should be available to travel. The preferred home location for this posting is in Washington, DC.', 'About WSP USA', "WSP USA is the U.S. operating company of one of the world's leading engineering and professional services firms. Dedicated to serving local communities, we are engineers, planners, technical experts, strategic advisors and construction management professionals. WSP USA designs lasting solutions in the transportation, buildings, energy, water and environment sectors. With nearly 9,500 people in 150 offices across the U.S., we partner with our clients to help communities prosper. www.wsp.com/usa", 'WSP provides a comprehensive suite of benefits including medical, dental, vision, disability, life, and retirement savings focused on a providing health and financial stability throughout the employee’s career.', 'At WSP, we want to give our employees the challenges they seek to grow their careers and knowledge base. Your daily contributions to your team will be a key piece in our meeting client objectives, goals and challenges. Are you ready to get started?', 'As a federal contractor and recipient of federal funds, WSP USA is a drug free workplace and Equal Opportunity Employer - Race/Age/Color/Religion/Sex/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity/National Origin/Disability or Protected Veteran Status', 'The selected candidate must be authorized to work in the United States.', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Civil Engineering']

Name: Data Analyst, Junior
Company: JDSAT Operations Research & Big Data Sciences
Description: ['JDSAT is an Operations Research and Data Sciences firm currently seeking talented analysts in fields of Operations Research, Data Science, Engineering, Computer Science or related fields. We have unique, challenging, and immediate opportunities for dynamic and detail-oriented individuals supporting both federal and private sector clients. We are seeking people who thrive on challenge, like to work in a flexible environment, and who want their work to make a difference.', 'The ideal candidate for this position is an analytically curious and enthusiastic Data Analyst who is passionate about Data Management, Business Intelligence, Data Visualization, and the development and maintenance of data products. The Junior Data Analyst Consultant will be expected to collect technical requirements, liaise with data owners, manipulate and analyze complex data sets, and provide analysis of results that can be visualized and easily comprehended by non-technical customers. The Consultant will produce technical data analysis on several existing work streams; work with customers to evaluate new requirements; serve as a technical expert capable of clearly explaining technical methodologies in lay terms; deliver technical solutions that meet requirements; and evaluate data sets to creatively explore how they can be developed into new work streams.', 'Position is on-site in Mclean, VA, so candidate must be willing to relocate (if necessary).', 'This position requires a SECRET clearance or demonstrated ability to obtain such clearance.', 'Responsibilities', ' ', ' Work with clients, managers, and technical staff to understand business needs and translate these needs into technical models. ', ' ', ' Write and execute queries using SQL. ', ' ', ' Extract, transform, integrate, and analyze data from disparate relational database management systems. ', ' ', ' Develop data models and data products using Excel, VBA, and a data science language like R or Python. ', ' ', ' Develop data visualizations based on ad hoc data analysis. Support visualization development for supply chain management tools. ', ' ', ' Assist in troubleshooting analytic tools and implementing required modifications. ', ' ', ' Assist in developing briefing products, white papers, and reports to help team communicate results. ', ' ', 'Requirements', ' Required Skills and Abilities ', ' ', ' Bachelor’s degree in a technical/quantitative field such as Operations Research, Data Science, Engineering, Analytics, Computer Science, Economics, Mathematics, Statistics, or similar. ', ' ', ' Minimum (1) year experience in a relevant field, as described above. ', ' ', ' Strong experience implementing SQL queries to extract and transform data for ad hoc analysis. ', ' ', ' Strong experience developing data analysis products and models using Excel and Visual Basic for Applications. ', ' ', ' Demonstrated experience in developing data visualizations for ad hoc analysis. ', ' ', ' Experienced conducting data analysis in a data science language such as R or Python. ', ' ', ' Experienced using MS Office including Word, PowerPoint, and Excel. ', ' ', ' Excellent oral and written communication skills, including demonstrated experience developing briefing slides, metric charts, and similar analytical products. ', ' ', ' Experience or demonstrated skill in integrating with a multi-functional team that includes both technical and non-technical professionals. ', ' ', ' Experience or demonstrated skill in interacting with clients in a consulting role. ', ' ', ' Familiarity and understanding of statistical modeling concepts such as linear and logistic regression. ', ' ', ' Possess or be able to obtain an active SECRET-level security clearance. ', ' ', 'Desired Skills And Abilities', ' ', ' Strong statistical foundations in predictive analytics, such as linear and logistic regression. ', ' ', ' Exposure to multi-objective optimization modeling or goal programming. ', ' ', ' Experience working with Department of Defense clients. ', ' ', ' Demonstrated experience as a consultant in a technical analysis role. ', ' ', ' ', ' Experience creating, developing, and implementing data analytics architecture, including data warehousing, data visualization, analytic modeling, and reporting. ', ' ', ' Experience creating, developing, and implementing large-scale optimization models. ', ' ', ' Experience creating, developing, and implementing large-scale agent-based and discrete event simulation. ', ' ', ' Experience building a variety of artificial intelligence models. ', ' ', ' Experience applying Robotic Process Automation to recurring analytics activities. ', ' ', ' Experience as a consultant balancing highly-technical and non-technical functional roles. ', ' ', 'Benefits', 'At JDSAT Inc., you will be joining a collaborative and energetic team with excellent career development opportunities. You will sharpen your knowledge on challenging projects with a great deal of autonomy while operating alongside other talented Operations Research and Data Science professionals. We like to cultivate our talent and promote from within by offering a variety of leadership and advancement opportunities throughout the company. We offer: above-market salaries; a competitive benefits package; a commitment to achieving the right work/life balance; and meaningful work to improve our employees and our clients.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Defense & Space', 'Computer Software', 'Management Consulting']

Name: Accounting Data Analyst
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Morgan McMahon', 'Morgan McMahon', 'Customer Success | Sr. Resource Development Manager | Recruiting & Delivery ', 'Identified as one of the top 100 fastest growing private businesses in San Diego by the SD Business Journal, HNM Systems is a rapidly growing, people-drive Communication Information and Emerging Technology staffing and consulting firm.', 'The Data Analyst Senior is responsible for providing accurate, complete and meaningful reports and analysis of financial information used for business management and decision making. The Senior Data Analyst works closely with Fiber department and/or functional managers to determine report requirements, build reports, and quality test financial results prior to distribution. The Senior Data Analyst also provides support with project management services for large data projects.', 'Essential Job Functions', '• Develops and deploys reporting and analysis that is accurate, complete and properly summarized to aid in management of business and management decision making. Responsible for extracting and summarizing data from JDE and other corporate systems.', '• Has expert knowledge of JDE tables and field usage. Has thorough knowledge of other corporate software, programs and data tools. Assists managers with report design and development. Tests reports and ensures that they perform as expected.', '• Understands flow of data internally and in relation to the General Ledger.', '• Produces weekly, monthly, and quarterly trend and activity reports as well as other operational and management reports. Ensures that reports are produced per scheduled timelines for review by functional management teams.', '• Analyzes large amounts of data and investigates and researches anomalies. Works with department and/or functional teams to correct issues when identified.', '• Works with IT Business Intelligence team to design, test and deploy MRE reports for general usage.', '• Provides support to management to produce reports and analyze large amounts of data as part of acquisitions or other special projects.', '• Produces ad-hoc reporting as assigned.', 'Education/Certifications', '• Bachelor’s Degree or equivalent experience in Business, Accounting, Finance or related field', 'Experience/Minimum Requirements', '• Accounting and Data Analytic background', '• 4+ years of schooling (Accounting will need to be part of this request)', '• Experience working with Accounting/Finance/Business end users', 'Other Skills/Abilities', '• Excellent PC skills –advanced Excel functions', '• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills', '• Ability to summarize large amounts of complex data into management reports', '• Knowledge of JDE and other data analysis and financial software and tools', '• Ability to problem solve to determine root causes of anomalies', '• Understand and write reports using various software and tools', '• Ability to manage multiple projects and priorities', '• Responds well under pressure with deadlines', 'Working Conditions: Works in a normal office setting with no exposure to adverse environmental conditions.', 'Benefits: Medical, Dental, Vision Coverage, Supplemental Insurance through Aflac, & 401K plan.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Contract', 'Job function', 'Accounting/Auditing', 'Analyst', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Telecommunications', 'Wireless', 'Information Technology and Services']

Description: ['Western Digital®', 'The next big thing in data is you!', 'Essential Duties And Responsibilities', ' Builds data pipelines to pull together Development data from Corporate cloud computing (e.g., AWS, BDP Edge) database by working with IT database engineer business counterpart; ', ' Conducts ETL (Extract, Transform & Load) to integrate, consolidate and clean data set to prepare data analysis; ', ' Identifies relevant data sets needed for wafer parametric and BE performance; ', ' Provide data visualization tool (Spotfire) and set up dashboards for R&D team’s engineering analysis; ', ' Co-work with team on data source and required parametric to applies expertise in statistics and building machine learning models to explore correlation among different group of data, makes predictions on head physical, wafer level, back end, and performance; ', ' Recommends solutions to improve wafer process, yield, efficiency and give insight for new technology understanding; ', ' Validate Data visualization and Prediction models. ', 'About Western Digital', 'The future. It’s on you. You & Western Digital.', 'We’ve been storing the world’s data for more than 50 years. Once, it was the most important thing we could do for data. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Data Analyst', "Roti Modern Mediterranean is seeking an experienced Data Analyst to help grow our data capabilities to best in class. We are looking for someone that can handle requests from business users and has a desire to grow into a more technical data engineering role in the future. This role will combine the opportunity to showcase independent thinking and mentorship to develop your skills and career further. It's ideal for someone looking to grow quickly and has a strong drive to learn new things and take on new challenges. The ideal candidate will not only have a passion for creating streamlined data processes but will also understand the best ways to visualize that data in a way that is easy for end users to understand.", "What You'll Do", ' Work with business stakeholders to define and answer ad-hoc analysis requests', ' Collaborate with data and product teams to help define data product roadmaps', ' Build automated and scalable data processes in SQL and Python', ' Identify inefficiencies and opportunities in our existing data processes', 'Required', "What we're looking for:", ' 2-4 years professional experience as a Data Analyst or similar role', ' Advanced SQL skills with the ability to write and optimize complex queries', ' Experience presenting results of Ad-Hoc analysis to stakeholders', ' Ability to explain technical data concepts to non-data users', 'Strongly Preferred', ' Experience working with Snowflake, Github, and Looker', ' 1+ years experience using Python for data analysis and automation', 'Nice To Have', ' Interest in data engineering and/or data science', ' Experience working with Airflow, Docker, AWS/Azure', 'The Perks', ' A positive work environment with an invested team', ' Competitive compensation plus annual bonus potential', ' Paid time off and company holidays', ' Medical, dental, & vision insurance and 401(k) with company match', ' Company paid disability benefits', ' All employees receive a 20% discount when they visit the restaurant with friends and family and a 10% discount on Roti catering orders', ' Employee Discount Program', 'Roti Modern Mediterranean is an Equal Opportunity Employer and participates in E Verify', "Roti is a growing fast-casual Modern Mediterranean restaurant company. Here's what we're about.", 'Food that loves you back.', 'We serve spectacular food. Food that leaves you feeling great-long after the meal is over. Fresh, flavorful, and always made with care from real, responsibly sourced ingredients.', 'People that love you back.', "Hospitality is in our DNA. That's why we hire people with an upbeat attitude and positive energy. And, we treat our team with the same integrity, kindness and friendly enthusiasm we expect for our customers.", 'An experience that loves you back.', "Every customer who experiences Roti feels the love - whether it's in our restaurants, on our app or at their place. The restaurant environment is clean, comfortable and welcoming. Lines move fast and the vibe is good. It's a delight to be there, and customers feel welcome to relax and stay awhile.", 'We hire people with upbeat attitudes, positive energy, and a passion for customer hospitality. We treat our team with the same integrity, kindness, and friendly enthusiasm. We know that to accomplish our goals, we need to attract the right people-people who care about our food and our customers; people who love a fast-paced, value-driven environment where results matter to everyone on the RoTeam.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Restaurants', 'Food & Beverages', 'Hospitality']

Name: Criminal Data Entry Analyst
Description: ['Criminal Data Entry Analyst:', ' InfoMart is a fast-growing global technology company with an established foundation of over 27 years’ experience as a US screening & data provider. Our work hard-play hard environment has been consistently recognized with best place to work awards, and our and industry-leading processes push us to the top of technology and security “best in breed” lists. InfoMart is a proven innovator with numerous first-to-market technologies and cutting edge products. We were recently the first in our industry to launch a biometric identity screening mobile application. ', ' A career at InfoMart will be a challenging and fast-paced, yet fun, community-based environment that has programs focused on healthy living, charitable giving, professional development, and more. ', 'Position Summary', 'Enter criminal record data into proprietary system', 'Essential Job Functions', 'InfoMart is a respected provider of background screening and drug testing services. We are committed to building long-term relationships with our clients by providing the most accurate and up-to-date information possible.', 'Data Analysts are relied upon to enter and submit information. The essential job functions of the position are as follows:', ' ', 'Interpretation and entry of criminal records into proprietary system.', ' ', 'May occasionally need to place telephone calls to court agencies to verify criminal history information.', ' ', 'Must possess good computer skills including Microsoft products, Outlook, and Internet research.', ' ', 'Attention to detail and analytical skills are a must.', ' ', 'Must type a minimum of 45 words per minute (WPM).', ' ', 'Maintains customer confidence and protects InfoMart operations by keeping information confidential.', ' ', 'Must be able to manually type reviewed and verified information accurately and timely.', ' ', 'Maintains operations by following policies and procedures and reporting needed changes.', ' ', 'Contributes to team efforts by accomplishing related tasks as needed.', ' ', 'Job Requirements', 'Education', 'High school diploma or equivalent.', 'Experience', 'A background in clerical/data entry and 10-key is preferred.', 'Knowledge/Skills/Abilities', 'Organization, Typing, Data Entry Skills, Attention to Detail, Confidentiality, Thoroughness, Decision Making, Independence, Analytical, Results Driven, Energy Level, Self-Starter, Quick Learner. Be a Self-Motivator, Have Excellent Written Communication Skills, Be Able to Meet Deadlines, and Be Able to Work Well Under Intense Pressure. Must Be Able to Follow Policies and Procedures Related to Job Functions.', 'Core Competencies', 'Good Reading, Writing, and Mathematical Skills; Good Verbal and Written Communication Skills; Strong Ability to Collect and Organize Information; Solid Phone and Computer Skills; Must be Comfortable Working in a Close-Knit, Team Environment Where Attitude and Work Ethic are Important.', 'Local candidates only, no relocation support available.', 'Only candidates authorized to work in the US will be considered.', 'All job applicants will undergo testing for presence of illegal drugs as a condition of employment.', 'NO PHONE CALLS OR FAXES PLEASE***', 'Seniority level', 'Not Applicable', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software']

Description: ['Manages projects and program execution of moderate complexity. Implements new program solutions and solves analytical problems that are uncommon. Determines own work priority and timelines. Set timeframes for self and team members. Allocates work and mentors new team members. Develops and implement analytical andor statistical methodologies for evaluating Operations processes, business problems, andor ROI of products and services. Identify actionable insights and recommendations to influence the direction of the business by effectively communicating results across functional groups. Name: Data and Business Insights Analyst - Content
Description: ['Job Title', 'Data and Business Insights Analyst - Content', 'Job Description', 'I. Job Summary ', '| ', 'Major goals and objectives.', 'Responsible for the strategy and execution of SEO through problem solving, strategizing, ticket creation, review/edit content, and reporting organic traffic and revenue for the Commerce businesses at Meredith.', 'The analyst will work with teams to strategize, execute, monitor, and optimize SEO throughout all Commerce businesses. The SEO Manager role will work on both content SEO and Technical SEO projects. From a content SEO perspective, this role will generate keywords, topic ideas, and competitive industry insights along with reviewing/editing content from SEO standards to increase organic traffic. From a Technical SEO perspective, this role will help determine, execute, and analyze SEO A/B tests and look for SEO opportunities or errors through Technical SEO standards. This role will work with the Product team to define and write SEO tickets as needed, participate in user acceptance testing/QA, and monitor rankings to ensure quality SEO growth. This role will take on other assignments as they present themselves.', 'Working alongside the Senior SEO Manager, the Analyst role will work on the full portfolio of Meredith commerce brands, as well as work on ecommerce platforms such as Shop Marketplace and Promo Codes. From a content SEO perspective, this role will need the ability to review and edit content for SEO standards and optimize on page items. From a Technical SEO perspective, this role will need the ability to look through code and use SEO tools to create SEO A/B tests.', 'II. Name: Genomic Data Analyst
Description: ['Company Description', 'Eurofins Scientific is an international life sciences company, providing a unique range of analytical testing services to clients across multiple industries, to make life and our environment safer, healthier and more sustainable. From the food you eat, to the water you drink, to the medicines you rely on, Eurofins works with the biggest companies in the world to ensure the products they supply are safe, their ingredients are authentic and labelling is accurate.', ' ', 'Eurofins believes it is a global leader in food, environmental, pharmaceutical and cosmetics products testing and in agroscience CRO services. It is also one of the global independent market leaders in certain testing and laboratory services for genomics, discovery pharmacology, forensics, CDMO, advanced material sciences and in the support of clinical studies. ', 'In over just 30 years, Eurofins has grown from one laboratory in Nantes, France to over 47,000 staff across a network of more than 900 independent companies in over 50 countries and operating more than 800 laboratories. Eurofins offers a portfolio of over 200,000 analytical methods to evaluate the safety, identity, composition, authenticity, origin, traceability and purity of biological substances and products, as well as providing innovative clinical diagnostic testing services, as one of the leading global emerging players in specialised clinical diagnostics testing. ', ' In 2019, Eurofins generated', ' ', 'total revenues of EUR € 4.56 billion, and has been among the best performing stocks in Europe over the past 20 years. ', 'Job Description', 'This Scientist will support processing next-generation sequencing (NGS) work for our PSS client.', 'Qualifications', 'The Ideal Candidate would possess:', 'Experience processing next-generation sequencing (NGS) data', 'Experience processing and analyzing single-cell/nuclei sequencing data', 'Experience optimizing single cell analysis pipelines', 'Experience adopting novel published computational methods for single-cell data analysis', 'Minimum Qualifications', 'BS/MS/PhD in science related discipline', 'Experience with genomics data analysis', 'Knowledge of R, Bioconductor, and python', 'Additional Information', 'Position is full -time Monday - Friday 8am -5pm with additional hours as workload requires. Name: Data Analyst
Location: Salt Lake City, Utah, United States
Description: ['Dematic is an intralogistics innovator that designs, builds and supports intelligent, automated solutions for manufacturing, warehouse and distribution environments for customers that are powering the future of commerce. With engineering centers, manufacturing facilities and service centers located in more than 25 countries, Dematic’s global network of 8,000 employees have helped achieve more than 6,000 worldwide customer installations for some of the world’s leading brands. Headquartered in Atlanta, Dematic is a member of KION Group, a global leader in industrial trucks, supply chain solutions and related services, and a leading provider of warehouse automation.', ' The Role ', 'Dematic Corp. is looking for a Solution Consultant in any of our Dematic locations across North America. The successful candidate will have 8 or more years’ experience working in supply chain, material handling, or an optimization related field . In this role, the Solution Consultant will:', ' Analyze the customer’s business information and convert into design criteria. ', ' Generate logistics/material handling ideas with potential merit to solve the customer’s business challenges. ', ' Validate that the logistics/material handling ideas have merit through financial analysis and recommend a solution to the customer. ', ' Present the solution to the decision makers and close the sale. ', 'Essential Role And Responsibilities', 'The Solution Consultant will engage with Dematic customers to analyze their business needs into innovative solutions.', ' Works on multiple projects, some with assistance from others but often conduct small to mid-sized projects without assistance. ', " Performs analysis of customers' business information and develops solutions to meet or exceed customers' requirements. ", ' Conducts or oversees the development of proposal documents. ', ' Estimates time frames, quality and quantity of resources required to successfully develop very complex solutions; develops project plans incorporating all project variables. ', ' Conducts periodic status checks with customer and team to assess progress against plan. ', ' Prepares weekly status reports on all project activities. ', ' May support pre-sales activities as needed. ', ' Collects data that accurately represents customer requirements (design criteria, flow charts, etc.). ', ' Accurately, clearly and concisely displays design requirements. ', ' Determines methodology for collecting, analyzing and summarizing data critical to design. ', ' Uses written descriptions, spreadsheets, charts, and material flow diagrams skillfully. ', ' Stay abreast of current / future operating strategies and technologies by attending industry conferences, seminars, etc. ', ' Thorough understanding of material handling technology, including software. ', ' Develops a wide range of concepts that meet or exceed the design criteria. Concepts may range from manual to fully automated solutions. ', ' To facilitate concept understanding, uses drawings and sketches skillfully. ', ' Evaluates concepts and recommends the best solution. Skilled in using evaluation techniques ranging from simple "pro and con" comparisons to sophisticated Return on Investment (ROI) calculations. ', ' Produces a Design Report that professionally summarizes the project. ', ' Thoroughly understands the practices, methodologies and requirements of the Supply Chain Solution Department and serves as advisor to all group members. ', ' May be exposed to next level of duties and responsibilities (mentoring and training). ', 'What We Are Looking For', ' Qualification Requirements ', ' Typically BS/BA in related discipline or advanced degree, where required. Certification may be required in some areas. ', ' Typically 8-10 years of successful experience working in supply chain, material handling, distribution center operations or an optimization related field and has successfully demonstrated the key responsibilities as presented above. ', ' Strong innovative and creative thinking, as evidenced in individual work ', ' High degree of proficiency in MS Office Suite (Access, Excel, Word, and PowerPoint). ', ' Excellent verbal and written communication skills. ', ' Able to multi-task and work in a high-growth, fast-paced and deadline driven environment successfully.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software']

Name: Feed Data & Analytics Specialist
Description: ['The Feed Data & Analytics Specialist position is responsible for the implementation of assigned projects to provide solutions for the business analysts within our branded feed product lines (Beef, Dairy & Aquaculture) and multiple areas of our integrated business including Sales, Customer Service, Operations, Supply Chain, and Ingredient Management & Finance. The role will provide technical expertise in planning and executing data and analytics projects including requirements gathering, implementation, testing, deployment and maintenance. Activities will include querying databases, cleansing data, aggregating data into reports and visualizations, and performing ad hoc studies and analyses as needed to provide actionable information to other analysts and for the purpose of driving better planning, measurement, and communication within CCSTNA’s Feed Products Segments.', 'Principal Accountabilities', '60% Solution Implementation Assist in requirements gathering for assigned work by attending meetings, conference calls, and participating in group planning activities. Adhering to data quality and standards and practices while implementing projects as assigned, within agreed upon timeframes. Query systems (CMMP, VOX PQDB, PI, Gamanet, Salesforce, CDP, and others) to support creation of usable data sets and use those data sets in analysis and visualizations to create solutions for the business or other analysts. Assist with the CORTX (core business processes with Salesforce) product and SAP implementation where assigned. Create and manage appropriate data collection, ETL processes, data cleansing and aggregation workflows.', '20% Evangelize Data Quality and Continuity Contribute to the creation of common data sets with governance and data quality standards. Evangelize data quality (not just expediency) across the business educating others where possible about the impact of poor- or low-quality data on the business overall. Document all work and maintain appropriate repositories to standards established by the business.', '10% Research/Training/Innovation Research and training to regularly expand skillsets as needed and apply to best serve the Feed Team data analyses. Such knowledge growth will support innovation in the business operations space. Learn about the business in depth and suggest improvements and innovations where possible.', '10% Backup & Support Responsibilities. Perform miscellaneous job-related duties and special projects as assigned working with multiple functions with the segment including: Sales, Marketing, Supply & Demand Operations, Supply Chain, Customer Service and plant operations. Required business trainings, presentations, meetings, webinars and other documents and activities as required.', 'Qualifications', 'Required', ' Bachelor’s degree in business, computer science, management information systems, engineering or related field', ' Minimum 2 years of business/technical related job experience (e.g. analytics, business information systems, I/T)', ' Strong skills with data systems, data structures and types, SQL, data manipulation, data parsing, data cleansing', ' Strong interpersonal & communication skills, written and verbal', ' Ability to manage multiple priorities', ' Ability to adapt and learn in a changing work environment', ' Self –starter with ability to work independently', ' Collaborative with the ability to interact effectively with multiple levels of the organization', ' Demonstrated ability to implement technical solutions and best practices.', ' Ability to travel up to 10%', 'Preferred', ' Experience with Salesforce.com, Tableau Desktop/Server, Alteryx Designer/Server', ' Experience with VOX, SAP,CMMP,JDE', ' Experience with DB2, iSeries, Oracle, Hadoop', ' Experience in web services and API’s', ' Multi-functional business experience (e.g. sales, customer service, supply chain, finance, I/T etc.)', ' Demonstrated 3rd party relationship & management (e.g. vendors, customers, service organizations)', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Chemicals', 'Food & Beverages', 'Food Production']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Job Openings', 'Data Analyst', ' EverCommerce - Operations ', ' Denver, Colorado', 'Department ', 'EverCommerce - Operations', 'Employment Type ', 'Full Time - US', 'EverCommerce is looking for a Data Analyst to join our team. The Data Analyst will play a crucial role supporting the VP of Strategic Planning & Analytics, General Managers, and Executive Team in a variety of projects, including KPI development, analysis and tracking; executive-level reporting/visualization; data infrastructure build across a diverse portfolio of businesses; and deep one-off operational analyses.', 'You', 'You are a collaborative, enthusiastic, high-performing individual with a “no job too small” attitude. You’re seeking a steep learning curve, driven by deadlines, and enjoy working in a fast paced, continually changing environment with other like-minded individuals. You love teams but also enjoy putting your head down and getting things done with your headphones on. You are highly self-motivated, possibly self-taught – someone that can initiate and drive projects to completion with minimal guidance because you have confidence to ask questions and work independently.', 'Us', 'EverCommerce is the leading service commerce platform, providing the top marketing, business management, and customer retention software and solutions to more than 200,000 service businesses across the globe.', 'The EverCommerce team has extensive expertise in marketing & sales, business operations, management, legal, finance, accounting, technology, and human resources that we provide as a centralized resource to drive continued growth and success of our subsidiaries. Our ecosystem enables its subsidiary B2B software companies to thrive in an environment of shared knowledge, best practices, and resources with significant cost savings.', 'Where', 'EverCommerce is currently located in the RiNo Arts District. Our collaborative, open-plan office space is filled with high-energy, talented people who enjoy our weekly lunches, dog-friendly environment and hanging with co-workers.', 'All candidates must be eligible to work in the U.S. for any employer. Please note that only local candidates will be considered for this role.', 'Core Responsibilities', ' ', 'Own the day-to-day processes and infrastructure for the collection, reporting, and analysis of operational KPIs across a large portfolio operating businesses. Responsible for processing, cleansing, and verifying the integrity of data used for analysis. ', ' ', "Develop an understanding of each operating business's role within the larger EverCommerce organization; maintain an advanced knowledge of their data quality, reference (definitions, sources), and needs.", ' ', 'Increase the efficiency of old business processes and aid in the development of new business processes to continually improve data collection processes, integrity, and reliability.', ' ', 'Own and track in-year forecasting drivers for each EverCommerce operating business, providing ongoing updates and guidance/revision/interpretation to both EverCommerce (FP&A, CorpDev teams) and field leadership.', ' ', 'Establish analytics and decision support capability that enables the business teams to make data-driven decisions driving acquisition growth and customer monetization and retention.', ' ', 'Own various special data-focused projects to support planning/forecasting, ongoing operations, and corporate development, as necessary.', ' ', 'Serve as key executional resource and liaison between EverCommerce business/financial leadership and field leadership team to drive completion of annual subsidiary budgeting process.', ' ', 'Extract and manipulate data from a variety of systems and offline reporting for use reporting, utilizing cloud-based and/or on-premise analytics tools to analyze data, as necessary.', ' ', 'Exercise inquisitive mindset to transform business questions into actionable data exploration exercises, as well as take reported data and shape it into actionable business questions.', ' ', 'Convey insights into effective presentations that are outcome- and action-oriented.', ' ', 'Experience And Skills', ' ', 'Bachelor’s degree in Business, Finance, Computer/Data Science, or other related field with a top-tier academic background, or equivalent experience', ' ', '2-5 years of post-undergraduate relevant work experience in a highly analytical environment; SaaS, payments, and/or technology industry experience preferred', ' ', 'Advanced knowledge of Excel and data modeling', ' ', 'Demonstrated experience with creating reports, dashboards, and summarizing large amounts of data into actionable intelligence to drive business decisions', ' ', 'Outstanding written and verbal communication skills.
