Name: Data Analyst (Python)
Description: ['Methods+Mastery Dallas is seeking a Data Analyst who is passionate about data-driven intelligence with an interest in data engineering. We’re looking for an entrepreneurial analyst who has professional experience conducting quantitative analyses using Python and pulling data from disparate sources via APIs to create rich datasets. ', 'Our new Junior Data Analyst will work directly with members of the multi-disciplinary Methods+Mastery team to produce work for top clients in an entrepreneurial and collaborative environment that values team above all. This work will include assisting our Data Scientist in building out data pipelines, and analyzing data using Python to deliver reports, actionable insights, and strategic recommendations for our clients. ', 'Methods+Mastery offers a fast-paced environment that encourages personal and professional growth and the opportunity to have a panoramic view of Dallas–34 floors up to be exact. We work on projects ranging from regional to global in scope for some resume bolstering brands. You’ll have the opportunity to contribute against the full spectrum of communication mediums and disciplines including interactive, mobile, social, advertising, branding, experiential, video, motion, presentations, environmental and print. ', 'Methods+Mastery is an entrepreneurial, collaborative environment that values talented, creative people who like to work with others to create cutting-edge programs for our clients. ', 'We believe a diverse team brings a wider range of personal and professional experiences and perspectives, and we recognize that diversity and inclusion benefit our agency, our clients, and the communities in which we work and live. To that end, we strongly encourage applications from women, people of color, members of the LGBTQ community, veterans, and individuals with disabilities. ', ' ', '\xa0 ', 'Responsibilities:', ' ', 'Support the development of data science products by helping to build data pipelines using cloud computing and APIs ', 'Conduct quantitative analyses in Python using packages such as Pandas, Scikit-Learn, and NLTK ', 'Develop insights and strategies from data pulled through social analytics tools, digital analytics tools, primary & secondary market research and business analysis and competitive data; translate those insights into creative marketing strategies; transform consumer insights into reports and strategic plans. ', 'Work closely with planning, creative and social media team members to develop audience-centric, KPI-driven content campaigns that inspire audiences and influence beliefs and behaviors. ', 'Package and communicate research findings, insights and strategic recommendations – written and verbal – in a clear, concise, and compelling way. ', 'Stay current with the latest social measurement tools and relevant industry trends. ', ' ', 'Key Qualifications', 'The ideal candidate is keenly strategic, versatile and insights-driven; someone who thrives in an energetic, fast-paced entrepreneurial environment.  In addition, our new team member will have: ', "Bachelor's degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related quantitative discipline ", '1+ years professional experience conducting quantitative analyses using Python ', '1+ years professional  experience working with multi-disciplinary teams ', '1+ years experience with relational databases and data manipulation using SQL ', 'Skilled user of tools such as Excel, Tableau ', ' ', 'Preferred Qualifications', ' ', 'Exposure to GCP or similar cloud computing platform (AWS, Azure, etc.) ', 'Experience with real-time listening for real-time engagement (ideally via social media command centers). ', 'Ability to quickly pattern spot and surface actionable insights; separate signal from noise. ', 'Excellent verbal and written communications skills. Experience writing clear and concise presentations summarizing data, insights, outcomes and implications in a straightforward and enlightening way for teams and clients. ', 'Experience distilling complex and high volumes of data into simple KPIs and data visualizations / dashboards / scorecards. ', 'Collaborative attitude, strong work ethic and ability to thrive and excel in a challenging fast-paced environment. ', 'A desire to work hard, play hard and deliver game-changing work. ', ' ', 'To be successful, the candidate must have a desire to deliver quality work for clients/brands, be a team player and demonstrate the ability to get the job done. You’ll need a serious interest of trends, best practices, technology and business applications on the Internet and within Methods+Mastery.', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Public Relations', 'Marketing', 'Advertising', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising']

Name: Data Governance Analyst
Description: ['Posted by:', 'Tiffany Nettles', 'Tiffany Nettles', 'Recruiter at Stratice, LLC', 'Data Governance Analyst', 'Location: Montgomery, AL', 'Description:', "This position will be part of a integral team to lead the Agency in the establishment of an Enterprise Data Governance infrastructure. The person who fills this position must be a positive, personable, well organized, team player with excellent communication skills. This position requires professional interaction with senior and executive level leaders and staff. A extremely strong background in Data Governance framework process implementation is an absolute and necessary for success in this arena. This position will be working in the Agency's Data Governance Office under the direct supervision of the Chief Data Officer. Specifically this person will work with other organizational units and resources to gather and analyze the Agency’s DG needs. Monitors, identifies, investigates, prioritizes, and communicates data quality issues. Performs data profiling, analyzes and communicates results in support of data quality processes. Demonstrates detailed understanding of overall data models, data relationships, mapping lineage, and business rules. Supports, develops, and maintains business data requirements and specifications to support data standards. Ensures that solutions (structure, values, relationships, quality standards) meet operational and business need. Work with business areas and project team members to understand new business data capabilities and perform impact analysis to determine additional data requirements, provide data expertise and data as needed. Analyzes customer requests (internal and external regulatory, e.g. data calls) to determines access and impact on existing systems, processes and develops appropriate specifications, enhancements and or procedures to address the LOB needs. Meets with internal customers and conducts requirements sessions to support DG processes. Supports the development of strategic solutions for architecture for managing of data including transformation logic, rules, tables as well as business requirements and specifications. Represents unit and department functions as part of various DM workgroups/committees with internal and external areas.", 'Skills Required:', 'Very well-organized, detail oriented individual to manage data governance and data management implementations, master plans and data stewardship activities.. Must be an active team member in the development of a DG strategy and implementation. A moderate to extensive knowledge of enterprise uses of data and total data flow within enterprise is preferred. Must possess a strong knowledge of data flow requirements, data modeling, data tools, and statistical modeling tools. Demonstrated intermediate analytic and diagnostic skills. Demonstrated excellent interpersonal, communication, and presentation skills. Ability to work independently and as part of a team. General understanding of the business functions, processes, and overall business strategies. Intermediate business acumen and problem solving skills. Ability to interact effectively with others across functions.', 'Skills Preferred:', 'Very strong knowledge and proficiency in Microsoft Sharepoint.', 'Experience Required:', 'Minimum four to seven years of experience in data governance and data management required in accordance with following areas: Data Governance Experience • Collaborate with business stakeholders to develop and document data needs and requirements • Conduct interviews with key end users and process stakeholders to collect and document information on business processes and user requirements. • Develop best practices, standards, policies, and methodologies to assist in the implementation and execution of the data governance program. • Defined accountability procedures that govern data access, processing, storage, and retention. • Developed and delivered auditing and reporting processes for data governance policy compliance. • Created and implemented data governance framework that established data management policies that align with the organization’s data strategy and industry best-practices. • Review and document the impact of process change on current users to determine gaps and training needs. • Identify and document gaps in the availability of data for business processes. • Lead the Data Governance Committee and work with committee members to implement data management and data quality standards across the organization. • Develop and deliver reports and dashboards that describe the state and progress of the data governance program. • Develop methodologies for the implementation and support of the enterprise data dictionary. • Develop methodologies for the implementation and support of the enterprise business glossary. • Managed the creation and delivery of progress monitoring reports for the data governance program and its associated practices. • Champion a holistic, multi-pronged approach to embedding EDM, MDM, and DG principles and practices across the enterprise. • Applied EDM and DG principles to create an efficient and effective data management environment that serves multiple business units in their pursuit of a data-driven organization. Data Stewardship Experience • Develop and implement enterprise data stewardship program. • Collaborate with business unit subject-matter-experts to understand the data needs of the business unit and how they integrate with the needs of the rest of the organization. • Established and maintained data domains and sub-domains for the organization. • Identify, educate, and assign data owners for the organization’s data domains. • Established metadata registry responsibilities for data stewardship program. • Engage subject-matter-experts from lines of business/business units and assimilate them into the enterprise data stewardship program. • Develop and deliver training on data stewardship roles and responsibilities. • Facilitate the resolution of conflicts with data concepts across multiple data domains. • Championed data consistency and data integrity efforts amongst key business users and enforced concept of “system of record”. • Defined roles and responsibilities related to data governance to ensure clear accountability for stewardship of the company’s data assets. Data Quality Experience • Developed and executed data quality strategies to increase the value of the organization’s data assets in support of the overall data strategy and goals. • Established data quality process and implemented issue tracking tools. • Works with data stewards and data owners to capture business-level data quality rules and translate them into technical data quality solutions. • Develop data quality metrics that identify gaps and ensure compliance with standards across the organization. • Develop and deliver reports and dashboards that describe the health of data by data domain and data system. • Worked with management and IT to remediate identified data issues, using both manual and automated solutions. • Established processes to continuously monitor data quality, using automated testing solutions. Ensured processes were in place to proactively detect, correct, and prevent invalid data values. • Automated data reconciliation checks from source to target systems. • Conformed dimensions leveraged by data marts across the organization for consistency in reporting.', 'Experience Preferred:', 'Collibra Experience • Collibra Expert or Ranger certification • Supported and configured Collibra application, including installation, maintenance, upgrades, user configuration, etc. • Experience in developing customized workflows and user interfaces within the Collibra Data Governance Center application. • Experience with Trillium DQ integration with Collibra • Experience with the Data Help Desk • Configuration and support of third-party tool integrations using Collibra Connect. Trillium DQ Experience • Supported and configured Trillium application, including installation, maintenance, upgrades, user configuration, etc. • Developed and maintained data quality rules and workflows within the Trillium DQ application. • Development of data matching and data cleansing solutions, including standardization of addresses using USPS database • Developed workflows to transform, parse, standardize, match and survive the best record. • De-duplicate and unify data sources to create a single “golden” record. • Automated data profiling and discovery • Experience with Collibra and Trillium DQ integration. • Integration of BI tools (PowerBI and Tableau) with Trillium DQ.', 'Education Required:', 'Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or other related field., or equivalent work experience.', 'Education Preferred:', 'Federal/State HHS Agency, and/or Health Information Management experience preferred. Thorough knowledge of DG strategy development and the DM/DQ life cycle is preferred', 'Seniority level', 'Mid-Senior level', 'Employment type', 'Contract', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Government Administration']

Name: Data and Reporting Analyst
Company: Research Foundation for Mental Hygiene, Inc.
Description: ["The Research Foundation for Mental Hygiene, Inc. (RFMH) is currently seeking a full-time qualified candidate to serve as a Data and Reporting Analyst in the New York State Office of Mental Health's (OMH) Bureau of Housing Development and Support (BHDS) in Albany, New York.", 'BHDS provides oversight and direction for residential programs for the seriously mentally ill (SMI) population across NYS. This includes administration of capital funding, oversight and monitoring, program guidance and policy development to maintain, expand and promote the effective functioning of the OMH-funded housing portfolio.', 'Responsibilities Include, But Are Not Limited To', "Under the direction of the Bureau Director, the Data and Reporting Analyst will be responsible for performing a various systems and data-driven functions and related duties, ranging from management of budgetary and expenditure information; tracking and reporting of housing program information; and capital project planning and implementation in support the Bureau's goals and objectives.", 'The Data and Reporting Analyst should display Solid organizational and information management skills, including ability to learn and navigate information systems.', 'Facilitate annual budget request and quarterly Division of Budget (DOB) capital project report;', 'Tracking and management of budgetary, expenditure, and contract information for capital projects. Generation of reports (e.g. bed charts, spending projections, etc.);', 'Maintain, update, and access housing and contract related information in the various systems such as Residential Information System (RIS), CONCERTS, Topher, CAIRS.', 'Serve as liaison to Statewide Financial System (SFS) and Grants Gateway administrators in order to assist in the development and administration of RFPs and assist project managers in the processing and/or approval of contracts and payments;', 'Manage capital projects as assigned; ', 'Serve as liaison to the Dormitory Authority (DASNY) and Housing Finance Agency (HFA) with respect to ongoing payment of bond debt service, collection of information necessary for bond closings, ensuring reimbursement of Short-Term Investment Pool (STIP) account with bond proceeds;', 'Provide reporting of data for Medicaid Redesign Team (MRT) related units to Department of Health (DOH);', 'Assist in the establishment and management of an MWBE tracking system;', 'Perform other similar duties such as conducting and analyzing of provider surveys, as assigned.', 'Minimum Requirements', "Bachelor's degree and two years of professional experience in an appropriate field. Appropriate fields include Psychology, Sociology, Social Work, Public Health, or a related social science field; OR", "Master's degree in an appropriate field and one year of experience as outlined in item #1; OR", 'Doctorate in an appropriate field as outlined in item #1. ', 'Knowledge of mental health housing and strong written and verbal communication skills are required.', 'Proficient with Microsoft Office suite of products including Excel, Word, Access and PowerPoint.', 'Preferred Requirements', 'Experience in data management, budgeting, housing, and/or capital development, is preferred.', 'Travel: ', 'Travel to program sites may be required.', 'Location:', ' 44 Holland Avenue, Albany, NY', 'To Apply:', ' To Apply: Submit a resume and cover letter by February 18, 2020 on our website at http://corporate.rfmh.org then click on Employment Opportunities. Only applications submitted through our website will be considered.', 'The Research Foundation is a private not-for-profit corporation and is not an agency or instrumentality of the State of New York. Name: Healthcare Data Analyst - Clinical Value Performance Imp
Description: ['Description', 'Swedish Medical Center is looking for a Healthcare Data Anaylst (1.0 FTE, Day) to work in the Clinical Value Performance Imp Department at the Bank of American building in Seattle, WA.', "The Healthcare Data Analyst role supports Swedish Health Services' goals by writing queries and creating reports that allow us to improve the quality and value of care that we deliver to our patients. This role provides analytic support to measure clinical process and outcome measures related to disease, clinical processes, care pathways and population health. The ideal candidate is passionate about data and its ability to tell stories and answer questions that are meaningful for providers and patients.", 'In This Position You Will', ' ', 'Create, validate, and maintain SQL queries to pull data from Epic’s Clarity database and other Swedish/Providence data sources (e.g., EDW) in order to understand and improve practice patterns and patient outcomes.', ' ', 'Collaborate with Quality Division colleagues, physicians, administrators, and other Swedish partners to scope, design, and validate recurring and ad hoc reports.', ' ', 'Document project details using Jira and maintain report specifications that clearly describe how the report works.', ' ', 'Enhance existing reports and reporting processes to create efficiencies and added value throughout Swedish.', ' ', 'Code review and other collaboration with Swedish and Providence analysts/database administrators to ensure coordination of efforts and best-practice sharing.', ' ', 'Interpret reports for administrative, clinical, and non-technical audiences.Understand and educate colleagues on the connection between data input and reporting output.', ' ', 'Use Tableau to create reports that effectively and efficiently communicate the key message.', ' ', 'Participate in initiatives to continuously improve the methods and processes of the Healthcare Analytics team.', ' ', 'Qualifications', 'Required qualifications for this position include:', ' ', "Bachelor's Degree in computer science, mathematics, statistics, information technology, health informatics, public health, or related subject.", ' ', '3 years of recent SQL programming. Skills should include some combination of: SQL Server 2012, Data Warehouse design, Oracle SQL.', ' ', '3 years of progressive experience in healthcare operations, decision support tools or management of complex databases and analytics', ' ', 'Proven experience creating, managing, and validating large data sets.', ' ', 'Working knowledge of healthcare and quality improvement.Excellent organization and analytic skills.', ' ', 'Knowledge of medical terminology and healthcare coding standards (e.g., CPT and ICD-10 codes)', ' ', 'Skills with analytical software (e.g., Excel, SQL, SAS, R) as well as demonstrated knowledge of business service systems and the ability to operate complex business applications and systems.', ' ', 'Ability to communicate complex clinical and/or financial information to operational staff. Ability to interact comfortably with a wide range of individuals, including clinicians and senior leadership.', ' ', 'Ability to work in a collaborative and supportive way with teams and colleagues from the Quality Division, Healthcare Intelligence, Information Services, Finance, and others.', ' ', 'Preferred Qualifications For This Position Include', ' ', " Master's Degree in computer science, mathematics, statistics, information technology, health informatics, public health, or related subject.", ' ', 'Experience with reporting data out of Epic Clarity and/or Chronicles databases.', ' ', 'Experience with Tableau data visualization software.', ' ', 'Experience and familiarity with statistical analysis methodologies, modeling, and hypothesis testing.', ' ', 'About Swedish Shared Services.', 'Swedish is the largest, most comprehensive, nonprofit health provider in the Greater Seattle area. Our expanding network of facilities currently includes three hospital locations in Seattle, a hospital in Edmonds and the new Swedish Issaquah campus. It also consists of Swedish Medical Group’s network of primary care clinics, and affiliations with suburban hospitals and specialty clinics throughout Greater Seattle.', 'Each campus has a local operations leadership team, supported by centrally located and led corporate services, such as Human Resources, Financial and Information Services.', 'We offer a full comprehensive range of benefits — see our website for details', 'https://caregiver.ehr.com', 'Our Mission', 'Our nonprofit Mission is to improve the health and wellbeing of each person we serve. Our Vision is to demonstrate the highest-quality, best-value healthcare to all we serve.', 'About Us', 'Swedish is the largest nonprofit health care provider in the greater Seattle area. It is comprised of five hospital campuses (First Hill, Cherry Hill, Ballard, Edmonds and Issaquah); ambulatory care centers in Redmond and Mill Creek; and Swedish Medical Group a network of more than 118 primary care and specialty locations throughout the Puget Sound. Swedish employs more than 13,300 employees and 3,100 physicians and allied health professionals. Whether through physician clinics, education, research and innovation or other outreach, we’re committed to caring for the people in our region and beyond. Swedish is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. Swedish does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, gender, disability, protected veteran, military status, religion, age, creed, national origin, gender identity, sexual orientation, marital status, genetic information, or any other basis prohibited by local, state, or federal law.', 'Schedule:', ' Full-time', 'Shift:', ' Day', 'Job Category:', ' Administrative (Non-Clinical)', 'Location:', ' Washington-Seattle', 'Work Locations:', ' Bank Of America Bldg (WA239) 800 Fifth Ave Seattle, 98104', 'Req ID:', ' 234871', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Nonprofit Organization Management', 'Health, Wellness and Fitness', 'Hospital & Health Care']

Name: Data Analysis Administrator
Description: ['Announcement Details', 'Exam Announcement Details', 'Exam Title', ' Data Analysis Administrator', 'Exam Number', ' 3H87-20200323-22-00', 'Salary', ' $72,957 - $93,797 per year.', 'Competition', ' Department Only Promotional', 'Department ', ' 22 - Department of Human Services', 'Announcement Date', ' 03/23/2020', 'Close Date', ' 04/03/2020', 'General Definition', 'Announced in Anticipation of Approval by the Administrative Board', 'This is supervisory statistical, analytical and administrative work with responsibility for directing the collection, classification, analysis, maintenance, and dissemination of statistics related to the provision of services in the area of assignment. Positions in the class serve as the technical expert in statistics for the department and are responsible for the implementation and use of information systems or applications for reporting and monitoring of statistics. Positions also ensure information systems in the area of assignment are working efficiently and effectively. Conferring with department program administrators and contracted agencies to develop and revise information systems is of major significance to the work. Work is performed under the direction of a technical/administrative superior.', 'Union Code', ' H. AFSCME D.C.47 Local 2186', 'FLSA Code', ' Exempt', 'Minimum Requirements', 'Minimum Training, Education & Experience', 'The following statement represents the minimum training and experience standards which will be used to admit or reject applicants for tests. Candidates must meet requirements within 30 days after the last date for filing applications.', ' Presently employed by the City of Philadelphia with permanent Civil Service status in the Department of Human Services with a performance rating of Satisfactory or higher;', 'AND', ' EDUCATION : Completion of a master’s degree at an accredited college or university with major course work in public health, public administration, biological sciences, social sciences, physical sciences, mathematics, or statistics, including or supplemented by coursework in statistics, data analysis, system analysis, and computer programming;', 'AND', ' GENERAL EXPERIENCE : Two years of experience performing statistical analysis or performing research of operations or programs which included conducting studies, collecting and analyzing data to identify trends or evaluate programs, and the use of statistical software;', 'AND', ' SPECIFIC EXPERIENCE :', 'Two years of experience in ONE of the following areas:', ' performing advanced level analytical work designing, implementing, or applying computer-based management information systems to improve operating efficiency and facilitate management reporting and analysis at the departmental level', ' performing advanced level research and information management work designing analytical studies or formulating data collection policies and procedures, and recommending the implementation of new or revised systems resulting from review of the data from these studies', ' performing administrative analysis and management work supervising subordinate analysts in a department-wide administrative analysis function with departmental goals and policies reporting to a Deputy Commissioner or equivalent division head of a department.', 'NOTE : Selective Factor Certification may be utilized, as needed, to fill specific assignments in the General Specialty. In accordance with Civil Service Regulation 11.032 – Selective Factor Certification – the appointing authority may request certification of eligible candidates with one or more of the specified qualifications to fill specific positions in this class. Certification to fill such positions will be made from the two highest-ranking eligible candidates on the eligible list who possess the specified qualifications in the assignment area.', 'CITY OF PHILADELPHIA CLASSES THAT TYPICALLY MEET THE MINIMUM SPECIFIC EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENTS OF THE CLASS :', 'Information Management Analyst 3 (1E04)', 'Research and Information Analyst 2 (2F22)', 'Physical & Medical Requirements', 'Ability to physically perform the duties and to work in the environmental conditions required of a position in this class.', 'Other Requirements', 'Required Licenses & Certifications', 'Documentation Requirements', 'Candidates MUST submit a copy of their official college transcript indicating the completion of a master’s degree at an accredited college or university with major course work in public health, public administration, biological sciences, social sciences, physical sciences, mathematics, or statistics, including or supplemented by coursework in statistics, data analysis, system analysis, and computer programming; .', 'Your Options Are Further Explained Below', 'It is an absolute requirement that you provide this documentation by May 5, 2020. It is Optional whether you provide this documentation by attaching it to this application or submitting via email, mail or fax by May 5, 2020.', 'Option 1 – Upload an official copy of your documentation and attach to this application– Good for this application and all future applications!', 'You may upload the documentation into your account, and attach to this application. Once uploaded to your account, the documentation may be attached to all future applications. This will save you time and money if you apply for an examination in the future. This also ensures that your documentation will not be misplaced.', 'Your documentation should be uploaded and attached to your application before it is submitted. It cannot be uploaded or added to your application electronically after your application has been submitted.', 'Option 2 – Submit an official copy of your documentation via email, mail or fax – One time use only!', 'If you submit the required documentation via email, mail or fax, it will be used for this application only. You will have to submit the documentation again whenever you apply for an examination in the future. Copies of the documentation will not be retained and will not be returned to applicants.', 'Mailing Address', 'City of Philadelphia', 'Office of Human Resources', '1401 J.F. Kennedy Boulevard, Room 1530', 'Philadelphia, PA 19102', 'Attention: Eric Myers', 'Email Address', 'Eric.Myers@phila.gov', 'Fax: 215-686-0861', 'Equivalency Statement(s)', 'Any equivalent combination of education and experience determined to be acceptable by the Office of Human Resources that has included a master’s degree and the specific experience described above.', 'Application Details', 'Application Procedures', 'Notes to Applicants', 'The City of Philadelphia is an Equal Opportunity employer and does not permit discrimination based on race, ethnicity, color, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, religion, national origin, ancestry, age, disability, marital status, source of income, familial status, genetic information or domestic or sexual violence victim status. If you believe you were discriminated against, call the Philadelphia Commission on Human Relations at 215-686-4670 or send an email to faqpchr@phila.gov. For more information, go to: www.phila.gov/humanrelations', 'The City of Philadelphia is committed to ensuring access to Civil Service examinations by providing appropriate accommodations for candidates with documented medical or religious reasons. Candidates may request an accommodation for a Civil Service examination by contacting the Equal Employment Opportunity / Affirmative Action Unit of the Mayor’s Office of Labor Relations at 215-683-5085. The accommodation process is interactive and requires cooperation and communication between the applicant requesting a test accommodation and the EEO Unit. Decisions will be made on a case-by-case basis using the required documentation that is submitted. Requests are to be made in a timely manner prior to the scheduled date of the Civil Service examination.', 'Only an on-line application will be accepted for this exam. Paper applications will not be accepted.', 'Computers are available in the 3-1-1 Walk-In Center located in Room 167 of City Hall (Weekdays from 9 AM to 5 PM) and at your local Philadelphia Free Library branch.', 'For inquiries regarding City employment, contact the Office of Human Resources Monday through Friday between 8 AM and 4 PM by telephone at 215-686-0880 or by email at hrhelpdesk@phila.gov', 'ALL Applications must be received by the end of business on April 3, 2020.', 'Your application will be rejected and you will be disqualified from competing in this examination if you:', ' Do not provide your complete and accurate social security number.', ' Attempt to practice fraud or deception in the preparation of this application', 'All correspondence and notifications will be sent to your e-mail address or postal address listed in the contact information (address, phone #, e-mail) of your account profile. Your contact information will be automatically updated each time you submit an application for employment. It is your responsibility to change your contact information and to ensure that it is correct', 'If you provide an e-mail address, all correspondence regarding this examination will be sent to you by e-mail. You should add Phila.OHR@phila.gov to your address book or list of trusted contacts to prevent notices from being marked as spam by your e-mail provider.', 'Please call the Office of Human Resources at 215-686-0880 or email hrhelpdesk@phila.gov if you have any questions.', 'Information concerning employment with the City of Philadelphia may be found at:', 'www.phila.gov/personnel', 'http://www.phila.gov/personnel/ExamsFAQ.html', 'Facebook @CityofPhiladelphiaJOBS', 'Twitter @PHLCityJobs', 'ELIGIBLE LIST', 'DEPARTMENTAL - ONLY PROMOTIONAL : Only a departmental promotional eligible list for the Department of Human Services will be established as a result of the examination.', 'Candidates who pass the exam and are placed on the civil service list will be retained on the list for a minimum of one year and a maximum of two years after the establishment of the Eligible List.', 'Preference For Philadelphia Residents', 'Candidates who have maintained a bona fide residence in Philadelphia for at least one year prior to the date of the civil service examination shall have priority over all other persons receiving an identical test score. If you have maintained a bona fide residence in Philadelphia for at least one year immediately preceding May 6, 2020 you are eligible to claim residency preference.', 'Your response to the residency question will be used to determine eligibility for residency preference. Documentation of residence may be required if there is any question as to whether you meet the residency preference requirements.', 'Projected Exam Date', 'If an oral exam is held, this examination will be scheduled for May 6, 2020. Please note that this examination date is subject to change.', 'Virtual Testing May Be Utilized For This Examination.', 'Candidates taking an oral examination may have their responses rated in person by a panel of Subject Matter Experts on the date of the examination, or have their responses recorded on the date of the examination and rated by Subject Matter Experts at a later date. Please refer all questions regarding this examination to the analyst listed below on the announcement.', 'If a training and experience evaluation is held, applicants will be evaluated and scored based upon their training and experience credentials. Applicants will not be asked to appear to take a scheduled examination.', 'Scores in the Training and Experience Evaluation will be based on documentation of education and experience provided by the candidate. To receive full credit for your education and experience, you should submit all relevant documentation including college transcripts, licenses, certifications, paid out of class documentation, etc. and provide a detailed description of your education, experience and credentials.', 'An Eligible List is planned for the week of May 18, 2020. Please note that this date may change.', 'Test Review', 'If an oral examination is held, in accordance with Civil Service Regulation 9.091B, candidates will have 30 days after the results have been mailed to review their test and to file appeals. In accordance with Civil Service Regulation 9.11, only candidates who have failed the oral examination may appeal to the Civil Service Commission upon the grounds of irregularity, bias, or fraud in the conduct of the oral test. Issues related to the suitability or adequacy of point scores awarded to passers are not appealable to the Commission. Call 215-686-0880 if you wish to schedule a Test Review.', 'If a training and experience evaluation is held, in accordance with Civil Service Regulation 9.091D, candidates may review their answer sheets and other test papers to determine if they have been scored correctly or if there has been an irregularity in the administration of the examination. Candidates will have 30 days after the results have been mailed to review their test and to file a written appeal. Call 215 686-0880 if you wish to schedule a test review.', 'Assigned to (view only)', 'Assigned to', ' Eric Myers', 'Parts & Weights', 'Part', ' Oral or Tranining and Experience Evaluation', 'Weight', ' 90%', 'Parts & Weights', 'Part', ' Seniority', 'Weight', ' 10%', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Contract', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Construction', 'Higher Education', 'Government Administration']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Software powers the world, and LaunchDarkly empowers all teams to deliver and control the best software. We serve hundreds of billions of feature flags daily, to help teams ship better software, faster and eliminate risk for companies big and small.', "We're based in downtown Oakland and growing quickly. You'll help us tackle some of the most challenging engineering problems around, like how can we deliver feature flags to hundreds of millions of users in milliseconds without breaking the bank.", ' About The Role ', "We are look for an experienced Data Analyst to join a new team at LaunchDarkly. We are growing rapidly, and need reliable and efficient answers for questions key to our future. You'll help develop the data, process and insights to power our next stage of growth.", 'We are searching for a talented Analyst to help us understand business critical data and leverage it across the entire organization. If you are data curious, excited about digging deeply into business data, and motivated by having impact on the whole company, we want to hear from you.', " What You'll Do ", 'Help create a data practice for the entire company.', 'Help ensure a data pipeline that is trustworthy and reliable.', 'Work with stakeholders around the business to understand their needs.', 'Help stakeholders ask good questions and get valuable insights.', "Help answer the business' most pressing questions in repeatable, reliable ways.", 'Build tools and teach people how to find answers to their own questions', 'On day one, you should have:', '2 or more years of experience in a hands-on Data Analytics role', 'Experience conducting data intensive analysis.', 'A visceral need to dive into data inconsistencies to pinpoint issues.', "Product- and market-awareness to jump in and quickly understand LaunchDarkly's position and goals. ", 'Expertise in SQL and proficiency in another data programming language (Python, R, etc.).', 'You may also know (bonus skills):', 'Experience in both enterprise and consumer environments.', 'LaunchDarkly is a Feature Management Platform that serves hundreds of billions of feature flags daily to help software teams build better software, faster. Feature flagging is an industry standard methodology of wrapping a new or risky section of code or infrastructure change with a flag. Each flag can easily be turned off independent of code deployment (aka "dark launching"). LaunchDarkly has SDKs for all major web and mobile platforms. We are building a diverse team so that we can offer robust products and services. Our team culture is dynamic, friendly, and supportive. Our headquarters are in Oakland.', "At LaunchDarkly, we believe in the power of teams. We're building a team that is humble, open, collaborative, respectful and kind. We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.", ' LaunchDarkly Offers ', 'Full Medical, Dental & Vision insurance', 'Unlimited vacation', 'Flexible schedule & work environment', 'Healthy lunches & snacks every day.', 'Conference & meetups as an opportunity for everyone.', 'A yearly education stipend for conferences and classes on your own.', 'A budget to personalize your work station.', 'A location in downtown Oakland, just steps from public transportation', 'Commuter benefits and bike parking', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Internet']

Name: Data Science Analyst
Description: ['Summary', 'Works in concert with Logicalis Managed Services Engineers, Architects and Developers to mine complex data and provide systems-related advice while managing statistical data and creating different models.', 'Essential Duties And Responsibilities', ' Designs and builds new data set processes for modeling, data mining, and production purposes.', ' Determines new ways to improve data and search quality, and predictive capabilities.', ' Performs and interprets data studies and product experiments concerning new data sources or new uses for existing data sources.', ' Develops prototypes, proof of concepts, algorithms, predictive models, and custom analysis.', ' Connects to data in RDBMS and Hadoop environments using SQL/HQL and complex functions.', ' Develops and tunes machine learning models in R, Python, and Spark.', ' Works with stakeholders, partners, and other development teams to create/express appropriate features from raw data to hit model target objectives and accuracy.', ' Assesses accuracy and effectiveness of new data sources and data gathering techniques.', ' Designs queries with SQL/HQL to extract data from data stores and bring into analytics products, such as Aqua Data Studio, Alteryx Designer, Tableau, R, and Spark for additional analysis.', ' Works with data in virtual environments and transforms it to fit analytics purpose, including OLAP, data pivoting, etc.', ' Performs initial discovery and analysis of newly identified data sources to determine how to integrate them with other data lake components.', ' Designs and engineers systems that can move large quantities of data and produce results within required near-real-time timeframes.', " Demonstrates and actively promotes an understanding and commitment to the mission of Logicalis through performing behaviors consistent with the organization's values.", ' Maintains a working knowledge of applicable Federal, State, and Local laws and regulations as well as policies and procedures of Logicalis in order to ensure adherence in a manner that reflects honest, ethical and professional behaviors.', ' Supports and conducts self in a manner consistent with customer service expectations.', 'Supervisory Responsibilities', 'This job has no supervisory responsibilities.', 'Qualifications', 'To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.', 'Education', ' Education/Experience/Technical Requirements/Certifications ', ' Bachelor’s Degree in related field.', 'Experience / Technical Requirements', ' 3 years’ practical experience with SAS, ETL, data processing, database programming and data analytics.', ' Advanced understanding of SQL/HQL; familiarity with one or more: Apache Hive, IBM Big SQL, IBM DB2, Oracle SQL, Microsoft SQL Server, Teradata SQL, Power BI, Tableau Desktop.', ' Knowledge and experience in statistical and machine learning techniques not limited to GLM/Regression, Gradient Boosting, Random Forest, Decision Trees, boosting and ensembling.', ' Knowledge of R, Spark/Scala, or equivalent statistical modeling language.', ' Driven to learn and apply new techniques; knowledge and experience with Data Visualization, Statistical Analysis, Predictive Analytics, Mathematics, and Elementary Statistics.', ' Proficient use of Microsoft Office applications.', 'May consider an equivalent combination of education and experience.', ' Certifications ', ' None', 'Other Skills And Abilities', ' Effectively visualizes and presents data to stakeholders and leadership.', ' Strong troubleshooting and initiative skills.', ' Strong customer service focus with excellent interpersonal skills.', ' Excellent communication skills – oral, written, and email.', ' Ability to multi-task and work in fast paced environment.', ' Ability to work independently with minimal supervision.', ' Works well with team members and cross-departmentally.', ' Physical Demands ', 'The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.', 'While performing the duties of this Job, the employee is constantly required to sit, talk, see, hear, and use hands and arms. The employee is frequently required to stand; move about, climb steps or balance and stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl. The employee must occasionally lift and/or move up to 10 pounds.', 'The above statements describe the general nature and level of work being performed by individuals assigned to this classification. This is not intended to be an exhaustive list of all responsibilities and duties required of personnel so classified.', 'Logicalis is an Equal Opportunity Employer. It is our policy to employ people who are qualified by reason of education, training, experience, and demonstrated performance. We value diversity and inclusion at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, marital status, age, height, weight, disability, veteran status, or any other reason prohibited by applicable federal or state laws.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Telecommunications']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['ConnectiveRx is a leading, technology-enabled healthcare services company. We work strategically with hundreds of biopharmaceutical manufacturers to help commercialize and maximize the benefits of specialty and branded medications. Our mission is to simplify how patients get on and stay on therapy. We fulfill our mission by providing our customers with innovative services such as patient and provider messaging, the design and operation of copay, vouchers and patient affordability programs, and hub services, all of which accelerate speed-to-therapy and help improve outcomes for manufacturers, healthcare providers and patients.', 'ConnectiveRx was formed in 2015 by bringing together the industry-leading business of PSKW, PDR/LDM, Careform (2017) and The Macaluso Group (2018) to advance our technology-driven expertise in providing state-of-the-art commercialization solutions. To learn more about our company, visit ConnectiveRx.com', 'Job Description', 'Reporting to the Director, Program Management, the Data Analyst will be responsible for supporting client and HUB operations with a variety of data and analytical services. The incumbent will use complex data analytic techniques to aggregate data into meaningful and impactful visual representations to be provide to client contacts at planned intervals and to fulfill ad hoc requests. The incumbent will also be responsible for performing standard statistical analyses, presenting results, and developing thorough documentation of the programming and results. Assistance with presentations, reports, and manuscripts preparation will be required.', 'Essential Functions', ' ', ' Collaborate with members of the operations leadership teams to understand business requirements, trends and expectations for analysis. ', ' ', ' Produce ad-hoc reports under tight deadlines for various client requests. ', ' ', ' Partner with IT staff to validate data attributes and to assure consistent integration across several data sources. ', ' ', ' Build database queries and deliver reports and dashboards using tools such as Tableau, Salesforce, MS Excel. ', ' ', ' Collaborate with the marketing and business development teams, as needed, to measure program effectiveness and track KPIs. ', ' ', ' Manage projects and ensure that deadlines are met and remain consistent with stakeholder expectations. ', ' ', ' Provide ongoing analytical and technical support of existing data sources, data integration, operational reports and dashboards. ', ' ', ' Develop and maintain relevant documentation. ', ' ', " Collaborate with senior management on a strategic vision and roadmap for ConnectiveRx's operational data solutions. ", ' ', ' Analyze ways internal business users leverage historical data to understand trends, answer questions, and create standardized report automation to reduce the need for ad hoc reporting requests. ', ' ', ' Participate in design sessions for new systems and features to enhance business processes. ', ' ', ' Monitor daily and weekly inbound and outbound data feed exchanges to ensure on-time delivery and complete and accurate data. ', ' ', ' Diagnosis of inbound/outbound file issues through a documented quality control process. ', ' ', 'Qualifications', ' ', ' Minimum of 2 years of experience in data analytics, preferably supporting client-facing business operations. ', ' ', ' Expertise in interpretation, forecasting, predictive modeling, and executive presentation. ', ' ', ' Bachelor’s Degree in Database Management, Data Analytics, or similar field. ', ' ', ' Advanced proficiency with reporting tools such as SQL, SSRS, and Excel. ', ' ', ' Minimum of 2 years Tableau design experience (required) ', ' ', ' Demonstrated ability to communicate concepts in both technical and user-friendly language. ', ' ', ' Strong communication (written and verbal), analytical, and problem-solving skills. ', ' ', ' Must be attentive to detail and capable of successfully functioning under limited supervision. ', ' ', ' Ability to prioritize and execute job tasks in a high-pressure, deadline-driven environment ', ' ', ' Experience in presenting data analysis to clients and internal stakeholders. ', ' ', ' Strong analytical skills and demonstrated ability to analyze data to identify trends and performance results. ', ' ', ' Ability to work well with individuals at all levels of the organization. ', ' ', ' Ability to work in high pressure situations demanding a positive outcome. ', ' Highly professional, strong work ethic, self-driven and strong sense of personal integrity. ', ' Strong knowledge of SFTP and API data feed process and delivery ', ' Proven ability to monitor various file exchanges for completeness and accuracy ', ' Previous experience analyzing and diagnosing delivery issues in large sets of data by comparing file data to data requirement documents ', 'Equal Opportunity Employer: This employer (hereafter the Company) is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate in recruitment, hiring, training, promotion, or other employment policies on the basis of age, race, sex, color, religion, national origin, disability, veteran status, genetic information, or any other basis that is prohibited by federal, state, or local law. No question in this application is intended to secure information to be used for such discrimination. In addition, the Company makes reasonable accommodation to the needs of disabled applicants and employees, so long as this does not create an undue hardship on the Company or threaten the health or safety of others at work. This application will be given every consideration, but its receipt does not imply that the applicant will be employed.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Information Technology and Services', 'Computer Software', 'Hospital & Health Care']

Name: Modeling Data Analyst - 185995
Description: ['Clicking "Apply Now" opens the link in a new window. ', 'How to Apply', 'Applications are welcomed and encouraged from all qualified individuals regardless of background and identity. To apply, please complete the application on the U-M Careers site. A one page cover letter is required for consideration for this position and should be attached as the first page of your resume. The cover letter should address your specific interest in the position and outline experience that directly relate to this position.', 'Job Summary', 'The Cooperative Institute for Great Lakes Research (CIGLR) is seeking an individual to work with the ecological and physical modeling teams at the NOAA Great Lakes Environmental Research Lab (GLERL) to develop experimental ecological forecasts linked to hydrodynamic models of the Great Lakes Operational Forecast system. Under the direction of the Project Principal Investigators, the Modeling Data Analyst will evaluate model performance through statistical comparison of modeled and observed water quality, biological, and physical variables.', 'The appointment will be with the Cooperative Institute of Great Lakes Research (CIGLR), which is part of the University of Michigan’s School for Environment and Sustainability (SEAS) located in Ann Arbor, Michigan. CIGLR is a collaboration between the University of Michigan and NOAA that brings together experts from academia and government research labs to work on pressing challenges. This person will spend the majority of their time at NOAA’s Great Lakes Environmental Research Lab (GLERL) in Ann Arbor where they will work on projects led by Dr. Mark Rowe and Dr. Eric Anderson.', 'The University of Michigan is a top-ranked public university highly focused on research and scholarship. Ann Arbor, home to the University of Michigan, is a town known for arts, culture, parks and restaurants.', 'SEAS is committed to creating an inclusive and equitable environment that respects diverse experiences, promotes generous listening and communications, discourages and genuinely respond to acts of discrimination, harassment, or injustice. Our commitment to diversity, equity and inclusion is rooted in our values for a sustainable and just society.', 'Term Appointment', 'Note: This is a one year term limited position with the possibility of renewal.', 'Responsibilities*', ' ', ' Conduct data analysis using a scripting (computer programming) for all development models ', ' ', ' Evaluate the performance of ecological and hydrodynamic models of the Great Lakes by statistical comparison of modeled versus observed water quality, biological, and physical variables ', ' ', ' Oversee numerical hydrodynamic and biophysical models of the Great Lakes using a high-performance computing system ', ' ', ' Conduct model transition to real-time forecasts ', ' ', ' Conduct model skill assessment and hindcasts ', ' ', ' Present data findings to internal and external audiences and contribute to the publications in scientific journals ', ' ', 'Required Qualifications*', ' ', ' A bachelor’s degree in the natural sciences, engineering, or related field ', ' ', ' 1 or more years of experience in ecological data, research and professional activities (e.g., large gridded data sets from model output or remote sensing ', ' ', ' Ability to analyze data, measure uncertainty, and report results promptly ', ' ', ' Ability to discreetly handle sensitive sampling data ', ' ', ' Strong communication skills ', ' ', ' Demonstrated ability to work in a collaborative environment and independently ', ' ', 'Desired Qualifications*', ' ', ' Master’s degree preferred ', ' ', ' Experience handling ecological and geophysical data in multiple formats such as ASCII, NetCDF and familiarity with a linux/unix computing environment. ', ' ', ' Experience with hydrodynamic/ocean modeling ', ' ', ' Experience with scripting data analysis software such as R, IDL, Python, or Matlab ', ' ', 'Additional Information', 'Salary will be determined by experience.', 'The University of Michigan offers excellent benefits and wellness opportunities.', 'You will receive vacation and sick leave with provisions for extended benefits, and opportunities for professional development activities through the University and travel to professional meetings . TIAA-CREF and Fidelity Investments retirement options available.', 'Application Deadline', 'Job openings are posted for a minimum of seven calendar days. The review and selection process may begin as early as the eighth day after posting. This opening may be removed from posting boards and filled anytime after the minimum posting period has ended.', 'U-M EEO/AA Statement', 'The University of Michigan is an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer.', 'Seniority level', 'Entry level', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Higher Education']

Name: Research Data Analyst I-(ISUDT)
Description: ['Department Name: California Correctional Health Care Services Region: Northern California Time Base/FT/PT: Full Time Closing Date/FFD: Until Filled', 'Research Data Analyst I-Integrated Substance-use Disorder Treatment Program (ISUDT)', '$64,872 - $81,252 Annual Range', 'CCHCS seeks to fill a permanent/full-time Research Data Specialist I position in the Electronic Health Records System Documentation and Decision Support, Medical Services Division.', 'Under general direction of the Research Data Manager of the EHRS Documentation and Decision Support Unit, the Research Data Specialist (RDS) I supports the day-to-day clinical management of the Integrated Substance-use Disorder Treatment (ISUDT) Program, and other related complex patient populations by independently developing, building, testing, and implementing front-end decision-support and documentation methods in EHRS using selected Cerner Millennium Tier I,II, and III software packages, Structured Querying Language (SQL) and Cerner Command Language (CCL) to ensure providers have effective, patient-centered tools to support communication, timeliness, and efficiency at the point-of-care. The RDS I engages with Information Technology (IT) and clinical staff to evaluate the adequacy of existing Cerner tools; and develops procedures for the movement and integration of clinical information within EHRS to ensure clinical staff have required information to support their decision-making at the point of care. The RDS I will serve in a leading role for routine to intermediate complex projects and will develop and manage a project work plan as well as ensure the completion of projects under critical timelines to meet project objectives and deadlines.', 'Please review the CalHR Job Control 176784 for more information and to apply.', 'Contact Debronna.Sanders@cdcr.ca.gov for your questions regarding the application process, and status of your application.', 'EOE', 'Apply Now Save This Vacancy', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Research', 'Analyst', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Government Administration', 'Health, Wellness and Fitness', 'Hospital & Health Care']

Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['The ', ' Data Analyst, Kronos ', ' is responsible for system analysis of all Kronos applications (Workforce Timekeeper, Workforce Absence Manager, Attendance, Attestation, Workforce Integration Manager (WIM), and Workforce TeleStaff). You will work closely with the Operations Workforce Management team and Kronos System Administration teams to implement TeleStaff initiatives. Assesses Human Resources needs and formulates solutions, through the use of the Kronos application suite and other tools. In addition, you will work closely with Payroll and JD Edwards support teams in assessing payroll related issues and initiatives.', "Responsibilities include system and data analysis, report analysis, system configuration support, leadership of testing efforts, and support of problem solving efforts. Responsible for the setup configuration of all modules in the Kronos application suite. Provides analytical and testing support for maintenance, implementation and upgrade of all modules in the Kronos application suite. Collaborates with functional areas in writing GAP's, use case scenarios, and test plans.", 'Essential Functions', ' Identifies system and application needs to support business goals. ', ' Analyzes current business practices and system workflows. Identifies potential issues within the application and recommends procedural or application changes. ', ' Provides primary system and data analysis for all application and system interface issues that may arise. ', ' Responsible for identifying trends, reporting to leadership, developing proactive responses with the system administration team to resolve the issues. ', ' Serves as Tier 2 support, along with system administration support, by providing needed analysis and testing support. ', ' Maintains knowledge of implemented application data schemas. Utilizes provided queried data and report outputs to analyze system performance and issues. Increases understanding of application function, and shares application knowledge with enterprise business intelligence team and Kronos system administration team. ', ' Identifies issues with reports, verifies corrections to reports, and proactively identifies report improvement. ', ' Performs overall Kronos configuration with the Kronos system administration team. Ensures accuracy and reliability of data. ', ' Maintains Kronos Pay Rules, answers questions pertaining to rules, modifies existing rules, and creates new rules. ', ' Documents and updates documentation of recurring tasks and recurring issue resolution. ', ' Maintains relationships with customer departments (HRIS, Payroll, HR, and WFM) to ensure all support is provided in the context of assisting application users succeed in their business goals. ', ' Assesses HR needs by soliciting requirements from business sponsors, owners, stakeholders, subject matter experts, vendors, and other IT staff to formulate solutions with the use of the Kronos application suite. ', ' Leads and/or participates in regression, integration and user acceptance testing to ensure Kronos enhancements meet the outlined requirements. ', " Collaborates with process owners, developers, administrators and Program Managers on GAP's, design specifications, Kronos/Data Mart mapping, and cost analysis for new project requests. ", ' Participates in planned quarterly technology outages. ', ' Domestic U.S. travel may be required. ', 'About Us', ' CoreCivic ', ' is a diversified government solutions company with the scale and experience needed to solve tough government challenges in cost-effective ways. We provide a broad range of solutions to government partners that serve the public good through high-quality corrections and detention management, innovative and cost-saving government real estate solutions, and a growing network of residential reentry centers to help address Americas recidivism crisis. We are a publicly traded real estate investment trust (REIT) and the nations largest owner of partnership correctional, detention and residential reentry facilities. We have been a flexible and dependable partner for government for more than 30 years.', ' Professionalism. Respect. Integrity. Duty. Excellence (PRIDE). ', ' These words describe the essence of our values as a company. ', ' PRIDE ', ' is personified everyday by every employee at every level at CoreCivic. It shapes the choices we make and is the roadmap to how we achieve our mission and realize our vision. CoreCivic is the leader in private correctional facilities and we are growing into the leader in the rehabilitation and re-entry market with facilities nationwide. Our facilities make a difference with the giving of both time and resources to organizations that are doing important work locally. CoreCivic is always recognized as a valued partner because of our unwavering commitment to community. Learn more at', 'Minimum Qualifications', " Graduate from an accredited college or university with a Bachelor's degree in computer systems analysis, computer science, computer information systems (CIS), management information systems (MIS), business intelligence or a similar field of study. ", ' Four years of experience with Kronos Workforce Timekeeper or Kronos Workforce TeleStaff (Advanced Scheduling System) in analyst, or a similar level position. ', ' Additional years of related experience may be substituted for the educational requirement on a year-for-year basis. ', ' Ability to prioritize and balance multiple tasks simultaneously and meet deadlines. ', ' Strong analytical, interpersonal, organizational, and communication skills. ', ' Ability to participate in on call support. ', ' Must have exceptional critical thinking, analytical skills and attention to detail. ', ' Ability to communicate effectively with business and technical staff, including the ability to document and convey complex ideas both verbally and in written form. ', ' Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications. ', ' A valid drivers license is required. ', 'Prefferred Qualifications', ' Five years of related experience. ', ' Experience with Oracle SQL and PL/SQL, Microsoft SQLServer, and Crystal Reports. ', ' Experience supporting DSIs Offender Management System, and/or Allscripts Touchworks electronic medical record system. ', ' Experience with and thorough understanding of Kronos pay rules. ', ' Experience working within a project management matrix organization. Name: Data Analyst
Description: ['Essential Duties and Responsibilities:', '• Support production processing including identifying and troubleshooting issues for ISO', '\xa0reporting.', '• Process and balance policy and claim data from multiple data sources, and', '\xa0analyze data for completeness, accuracy, and anomalies.\xa0', '• Research and determine root cause of data errors and identifies solutions.\xa0', '• Create and maintain comprehensive system and process documentation.\xa0', '• Perform statistical data reconciliation across systems and addresses discrepancies.\xa0', '• Research and interpret statistical requirements, including identifying and translating', '\xa0reporting needs for regulatory changes and expanded statistical reporting services (new', '\xa0states and/or mechanisms).\xa0', '• Document processing requirements and collaborate with Programming to define', '\xa0system changes.\xa0', '• Support testing of changes/enhancements to the ISO Reporting system.\xa0', '• Serve as liaison with the Policy & Claim vendors to identify and address data issues.\xa0', '• Identify opportunities to improve product quality and streamline processes.\xa0', '• Serve as project lead for statistical reporting projects to expand services.\xa0', '• Provide training to other team members on statistical reporting.\xa0', 'Education:', "Bachelor's degree (BA/BS) from four-year college or university in Statistical/Data Analysis or related field preferred.\xa0Additional appropriate experience or training may be considered in lieu of degree.", 'Experience:', '3 or more years of statistical reporting experience in the insurance industry, preferably automobile insurance. Experience in researching statistical manuals, interpreting regulatory requirements, identifying business needs, and defining system solutions.', 'Skills and Knowledge:', '• Strong knowledge of statistical regulatory business rules and requirements.\xa0', '• Strong analytical skills to research, interpret and assess impact of regulatory needs.\xa0', '• Knowledge of technology platforms and software such as job scheduling software is a', '\xa0plus.', '• Proficient in the use of Microsoft Office productivity tools (e.g. Outlook, Word, Excel) to', '\xa0manage work.\xa0', '• Effective problem-solving skills, including ability to analyze complex issues, find the root', '\xa0cause of the problem, and consider a wide range of alternatives before acting.\xa0', '• Demonstrate strong verbal and written communication skills, including ability to', '\xa0effectively present information and respond to questions from groups or individuals.\xa0', '• Ability to multi-task and demonstrate flexibility while maintaining attention to detail.\xa0', '• Demonstrate excellent organizational and customer service skills.\xa0', '• Ability to work independently and interact professionally and effectively in a team', '\xa0environment.', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Analyst', 'Quality Assurance', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Insurance']

Name: Reporting Analyst (Qualitative and Quantitative)
Location: Salt Lake City, Utah, United States
Description: ['The Analyst on the Reporting team has the primary responsibility to analyze quantitative and qualitative buyer, customer and seller data and create in-depth actionable reports. The analyst will compose reports with concise written intelligence summaries, recommendations, and supporting visuals and evidence. In addition, the analyst will provide recommendations to improve reports and/or new reporting deliverables.', 'Requirements', ' Essential Duties & Responsibilities ', ' ', ' Prepare both standardized and custom reports for Win Loss, Customer Experience, ', ' Competitive Intelligence ', ' and custom market research programs. ', ' ', ' Synthesize findings from a broad dataset and reduce into a consumable format while maintaining accuracy. ', ' ', ' Utilize Excel and PowerPoint to manipulate data and create visually appealing graphics. ', ' ', ' Analyze buyer and seller interviews to identify pertinent and actionable intelligence in each dataset. ', ' ', ' Create summary and/or analysis of quantitative and qualitative data that synthesizes the key learnings from buyer, customer and/or seller interviews. ', ' ', ' Align findings with clients’ objectives. Approach each dataset with focus on extracting most important takeaways ', ' from that particular set of findings. ', ' ', ' ', ' Collaborate with Partner/Consultant to craft top takeaways and recommendations for clients based on findings. ', ' ', ' Prioritize tasks to meet deadlines working with team members where needed. ', ' ', ' Recommend new reporting formats and/or deliverables. ', ' ', 'Required Education & Experience', ' ', ' 2-5 years of experience as a Business Analyst or similar role. ', ' ', ' A high proficiency with Microsoft Office applications, ', ' including Excel and PowerPoint. ', ' ', ' ', ' Experience with quantitative and qualitative research; experience specifically with market research. ', ' ', ' Demonstrated ability to analyze both quantitative and qualitative data; past experience with employing analytical techniques to address a specific problem. ', ' ', ' Demonstrated ability to draw conclusions and craft advice for tailored audiences. ', ' ', ' Excellent verbal, written, interpersonal, and presentation skills with the ability to communicate effectively with a wide variety of audiences. ', ' ', ' Ability to manage multiple projects at once and adapt to changing priorities while maintaining excellence. ', ' ', 'Preferred Education & Experience', ' ', ' BS/BA in business communication, social sciences, English, journalism, literature, or other liberal arts is preferred ', ' ', ' Experience working with large complex B2B service sales ', ' ', 'Benefits', 'Open PTO', '401k Profit Sharing', 'Medical, Dental, Vision', 'FSA', 'Seniority level', 'Associate', 'Employment type', 'Full-time', 'Job function', 'Information Technology', 'Industries', 'Marketing and Advertising', 'Market Research', 'Research']
